ntract.md`.\n165: \n166: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n167: \n168: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n169: \n170: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n171: \n172: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n173: \n174: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n175: \n176: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n177: \n178: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n179: \n180: ```yaml\n181: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n182:   research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n183:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n184:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n185:   maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n186:   convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n187:   executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code | cli-opencode\n188:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n189:   executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n190:   executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n191:   executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n192:   executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n193:   resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n194: ```\n195: \n196: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n197: \n198: ### Default Resolution Table\n199: \n200: | Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n201: | -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n202: | `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n203: | `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n204: | `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n205: | `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n206: | `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n207: | `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n208: | `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n209: | `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n210: | `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n211: | `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n212: | `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n213: | `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n214: | `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n215: | `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n216: \n217: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n218: ~~~\n219: <!-- END renderBlocks.auto -->\n220: \n221: ## renderBlocks.confirm\n222: \n223: Rule: render the marked block verbatim; do not paraphrase, summarize, reorder, or substitute inside the START/END boundary.\n224: \n225: <!-- START renderBlocks.confirm -->\n226: ~~~markdown\n227: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n228: \n229: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n230: \n231: ```\n232: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n233: \n234: 1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n235:    |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n236:    |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n237:    +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n238: \n239: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n240:    |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n241:    |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n242:    +-- Empty -> include Q0\n243: \n244: 3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n245:    |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n246:    |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n247:    |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n248:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code` | `cli-opencode`)\n249:    |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n250:    |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n251:    |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n252:    |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n253:    |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n254:    |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n255:    |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n256:    |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n257:    |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n258:    |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n259:    |\n260:    |   Fan-out default policy:\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 479. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- GENERATED_COMMAND_CONTRACT_HEADER_START\n{\n  \"id\": \"deep/research\",\n  \"command\": \"/deep:research\",\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"generatedBy\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs\",\n  \"sourceDigests\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/research.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"d0b29d814e0b47a5876c942beab504e93fe838f55fff8813c4fe88069e8b96f5\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt\",\n      \"sha256\": \"ef9fd8156deccea8f0bf332c7eea4378f28d3b6b6937d8bea00198a8ae15db2e\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"cc283b7c5e62bd8b012a8f249f4cc63f4f353ad264358e1a5c9b85d753713d64\",","truncated":true,"lo