{"type":"text","timestamp":1783486581177,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f40157469001zxVrUzF00mWcKJ","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","type":"text","text":"The compiled contract confirms this is an autonomous pre-bound run and Gate 3 is already satisfied by the supplied spec folder. I’m now extracting only the workflow steps needed for init, loop validation, convergence, and synthesis.","time":{"start":1783486575721,"end":1783486581176},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ff6f2d6d173666b016a4dd86fb810819187abfe0e71533dde","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486581212,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_9boCmLvS7sqI2kH88Lhr0HyB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"phase_main_loop|phase_synthesis|post_dispatch|reduce-state|dispatch|opencode run|convergence|step_synthesize|step_save|step_update|step_render|step_validate","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","include":"*.yaml"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 52:     graph_convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --loop-type council\n\n  Line 110:           convergenceThreshold: \"{saturation_threshold}\"\n\n  Line 130:           - executor_config: \"Executor config with seats, cost guards, and dispatch/adjudication functions\"\n\n  Line 148:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_agent-improvement_auto.yaml:\n  Line 94:     reducer: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 207:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 219:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_agent-improvement_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 100:     reducer: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 228:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 250:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_model-benchmark_auto.yaml:\n  Line 40:   grader: \"[GRADER] - 'noop' deterministic no-dispatch grader, 'mock', or 'llm' (model dispatch). Default: noop.\"\n\n  Line 43:   target_model: \"[TARGET_MODEL] - Model identifier dispatched only when grader=llm. Optional; ignored for noop/mock graders.\"\n\n  Line 94:     dispatch_model: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs\n\n  Line 97:     reducer: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 175:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 183:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 187:         description: \"Render the final dashboard via reduce-state and present benchmark trends and stop reason\"\n\n  Line 188:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_model-benchmark_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 40:   grader: \"[GRADER] - 'noop' deterministic no-dispatch grader, 'mock', or 'llm' (model dispatch). Default: noop.\"\n\n  Line 43:   target_model: \"[TARGET_MODEL] - Model identifier dispatched only when grader=llm. Optional; ignored for noop/mock graders.\"\n\n  Line 99:     dispatch_model: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs\n\n  Line 102:     reducer: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 197:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 216:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 220:         description: \"Render the final dashboard via reduce-state and present benchmark trends and stop reason\"\n\n  Line 221:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection and user approval gates\n\n  Line 15:   validation: convergence_detection\n\n  Line 36:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n\n  Line 62:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n\n  Line 141:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n\n  Line 142:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n\n  Line 143:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n\n  Line 160:         dispatch:\n\n  Line 169:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n\n  Line 182:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n\n  Line 279:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 376:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n\n  Line 390:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n\n  Line 395:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n\n  Line 408:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n\n  Line 428:           **Convergence Threshold**: {convergence_threshold}\n\n  Line 499:       step_graph_convergence:\n\n  Line 500:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n\n  Line 505:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n\n  Line 510:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n\n  Line 511:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n\n  Line 512:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n\n  Line 515:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n\n  Line 520:       step_check_convergence:\n\n  Line 523:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n\n  Line 531:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n\n  Line 535:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n\n  Line 539:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n\n  Line 557:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n\n  Line 572:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n\n  Line 573:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n\n  Line 613:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n\n  Line 621:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n\n  Line 622:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n\n  Line 644:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n\n  Line 645:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n\n  Line 653:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n\n  Line 658:       step_handle_convergence:\n\n  Line 659:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n\n  Line 702:         purpose: \"Show planned dimension focus and get approval before dispatching agent\"\n\n  Line 719:         on_A: { proceed_to: step_dispatch_iteration }\n\n  Line 720:         on_B: { action: \"Update next_dimension to user's choice\", proceed_to: step_dispatch_iteration }\n\n  Line 724:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n\n  Line 729:         pre_dispatch:\n\n  Line 761:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n\n  Line 770:           dispatch:\n\n  Line 820:             opencode run \\\n\n  Line 837:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n\n  Line 840:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n\n  Line 842:         post_dispatch_validate:\n\n  Line 843:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n\n  Line 861:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n\n  Line 873:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n\n  Line 917:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n\n  Line 921:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n  Line 925:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n\n  Line 1043:       step_update_tracking:\n\n  Line 1063:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 1191:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n\n  Line 1250:       step_convergence_report:\n\n  Line 1251:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n\n  Line 1255:       step_update_config_status:\n\n  Line 1357:     p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n\n  Line 1381:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and show to user for decision.\"\n\n  Line 1392:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n\n  Line 1393:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n\n  Line 1403:     - skip_convergence_check\n\n  Line 1404:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_auto.yaml:\n  Line 52:     graph_convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --loop-type council\n\n  Line 103:           convergenceThreshold: \"{saturation_threshold}\"\n\n  Line 116:           - executor_config: \"Executor config with seats, cost guards, dispatch/adjudication functions, resolved_route_header, and route_fields\"\n\n  Line 127:           contract: \"Per-seat stepwise persistence (GAP-32/GAP-36). Each seat is persisted as it returns via persist-artifacts.cjs --seat (lib/persist-artifacts.cjs#persistSeatStepwise) WITHOUT requiring the full report sections, so one seat's dispatch cannot fail because other seats have not returned yet.\"\n\n  Line 133:         post_dispatch_validate:\n\n  Line 146:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"phase_main_loop|phase_synthesis|post_dispatch|reduce-state|dispatch|opencode run|convergence|step_synthesize|step_save|step_update|step_render|step_validate","time":{"start":1783486581199,"end":1783486581211}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff6f2d6d173666b016a4dd875273481918ee417fe95b14290"}},"id":"prt_f401589b90015QcQ27lf4WbtAT","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486581221,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_I3fpKQF0gxBe3fgWML2ffhIU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":261,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n261:           gate3_classification: write-path\n262:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n263:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: phase_loop\n266:         on_restart:\n267:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n268:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n269:           set:\n270:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n271:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n272:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n273:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n274:           skip_to: step_create_config\n275:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n276:         on_completed_session:\n277:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n278:           halt: true\n279:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n280:         on_invalid_state:\n281:           halt: true\n282:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n283:         on_fresh:\n284:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n285: \n286:       step_resolve_session_id:\n287:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n288:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n289:         if_present:\n290:           bind:\n291:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n292:         if_absent:\n293:           bind:\n294:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n295: \n296:       step_create_config:\n297:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n298:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n299:         populate:\n300:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n301:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n302:           minIterations: 3\n303:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n304:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n305:           convergenceMode: \"default\"\n306:           stuckThreshold: 3\n307:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n308:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n309:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n310:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n311:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n312:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n313:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n314:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n315:           status: \"initialized\"\n316:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n317:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n318:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n319:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n320:           lineage.generation: 1\n321:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n322:           nextRunAt: null\n323:           remainingDelayMs: null\n324:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n325: \n326:       step_create_state_log:\n327:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n328:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n329:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n330:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n331: \n332:       step_create_strategy:\n333:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n334:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n335:         populate:\n336:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n337:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n338:           known_context: \"None\"\n339:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n340:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n341:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n342:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343: \n344:       step_create_registry:\n345:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n346:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n347:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n348: \n349:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n350:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n351:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n352:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n353:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n354: \n355:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n356:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n357:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n358:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n359: \n360:       step_detect_spec_present:\n361:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n362:         inspect:\n363:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n364:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n365:         classify:\n366:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n367:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n368:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n369:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n370:         outputs:\n371:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n372:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n373:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n374: \n375:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n376:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n377:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n378:         branches:\n379:           no-spec:\n380:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n381:             seed_markers:\n382:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n383:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n384:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n385:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n386:             set:\n387:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n388:               validate_spec_doc: true\n389:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n390:           spec-present:\n391:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n392:             set:\n393:               validate_spec_doc: true\n394:             idempotency_check:\n395:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n396:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n397:               if_match:\n398:                 skip_append: true\n399:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n400:               if_no_match:\n401:                 append_only:\n402:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n403:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n404:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n405:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n406:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n407:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n408:             verify_markers:\n409:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n410:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n411:             set:\n412:               validate_spec_doc: false\n413:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n414:           conflict-detected:\n415:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n416:             halt: true\n417: \n418:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n419:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n420:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n421:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n422:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n423: \n424:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n425:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n426:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n427:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n428:         command: |\n429:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n430:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n431: \n432:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n433:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n434: \n435:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n436:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n437:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n438:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n439:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n440:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n441:           const row = {\n442:             event: 'started',\n443:             label: 'single',\n444:             at: timestamp,\n445:             duration_ms: 0,\n446:             loop_type: 'research',\n447:             sessionId,\n448:             generation,\n449:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n450:           };\n451: \n452:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n453:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n454:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n455:           });\n456:           if (appended) {\n457:             try {\n458:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n459:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n460:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n461:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n462:                 event: row.event,\n463:                 status: 'running',\n464:               });\n465:             } catch {}\n466:           }\n467:           EOF\n468:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n469:         outputs:\n470:           - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n471: \n472:       step_init_complete:\n473:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n474:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n475: \n476:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n477:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n478:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n479:   phase_loop:\n480:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n481:     repeat: true\n482:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n483:     steps:\n484: \n485:       step_read_state:\n486:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n487:         read:\n488:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n489:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n490:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n491:         extract:\n492:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n493:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n494:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n495:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n496:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n497:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n498:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n499:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n500:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n501:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n502:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n503:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n504:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n505:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n506:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n507:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n508:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n509:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n510:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n511:           - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n512:           - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n513:           - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n514:           - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n515:           - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n516:           - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n517:           - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n518:           - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n519:           - convergence_mode: \"Extract convergenceMode when it is 'default' or 'off'; default to 'default'\"\n520:           - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n521:           - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n522:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n523:           - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n524:           - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n525:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n526:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n527:           - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n528:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n529: \n530:       step_run_now_check:\n531:         action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n532:         command: |\n533:           node <<'EOF'\n534:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n535: \n536:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n537:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n538:           const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n539:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n540:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n541:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n542:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n543: \n544:           function append(event) {\n545:             appendFileSync(\n546:               stateLogPath,\n547:               `${JSON.stringify({\n548:                 type: \"event\",\n549:                 mode: \"research\",\n550:                 run,\n551:                 timestamp,\n552:                 sessionId,\n553:                 generation,\n554:                 ...event,\n555:               })}\\n`,\n556:               \"utf8\",\n557:             );\n558:           }\n559: \n560:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n561:             append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n562:             if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n563:               append({\n564:                 event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n565:                 reason: \"loop_paused\",\n566:                 sentinelPath,\n567:                 pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n568:               });\n569:             } else {\n570:               const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n571:               try {\n572:                 renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n573:                 unlinkSync(claimPath);\n574:                 append({\n575:                   event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n576:                   sentinelPath,\n577:                   dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n578:                 });\n579:               } catch (error) {\n580:                 if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n581:                   throw error;\n582:                 }\n583:               }\n584:             }\n585:           }\n586:           EOF\n587:         outputs:\n588:           - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n589:           - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n590:           - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n591: \n592:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n593:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n594:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n595:         if_exists:\n596:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n597:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n598:           halt: true\n599:         if_not_exists:\n600:           proceed: true\n601: \n602:       step_validate_convergence_config:\n603:         action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n604:         if_min_iterations_missing:\n605:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n606:           log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n607:         if_min_iterations_clamped:\n608:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n609:           log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n610:         if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n611:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n612:           log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n613: \n614:       step_graph_convergence:\n615:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n616:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n617:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n618:         outputs:\n619:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n620:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n\n(Showing lines 261-620 of 1740. Use offset=621 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          convergenceMode: \"default\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n                event: row.event,\n                status: 'running',\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n          - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n          - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n          - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n          - convergence_mode: \"Extract convergenceMode when it is 'default' or 'off'; default to 'default'\"\n          - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n          - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n          - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n          - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n\n      step_run_now_check:\n        action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function append(event) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n                ...event,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n            append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n            if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n              append({\n                event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n                reason: \"loop_paused\",\n                sentinelPath,\n                pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n              });\n            } else {\n              const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n              try {\n                renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n                unlinkSync(claimPath);\n                append({\n                  event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n                  sentinelPath,\n                  dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n                });\n              } catch (error) {\n                if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n                  throw error;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n          - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n          - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_validate_convergence_config:\n        action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n        if_min_iterations_missing:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n        if_min_iterations_clamped:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n        if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"","lineStart":261,"lineEnd":620,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486581214,"end":1783486581218}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff6f2d6d173666b016a4dd87527448191b12370f2e422b336"}},"id":"prt_f401589d0001k0M7Y8YWsLBLlU","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486581223,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PGIxkinx9HIE2jNfMT2R1oeM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: State Format Reference\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state format\"\n6:   - \"research state packet hub\"\n7:   - \"research file ownership model\"\n8:   - \"research file protection rules\"\n9:   - \"research packet location\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # State Format Reference\n16: \n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n30: \n31: ### Routed Details\n32: \n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n36: \n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n38: \n39: ### Packet Summary\n40: \n41: The deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n42: \n43: | File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n44: |------|--------|---------|------------|\n45: | `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n46: | `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n47: | `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n48: | `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n49: | `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n50: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n51: | `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n52: | `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n53: | `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n54: \n55: The artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n60: \n61: Root specs use:\n62: \n63: ```text\n64: {spec_folder}/research/\n65: ```\n66: \n67: Child-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n68: \n69: - first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n70: - a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n71: - continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n72: \n73: This avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n78: \n79: | Owner | Writes |\n80: |-------|--------|\n81: | Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n82: | Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n83: | Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n84: | Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n85: \n86: The reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n91: \n92: | Protection | Meaning |\n93: |------------|---------|\n94: | `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n95: | `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n96: | `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n97: | `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n98: | `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n99: \n100: The config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n105: \n106: | Resource | Use When |\n107: |----------|----------|\n108: | `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n109: | `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n110: | `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n111: | `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n112: | `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n117: \n118: - Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n119: - Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n120: - Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.\n\n(End of file - total 120 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSummarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n\n### Routed Details\n\n- `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n- `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n- `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n\nFor iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n\n### Packet Summary\n\nThe deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n\n| File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n|------|--------|---------|------------|\n| `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n| `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n| `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n| `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n| `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n| `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n| `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n| `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n\nThe artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n\nRoot specs use:\n\n```text\n{spec_folder}/research/\n```\n\nChild-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n\n- first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n- a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n- continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n\nThis avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n\n| Owner | Writes |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n| Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n| Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n| Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n\nThe reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n\n| Protection | Meaning |\n|------------|---------|\n| `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n| `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n| `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n| `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n| `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n\nThe config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n| `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n| `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n| `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n| `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n- Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n- Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":120,"totalLines":120,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1783486581219,"end":1783486581222}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff6f2d6d173666b016a4dd875274c819190946a74025aa4a9"}},"id":"prt_f401589df001qwqmmaeJ7ZcyHw","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486581236,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6rOsFCVwAvqq5AweUGFjrRTZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","offset":1,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"research config record\"\n7:   - \"research iteration records\"\n8:   - \"research negative knowledge\"\n9:   - \"research graph events\"\n10:   - \"research event records\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n17: \n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n39: \n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"type\": \"config\",\n45:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n46:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n47:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n48:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n49:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n50:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n51: }\n52: ```\n53: \n54: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n59: \n60: ```json\n61: {\n62:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n63:   \"run\": 1,\n64:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n65:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n66:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n67:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n68:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n69:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n70:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n71:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n72:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: | Field | Required | Notes |\n77: |-------|----------|-------|\n78: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n79: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n80: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n81: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n82: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n83: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n84: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n85: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n86: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n87: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n88: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n89: \n90: Status values:\n91: \n92: | Status | Meaning |\n93: |--------|---------|\n94: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n95: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n96: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n97: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n98: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n99: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n104: \n105: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n106: \n107: ```json\n108: {\n109:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n110:   \"run\": 5,\n111:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n112:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n113:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n114:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n115:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n116:   }\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n125: \n126: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n127: \n128: ```json\n129: {\n130:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n131:   \"run\": 3,\n132:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n133:   \"ruledOut\": [\n134:     {\n135:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n136:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n137:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n138:     }\n139:   ]\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n148: \n149: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n150: \n151: ```json\n152: {\n153:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n154:   \"run\": 4,\n155:   \"graphEvents\": [\n156:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n157:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n158:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n159:   ]\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n168: \n169: Lifecycle event:\n170: \n171: ```json\n172: {\n173:   \"type\": \"event\",\n174:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n175:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n176:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n177:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n178:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n179:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n180:   \"generation\": 1,\n181:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n182:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: Blocked stop event:\n187: \n188: ```json\n189: {\n190:   \"type\": \"event\",\n191:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n192:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n193:   \"run\": 7,\n194:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n195:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n196:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n197:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Pause event:\n202: \n203: ```json\n204: {\n205:   \"type\": \"event\",\n206:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n207:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n208:   \"run\": 7,\n209:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n210:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n211:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: Stuck recovery event:\n216: \n217: ```json\n218: {\n219:   \"type\": \"event\",\n220:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n221:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n222:   \"run\": 7,\n223:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n224:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n225:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n226:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n227:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Idea observation event:\n232: \n233: ```json\n234: {\n235:   \"type\": \"event\",\n236:   \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n237:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n238:   \"run\": 7,\n239:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n240:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n241:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n242:   \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n243:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n248: \n249: Idea promotion event:\n250: \n251: ```json\n252: {\n253:   \"type\": \"event\",\n254:   \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n255:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n256:   \"run\": 8,\n257:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n258:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n259:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n260:   \"observationCount\": 2,\n261:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n262:   \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n263:   \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n264:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: The reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n269: \n270: Rejected idea event:\n271: \n272: ```json\n273: {\n274:   \"type\": \"event\",\n275:   \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n276:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n277:   \"run\": 7,\n278:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n279:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n280:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n281:   \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n282:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: `idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n287: \n288: Rejected idea removal event:\n289: \n290: ```json\n291: {\n292:   \"type\": \"event\",\n293:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n294:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n295:   \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n296:   \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n297:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n301: Rejected idea reset event:\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"type\": \"event\",\n306:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedReset\",\n307:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n308:   \"reason\": \"Operator wants previously rejected ideas eligible again\",\n309:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n310: }\n311: ```\n312: \n313: The reducer derives a bounded active rejected-pattern cache from these events. `idea_rejected` adds or refreshes one pattern, `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single matching pattern or id, and `ideaRejectedReset` clears the active cache. Legacy `ideaRejected`, `ideaRejectedRemoved`, and `ideaRejectedReset` rows remain replayable for existing state logs. The active cache is capped at 100 entries; when more are added, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning.\n314: \n315: Candidate checks compare normalized exact text first, then apply fuzzy matching only when the candidate category is compatible with the rejected category. Omit `category` for a general rejection that can suppress candidates across next-focus, recovery, or ideas surfaces.\n316: \n317: Graph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n\n(Showing lines 1-320 of 325. Use offset=321 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nIdea observation event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nLeaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n\nIdea promotion event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 8,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"observationCount\": 2,\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n  \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n\nRejected idea event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n`idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n\nRejected idea removal event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n  \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nRejected idea reset event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedReset\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"reason\": \"Operator wants previously rejected ideas eligible again\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer derives a bounded active rejected-pattern cache from these events. `idea_rejected` adds or refreshes one pattern, `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single matching pattern or id, and `ideaRejectedReset` clears the active cache. Legacy `ideaRejected`, `ideaRejectedRemoved`, and `ideaRejectedReset` rows remain replayable for existing state logs. The active cache is capped at 100 entries; when more are added, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning.\n\nCandidate checks compare normalized exact text first, then apply fuzzy matching only when the candidate category is compatible with the rejected category. Omit `category` for a general rejection that can suppress candidates across next-focus, recovery, or ideas surfaces.\n\nGraph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n\n---\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":320,"totalLines":325,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1783486581232,"end":1783486581235}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff6f2d6d173666b016a4dd87527508191a0402a57233827e8"}},"id":"prt_f401589e4001l5KaYR9nCa9XRp","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486581240,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2ZY7McscwAhLQvyzTq6Whcm1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n58: \n59: ### stopReason Values\n60: \n61: | Value | When It Is Used |\n62: |-------|-----------------|\n63: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n64: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n65: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n66: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n67: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n68: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n69: \n70: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n71: \n72: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n73: \n74: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n75: |------------------------|------------------|\n76: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n77: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n78: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n79: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n80: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n81: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n82: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n87: \n88: ### Decision Order\n89: \n90: ```text\n91: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n92: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n93: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n94: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n95: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n96: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n97: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n98: 8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Composite Signal Weights\n102: \n103: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n104: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n105: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n106: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n107: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n108: \n109: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n114: \n115: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n116: \n117: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n118: |------|------|---------|\n119: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n120: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n121: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n122: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n123: \n124: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n129: \n130: | Resource | Use When |\n131: |----------|----------|\n132: | `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n133: | `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n134: | `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n135: | `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n136: | `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n137: | `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n142: \n143: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n144: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n145: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1783486581237,"end":1783486581239}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff6f2d6d173666b016a4dd87527588191bbb63ab01ab9b4cf"}},"id":"prt_f401589f1001a0ikN2MtCmbtrJ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783486581824,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f40158c3e001bJx7Lcn2lD3tz5","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"","messageID":"msg_f401564d7001aQCGHYy3PI3PBp","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":48567,"input":18938,"output":391,"reasoning":54,"cache":{"write":0,"read":29184}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783486583223,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f401591b4001bMOwZ6cMaizX3l","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","snapshot":"1aefe6e3f18684fce5e209858ae6abafa93ea75a","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486589957,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9aWwetEmw9lXw2KyLsJs5zcB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":621,"limit":430},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n621:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n622:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n623:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n624:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n625:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n626: \n627:       step_check_convergence:\n628:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n629:         algorithm: |\n630:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n631:           2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n632:           3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n633:           4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n634:           5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n635:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n636:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n637:                signals = []\n638:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n639:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n640:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n641:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n642:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n643:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n644:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n645:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n646:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n647:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n648:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n649:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n650:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n651:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n652:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n653:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n654:                  stop_blocked = true\n655:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n656:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n657:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n658:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n659:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n660:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n661:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n662:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n663:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n664:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n665:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n666:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n667:                  stop_blocked = false\n668:           6. else: CONTINUE\n669:           7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n670:                decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n671:                reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n672:                min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n673:                min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n674:           8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n675:                min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n676:           9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n677:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n678:                if not guardResult.passed:\n679:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n680:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n681:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n682:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n683:         outputs:\n684:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n685:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n686:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n687:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n688:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n689:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n690:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n691:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n692:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n693:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n694:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n695:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n696:           - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n697:           - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n698: \n699:       step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n701:         if_pass:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n704: \n705:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n706:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n707:         if_blocked:\n708:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n709:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n710:           set:\n711:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n712:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n713:             stop_blocked: false\n714: \n715:       step_handle_convergence:\n716:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n717:         if_stop:\n718:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n719:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n720:         if_stuck_recovery:\n721:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n722:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n723:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n724:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n725:         if_continue:\n726:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n727: \n728:       step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n729:         action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n730:         read:\n731:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n732:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n733:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n734:         candidate_sources:\n735:           next_focus:\n736:             category: \"next-focus\"\n737:             values:\n738:               - \"{next_focus}\"\n739:               - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n740:               - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n741:           recovery:\n742:             category: \"recovery\"\n743:             values:\n744:               - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n745:               - \"{least_explored}\"\n746:           ideas:\n747:             category: \"ideas\"\n748:             values:\n749:               - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n750:             optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n751:         algorithm: |\n752:           Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n753:           reducer pass as the source of truth.\n754:           Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n755:           rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n756:           are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n757:           selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n758:           halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n759:         outputs:\n760:           - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n761:           - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n762:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n763:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n764:         if_next_focus_suppressed:\n765:           set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n766:           log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n767:         if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n768:           halt: true\n769:           message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n770: \n771:       step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n772:         action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n773:         read:\n774:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n775:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n776:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n777:         lifecycle:\n778:           observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n779:           promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n780:           rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n781:           min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n782:           authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n783:         validate:\n784:           - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n785:           - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n786:           - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n787:         outputs:\n788:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n789:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n790:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n791:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n792: \n793:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n794:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n795:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n796:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n797:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n798:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n799:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n800:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n801:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n802: \n803:       step_marker_scan:\n804:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n805:         algorithm: |\n806:           if current_iteration > 1:\n807:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n808:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n809:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n810:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n811:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n812:                 halt with exit code 2\n813:         note: |\n814:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n815:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n816:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n817:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n818: \n819:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n820:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n821:         resolve_executor:\n822:           source: \"config.executor\"\n823:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n824:         pre_dispatch:\n825:           generate_summary: |\n826:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n827:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n828:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n829:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n830:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n831:             {memory_context_prompt_line}\n832:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n833:           render_prompt_pack:\n834:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n835:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n836:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n837:             variables:\n838:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n839:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n840:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n841:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n842:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n843:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n844:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n845:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n846:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n847:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n848:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n849:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n850:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n851:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n852:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n853:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n854:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n855:           args:\n856:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n857:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n858:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n859:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n860:         if_native:\n861:           dispatch:\n862:             agent: deep-research\n863:             model: opus\n864:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n865:           wait_for_completion: true\n866:         if_cli_claude_code:\n867:           command: |\n868:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n869:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n870:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n871: \n872:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n873:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n874: \n875:             const executor = {\n876:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n877:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n878:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n879:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n880:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n881:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n882:             };\n883:             const args = [\n884:               '-p',\n885:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n886:               '--model',\n887:               executor.model,\n888:               '--permission-mode',\n889:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n890:               '--output-format',\n891:               'text',\n892:             ];\n893:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n894:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n895:             }\n896: \n897:             const dispatchFacts = {\n898:               command: 'deep/research',\n899:               mode: 'research',\n900:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n901:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n902:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n903:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n904:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n905:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n906:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n907:             };\n908:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n909:             process.exit(\n910:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n911:                 command: 'claude',\n912:                 args,\n913:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n914:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n915:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n916:                 executor,\n917:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n918:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n919:                 dispatchId,\n920:               }),\n921:             );\n922:             EOF\n923:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n924:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n925:           wait_for_completion: true\n926:           notes:\n927:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n928:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n929:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n930:         record_executor_audit:\n931:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n932:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n933:           field: \"executor\"\n934:           value:\n935:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n936:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n937:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n938:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n939:         if_cli_opencode:\n940:           command: |\n941:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n942:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n943:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n944: \n945:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n946: \n947:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n948:             const executor = {\n949:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n950:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n951:               configDir: null,\n952:               reasoningEffort,\n953:               serviceTier: null,\n954:               sandboxMode: null,\n955:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n956:               governor: null,\n957:             };\n958:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n959:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n960:               + '\\n\\n'\n961:               + promptBody;\n962:             const args = [\n963:               'run',\n964:               '--model',\n965:               executor.model,\n966:               '--format',\n967:               'json',\n968:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n969:               '--pure',\n970:               '--dir',\n971:               '{repo_root}',\n972:             ];\n973:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n974:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n975:             }\n976:             args.push(message);\n977: \n978:             const dispatchFacts = {\n979:               command: 'deep/research',\n980:               mode: 'research',\n981:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n982:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n983:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n984:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n985:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n986:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n987:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n988:             };\n989:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n990:             process.exit(\n991:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n992:                 command: 'opencode',\n993:                 args,\n994:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n995:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n996:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n997:                 executor,\n998:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n999:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1000:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1001:                 input: '',\n1002:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1003:                 dispatchId,\n1004:               }),\n1005:             );\n1006:             EOF\n1007:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1008:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1009:           wait_for_completion: true\n1010:           notes:\n1011:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1012:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1013:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1014:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1015:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1016:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1017:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1018:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1019:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1020:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1021:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1022:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1023:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n1024:           route_proof:\n1025:             mode: research\n1026:             target_agent: deep-research\n1027:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1028:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n1029:           dispatchReceipt:\n1030:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1031:             dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n1032:           optional_jsonl_fields:\n1033:             logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n1034:             logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n1035:             logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n1036:             skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n1037:             slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n1038:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1039:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1040:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1041:           on_failure:\n1042:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1043:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1044:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1045:           failure_reasons_reference:\n1046:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n1047:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n1048:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n1049:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n1050:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n\n(Showing lines 621-1050 of 1740. Use offset=1051 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n          4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n          4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          6. else: CONTINUE\n          7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n               decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n               reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n               min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n          8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n          9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n\n      step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n        if_pass:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n        action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        candidate_sources:\n          next_focus:\n            category: \"next-focus\"\n            values:\n              - \"{next_focus}\"\n              - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n          recovery:\n            category: \"recovery\"\n            values:\n              - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n              - \"{least_explored}\"\n          ideas:\n            category: \"ideas\"\n            values:\n              - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n            optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n        algorithm: |\n          Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n          reducer pass as the source of truth.\n          Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n          rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n          are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n          selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n          halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n        outputs:\n          - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n        if_next_focus_suppressed:\n          set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n          log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n        if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n\n      step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n        action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        lifecycle:\n          observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n          promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n          rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n          min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n          authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n        validate:\n          - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n          - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n          - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n        outputs:\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            {memory_context_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: research\n            target_agent: deep-research\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n          optional_jsonl_fields:\n            logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n            logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n            logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n            skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n            slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"","lineStart":621,"lineEnd":1050,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486589951,"end":1783486589955}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0acb375b0dc0e304016a4dd87de074819197d8c59efd9da72f"}},"id":"prt_f4015abd8001SAE5ZVrI470pry","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486590003,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2ZuFLqGLs60pXd0fXmOtTOGT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1051,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1051:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n1052:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n1053:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n1054:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n1055:             - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n1056:             - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n1057:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n1058:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n1059: \n1060:       step_run_now_restore_check:\n1061:         action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n1062:         command: |\n1063:           node <<'EOF'\n1064:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n1065: \n1066:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n1067:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n1068:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n1069:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n1070:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n1071:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n1072: \n1073:           function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n1074:             if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n1075:             const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n1076:             for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n1077:               const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n1078:               if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n1079:               if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n1080:               if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n1081:             }\n1082:             return false;\n1083:           }\n1084: \n1085:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n1086:             appendFileSync(\n1087:               stateLogPath,\n1088:               `${JSON.stringify({\n1089:                 type: \"event\",\n1090:                 event: \"run_now_restored\",\n1091:                 mode: \"research\",\n1092:                 run,\n1093:                 sentinelPath,\n1094:                 timestamp,\n1095:                 sessionId,\n1096:                 generation,\n1097:               })}\\n`,\n1098:               \"utf8\",\n1099:             );\n1100:           }\n1101:           EOF\n1102:         outputs:\n1103:           - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n1104: \n1105:       step_reduce_state:\n1106:         action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n1107:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1108:         inputs:\n1109:           latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n1110:           newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1111:           priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1112:         outputs:\n1113:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1114:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1115:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1116:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n1117:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n1118:           - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n1119:         failure_modes:\n1120:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1121:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1122:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1123:           question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n1124:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1125: \n1126:       step_graph_upsert:\n1127:         action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n1128:         read:\n1129:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1130:         extract:\n1131:           - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n1132:           - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n1133:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n1134:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n1135:         if_graph_events_present:\n1136:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n1137:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n1138:         if_graph_events_missing:\n1139:           proceed: true\n1140: \n1141:       step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n1142:         action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n1143:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1144:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n1145:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1146:         idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n1147:         failure_policy:\n1148:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1149:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1150:         outputs:\n1151:           - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1152:           - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n1153: \n1154:       step_refresh_memory_context:\n1155:         action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n1156:         mcp_tool: memory_context\n1157:         invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n1158:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1159:         use_response:\n1160:           - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n1161:         failure_policy:\n1162:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1163:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1164:         outputs:\n1165:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n1166:           - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n1167: \n1168:       step_evaluate_results:\n1169:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1170:         verify:\n1171:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1172:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1173:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n1174:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n1175:         extract:\n1176:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1177:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1178:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1179:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1180:         on_missing_outputs:\n1181:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1182:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n1183:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n1184:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n1185: \n1186:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n1187:         action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n1188:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1189:         command: |\n1190:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1191:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1192: \n1193:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1194:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1195: \n1196:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1197:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1198:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1199:           const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n1200:           const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n1201:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1202: \n1203:           function readRecords(path) {\n1204:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1205:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1206:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1207:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1208:               .filter(Boolean)\n1209:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1210:           }\n1211: \n1212:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1213:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1214:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1215:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1216:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1217:           }\n1218: \n1219:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1220:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1221:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1222:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1223:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1224:             ?? timestamp;\n1225:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1226:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1227:           const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n1228:           const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n1229:           const row = {\n1230:             event: 'progress',\n1231:             label: 'single',\n1232:             at: timestamp,\n1233:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1234:             loop_type: 'research',\n1235:             sessionId,\n1236:             generation,\n1237:             run,\n1238:             status,\n1239:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1240:           };\n1241: \n1242:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1243:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1244:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1245:           });\n1246:           if (appended) {\n1247:             try {\n1248:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1249:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1250:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1251:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n1252:                 event: row.event,\n1253:                 status,\n1254:               });\n1255:             } catch {}\n1256:           }\n1257:           EOF\n1258:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1259:         outputs:\n1260:           - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n1261: \n1262:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1263:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n1264:         read:\n1265:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1266:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1267:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1268:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n1269:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1270:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1271: \n1272:       step_update_tracking:\n1273:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1274:         set:\n1275:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1276:           stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n1277:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1278: \n1279:       step_loop_decision:\n1280:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1281:         goto: step_read_state\n1282: \n1283:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1284:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1285:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1286:   phase_synthesis:\n1287:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n1288:     steps:\n1289: \n1290:       step_fanout_merge:\n1291:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n1292:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1293:         command: |\n1294:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1295:             --loop-type research \\\n1296:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1297:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1298:         wait_for_completion: true\n1299: \n1300:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1301:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1302:         read:\n1303:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1304:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1305:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1306:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1307:         extract:\n1308:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1309:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n1310:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n1311:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n1312:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n1313:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n1314:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n1315:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n1316:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n1317:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n1318:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n1319:           - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1320: \n1321:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1322:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1323:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1324:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1325: \n1326:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1327:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1328:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1329:         read:\n1330:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1331:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1332:         write:\n1333:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1334:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1335: \n1336:       step_compile_research:\n1337:         action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n1338:         instructions: |\n1339:           If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n1340:             1. Read current research/research.md\n1341:             2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n1342:             3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n1343:             4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n1344:             5. Add convergence report as appendix\n1345:             6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n1346: \n1347:           If research/research.md does not exist:\n1348:             1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n1349:             2. Populate sections from iteration files\n1350:             3. Add citations from original sources\n1351:             4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n1352:             5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n1353:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n1354:         output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n1355: \n1356:       step_convergence_report:\n1357:         action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n1358:         report: |\n1359:           ## Convergence Report\n1360:           - Stop reason: {reason}\n1361:           - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n1362:           - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n1363:           - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n1364:           - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n1365:           - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n1366:           - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n1367:         command: |\n1368:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1369:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1370: \n1371:           const paths = {\n1372:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1373:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.registry}`,\n1374:             research: String.raw`{state_paths.research_output}`,\n1375:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1376:           };\n1377: \n1378:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1379:             try {\n1380:               return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n1381:             } catch {\n1382:               return false;\n1383:             }\n1384:           }\n1385: \n1386:           function readJson(filePath) {\n1387:             try {\n1388:               return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n1389:             } catch {\n1390:               return null;\n1391:             }\n1392:           }\n1393: \n1394:           function readJsonl(filePath) {\n1395:             if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n1396:             return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n1397:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1398:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1399:               .filter(Boolean)\n1400:               .flatMap((line) => {\n1401:                 try {\n1402:                   return [JSON.parse(line)];\n1403:                 } catch {\n1404:                   return [];\n1405:                 }\n1406:               });\n1407:           }\n1408: \n1409:           function countIterationFindings(record) {\n1410:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n1411:             const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n1412:             if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n1413:             if (Array.isArray(record.keyFindings)) return record.keyFindings.length;\n1414:             if (Array.isArray(record.findings)) return record.findings.length;\n1415:             return 0;\n1416:           }\n1417: \n1418:           function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n1419:             return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n1420:           }\n1421: \n1422:           function findingKeys(candidate) {\n1423:             if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n1424:               const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n1425:               return key ? [key] : [];\n1426:             }\n1427:             if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n1428:             return [...new Set([\n1429:               candidate.id,\n1430:               candidate.title,\n1431:               candidate.summary,\n1432:               candidate.text,\n1433:               candidate.finding,\n1434:               candidate.description,\n1435:             ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n1436:           }\n1437: \n1438:           function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n1439:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return [];\n1440:             const structured = [record.keyFindings, record.findings]\n1441:               .find((value) => Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0);\n1442:             if (!Array.isArray(structured)) return [];\n1443:             return structured\n1444:               .map(findingKeys)\n1445:               .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n1446:           }\n1447: \n1448:           function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n1449:             if (!Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings)) return [];\n1450:             return registry.keyFindings\n1451:               .flatMap(findingKeys);\n1452:           }\n1453: \n1454:           function appendEvent(event) {\n1455:             appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n1456:           }\n1457: \n1458:           const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n1459:           const registryFindingCount = Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings) ? registry.keyFindings.length : null;\n1460:           const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n1461:           const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n1462:           const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n1463:           const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n1464:           const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n1465:           const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n1466:           const missingArtifacts = [\n1467:             ['registry', paths.registry],\n1468:             ['research', paths.research],\n1469:             ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n1470:           ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n\n(Showing lines 1051-1470 of 1740. Use offset=1471 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n            - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_run_now_restore_check:\n        action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n            - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_run_now_restore_check:\n        action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n            if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n            const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n            for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n              const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n              if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n            }\n            return false;\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                event: \"run_now_restored\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                sentinelPath,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n\n      step_reduce_state:\n        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n          question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n        extract:\n          - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n          - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n        action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_refresh_memory_context:\n        action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_context\n        invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        use_response:\n          - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n          - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n          const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n          const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'progress',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            run,\n            status,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n                event: row.event,\n                status,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md\n            2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n            3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n            4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n            5. Add convergence report as appendix\n            6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n\n          If research/research.md does not exist:\n            1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n            2. Populate sections from iteration files\n            3. Add citations from original sources\n            4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n            5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n        report: |\n          ## Convergence Report\n          - Stop reason: {reason}\n          - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n          - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n          - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n          - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n          - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n          - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.registry}`,\n            research: String.raw`{state_paths.research_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n            } catch {\n              return false;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJson(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n            } catch {\n              return null;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJsonl(filePath) {\n            if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .flatMap((line) => {\n                try {\n                  return [JSON.parse(line)];\n                } catch {\n                  return [];\n                }\n              });\n          }\n\n          function countIterationFindings(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n            const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n            if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n            if (Array.isArray(record.keyFindings)) return record.keyFindings.length;\n            if (Array.isArray(record.findings)) return record.findings.length;\n            return 0;\n          }\n\n          function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n            return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n          }\n\n          function findingKeys(candidate) {\n            if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n              const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n              return key ? [key] : [];\n            }\n            if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n            return [...new Set([\n              candidate.id,\n              candidate.title,\n              candidate.summary,\n              candidate.text,\n              candidate.finding,\n              candidate.description,\n            ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n          }\n\n          function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return [];\n            const structured = [record.keyFindings, record.findings]\n              .find((value) => Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0);\n            if (!Array.isArray(structured)) return [];\n            return structured\n              .map(findingKeys)\n              .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n          }\n\n          function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n            if (!Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings)) return [];\n            return registry.keyFindings\n              .flatMap(findingKeys);\n          }\n\n          function appendEvent(event) {\n            appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n          }\n\n          const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n          const registryFindingCount = Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings) ? registry.keyFindings.length : null;\n          const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n          const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n          const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n          const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n          const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n          const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n          const missingArtifacts = [\n            ['registry', paths.registry],\n            ['research', paths.research],\n            ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n          ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));","lineStart":1051,"lineEnd":1470,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486589985,"end":1783486590000}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0acb375b0dc0e304016a4dd87de0c881919b5930d2e9ff6aa6"}},"id":"prt_f4015ac1a001y3JE4p203FvEzV","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486590003,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_IbJ4hKjbsu8Asxh0UAwkDLvV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1471,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1471:           const invariantFailures = [];\n1472:           if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n1473:           if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_keyFindings');\n1474:           if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n1475:           if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n1476:           if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n1477: \n1478:           if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n1479:             appendEvent({\n1480:               type: 'event',\n1481:               event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n1482:               mode: 'research',\n1483:               severity: 'warning',\n1484:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1485:               answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n1486:               totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n1487:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1488:               reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n1489:               invariantFailures,\n1490:               missingArtifacts,\n1491:               registryFindingCount,\n1492:               iterationFindingCount,\n1493:               identifiableFindingCount,\n1494:               missingStructuredFindingCount,\n1495:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1496:             });\n1497:           } else {\n1498:             appendEvent({\n1499:               type: 'event',\n1500:               event: 'synthesis_complete',\n1501:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1502:               answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n1503:               totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n1504:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1505:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1506:             });\n1507:           }\n1508:           EOF\n1509: \n1510:       step_writeback_spec_findings:\n1511:         action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n1512:         edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n1513:         host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n1514:         generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n1515:         generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n1516:         fail_closed_conflict_check:\n1517:           if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n1518:             detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n1519:             on_manual_edit_conflict:\n1520:               append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1521:               halt: true\n1522:         instructions:\n1523:           - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n1524:           - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n1525:           - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n1526:           - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n1527:           - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n1528:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1529: \n1530:       step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n1531:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n1532:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n1533:         note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n1534: \n1535:       step_update_config_status:\n1536:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1537:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1538:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1539: \n1540:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_terminal:\n1541:         action: \"Emit a single-loop terminal row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n1542:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1543:         terminal_events: [completed, failed, stopped]\n1544:         command: |\n1545:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1546:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1547: \n1548:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1549:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1550: \n1551:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1552:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1553:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n1554:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1555:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{config.lineage.sessionId}');\n1556:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? '{config.lineage.generation}');\n1557:           const reason = '{reason}';\n1558:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1559: \n1560:           function readRecords(path) {\n1561:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1562:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1563:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1564:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1565:               .filter(Boolean)\n1566:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1567:           }\n1568: \n1569:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1570:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1571:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1572:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1573:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1574:           }\n1575: \n1576:           function terminalEvent(stopReason) {\n1577:             if (stopReason === 'manualStop' || stopReason === 'userPaused') return 'stopped';\n1578:             if (stopReason === 'error') return 'failed';\n1579:             return 'completed';\n1580:           }\n1581: \n1582:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1583:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1584:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1585:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1586:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1587:             ?? timestamp;\n1588:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1589:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1590:           const event = terminalEvent(reason);\n1591:           const row = {\n1592:             event,\n1593:             label: 'single',\n1594:             terminal: true,\n1595:             reason,\n1596:             at: timestamp,\n1597:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1598:             loop_type: 'research',\n1599:             sessionId,\n1600:             generation,\n1601:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1602:           };\n1603: \n1604:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1605:             diffData: { event, label: row.label, reason, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1606:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1607:           });\n1608:           if (appended) {\n1609:             try {\n1610:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1611:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1612:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1613:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, reason },\n1614:                 event,\n1615:                 status: event,\n1616:               });\n1617:             } catch {}\n1618:           }\n1619:           EOF\n1620:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1621:         outputs:\n1622:           - status_ledger_terminal: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event completed, failed, or stopped\"\n1623: \n1624:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1625:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1626:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1627:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n1628:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1629: \n1630:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1631:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1632:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1633:   phase_save:\n1634:     purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n1635:     steps:\n1636: \n1637:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1638:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1639:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1640:         requirements:\n1641:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1642:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n1643:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1644:         example_payload: |\n1645:           {\n1646:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1647:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n1648:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n1649:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n1650:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1651:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1652:           }\n1653: \n1654:       step_generate_context:\n1655:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1656:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1657:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1658: \n1659:       step_index_memory:\n1660:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1661:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1662:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1663:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1664: \n1665:       step_verify_save:\n1666:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1667:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1668:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1669: \n1670:       step_release_lock:\n1671:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1672:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1673:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1674: \n1675:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1676:   # COMPLETION\n1677:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1678:   completion:\n1679:     message: |\n1680:       Deep research complete.\n1681:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1682:       Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n1683: \n1684:       Artifacts:\n1685:         - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1686:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n1687:         - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n1688:         - Memory context saved\n1689: \n1690:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1691:     next_steps:\n1692:       - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n1693:       - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n1694:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1695: \n1696: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1697: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1698: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1699: error_recovery:\n1700:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1701:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1702:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1703:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n1704: \n1705: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1706: # RULES\n1707: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1708: rules:\n1709:   ALWAYS:\n1710:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1711:     - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n1712:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1713:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1714:     - upsert_iteration_memory_after_reducer\n1715:     - refresh_memory_context_before_next_prompt\n1716:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1717:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1718:   NEVER:\n1719:     - skip_convergence_check\n1720:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1721:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1722:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1723:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1724:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1725: \n1726: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1727: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1728: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1729: reference_only_appendix:\n1730:   checkpoint_commit:\n1731:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1732:     commands:\n1733:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n1734:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1735:   wave_orchestration:\n1736:     note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1737:     summary:\n1738:       - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n1739:       - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n1740:       - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"\n\n(End of file - total 1740 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_keyFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'research',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n              totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_keyFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'research',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n              totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,\n              registryFindingCount,\n              iterationFindingCount,\n              identifiableFindingCount,\n              missingStructuredFindingCount,\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          } else {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_complete',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n              totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          }\n          EOF\n\n      step_writeback_spec_findings:\n        action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n        edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n        host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        fail_closed_conflict_check:\n          if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n            detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n            on_manual_edit_conflict:\n              append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              halt: true\n        instructions:\n          - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n          - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n          - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n          - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n          - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_terminal:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop terminal row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        terminal_events: [completed, failed, stopped]\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{config.lineage.sessionId}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? '{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const reason = '{reason}';\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          function terminalEvent(stopReason) {\n            if (stopReason === 'manualStop' || stopReason === 'userPaused') return 'stopped';\n            if (stopReason === 'error') return 'failed';\n            return 'completed';\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const event = terminalEvent(reason);\n          const row = {\n            event,\n            label: 'single',\n            terminal: true,\n            reason,\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event, label: row.label, reason, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, reason },\n                event,\n                status: event,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_terminal: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event completed, failed, or stopped\"\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep research complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n        - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n      - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - upsert_iteration_memory_after_reducer\n    - refresh_memory_context_before_next_prompt\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  wave_orchestration:\n    note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    summary:\n      - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n      - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n      - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"","lineStart":1471,"lineEnd":1740,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486589988,"end":1783486590001}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0acb375b0dc0e304016a4dd87de0d88191a440ef2d71c25fa5"}},"id":"prt_f4015ac220015Kix6WmnsBw4Rt","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486590003,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qzmZPR3c9VrMOq7hXmlKrwNp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":380},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1783486589989,"end":1783486590002}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0acb375b0dc0e304016a4dd87de0e4819185d6ed3643a8d014"}},"id":"prt_f4015ac24001QGgKs5xSC7yWRt","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486590010,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7XedSuwyVAiuaeXyxyv1gCPR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":340},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"research findings registry\"\n7:   - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n8:   - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n9:   - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n10:   - \"research dashboard derivation\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.2\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n17: \n18: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n39: \n40: The workflow reducer:\n41: \n42: - reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n43: - reads `inbox.jsonl` as immutable question input;\n44: - reads the prior registry as canonical question state when present;\n45: - validates required iteration artifacts;\n46: - updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n47: - regenerates the findings registry;\n48: - regenerates the dashboard;\n49: - records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n50: \n51: It must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n56: \n57: The canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n58: \n59: ```json\n60: {\n61:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n62:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n63:   \"keyFindings\": [],\n64:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n65:   \"coverageBySources\": {},\n66:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n67:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n68:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n69:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n70:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n71:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: Question ownership:\n76: \n77: - `inbox.jsonl` is append-only input for external questions.\n78: - The registry is the canonical owner of promoted question text, provenance, and operator decisions.\n79: - The strategy `key-questions` block is a generated projection and is rewritten from registry state on every reduce step.\n80: \n81: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question by promoted question id or inbox id but carries different text, the reducer records a conflict instead of overwriting markdown. Conflict records use `operatorDecision` values of `accepted`, `rejected`, `superseded`, or `needs_decision`; the default unresolved decision is `needs_decision`. The emitted `question_conflict` JSONL event includes both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n82: \n83: The currently documented live registry name is `deep-research-findings-registry.json` in command state paths, with `findings-registry.json` still appearing in older docs and packet examples. New docs should prefer the command state path and mention the older name only when explaining compatibility.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n88: \n89: Blocking validation:\n90: \n91: - config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n92: - every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n93: - every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n94: - JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n95: - reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n96: - convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n97: \n98: Post-dispatch failure codes include:\n99: \n100: | Code | Meaning |\n101: |------|---------|\n102: | `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n103: | `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n104: | `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n105: | `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n106: | `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n107: \n108: Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n113: \n114: Fault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n115: \n116: Safe recovery order:\n117: \n118: 1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n119: 2. Read valid JSONL records.\n120: 3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n121: 4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n122: 5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n123: 6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n124: \n125: Example reconstructed record:\n126: \n127: ```json\n128: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n134: \n135: The config may include:\n136: \n137: ```json\n138: {\n139:   \"fileProtection\": {\n140:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n141:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n142:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n143:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n144:     \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n145:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n146:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n147:   }\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: Protection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n156: \n157: Dashboard values are derived from raw state:\n158: \n159: | Dashboard Field | Source |\n160: |-----------------|--------|\n161: | iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n162: | current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n163: | convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n164: | blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n165: | graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n166: | next focus | strategy |\n167: \n168: `synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n173: \n174: The workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.\n\n(End of file - total 174 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n\n---\n\n## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n\nThe workflow reducer:\n\n- reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n- reads `inbox.jsonl` as immutable question input;\n- reads the prior registry as canonical question state when present;\n- validates required iteration artifacts;\n- updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n- regenerates the findings registry;\n- regenerates the dashboard;\n- records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n\nIt must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n  \"coverageBySources\": {},\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nQuestion ownership:\n\n- `inbox.jsonl` is append-only input for external questions.\n- The registry is the canonical owner of promoted question text, provenance, and operator decisions.\n- The strategy `key-questions` block is a generated projection and is rewritten from registry state on every reduce step.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question by promoted question id or inbox id but carries different text, the reducer records a conflict instead of overwriting markdown. Conflict records use `operatorDecision` values of `accepted`, `rejected`, `superseded`, or `needs_decision`; the default unresolved decision is `needs_decision`. The emitted `question_conflict` JSONL event includes both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\nThe currently documented live registry name is `deep-research-findings-registry.json` in command state paths, with `findings-registry.json` still appearing in older docs and packet examples. New docs should prefer the command state path and mention the older name only when explaining compatibility.\n\n---\n\n## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n\nBlocking validation:\n\n- config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n- every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n- every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n- JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n- reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n- convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n\nPost-dispatch failure codes include:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n| `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n| `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n| `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n| `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n\nThree consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n\nFault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n\nSafe recovery order:\n\n1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n2. Read valid JSONL records.\n3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n\nExample reconstructed record:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n\nThe config may include:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nProtection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n\n---\n\n## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n\nDashboard values are derived from raw state:\n\n| Dashboard Field | Source |\n|-----------------|--------|\n| iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n| current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n| convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n| blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n| graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n| next focus | strategy |\n\n`synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n\n---\n\n## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n\nThe workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":174,"totalLines":174,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1783486589992,"end":1783486590009}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0acb375b0dc0e304016a4dd87de0f081918b2820707ee5594e"}},"id":"prt_f4015ac26001S4zDbtBO6ofsxg","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783486590359,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f4015ad950010TjRz7adVNhiok","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"1aefe6e3f18684fce5e209858ae6abafa93ea75a","messageID":"msg_f40158e0f001p71R7T7T49lPbP","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":64388,"input":16435,"output":298,"reasoning":39,"cache":{"write":0,"read":47616}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783486591772,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f4015b31b001b1rkITrLu6UPFV","messageID":"msg_f4015af3f001iy1fq6t6qB2rdO","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","snapshot":"1aefe6e3f18684fce5e209858ae6abafa93ea75a","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1783486599408,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f4015cd6c001ycr65r6pcNIWHj","messageID":"msg_f4015af3f001iy1fq6t6qB2rdO","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","type":"text","text":"The workflow’s CLI branch has a self-invocation guard, while the user explicitly declared this a detached fan-out lineage. I’m checking the CLI executor contract before deciding whether the provided detached boundary satisfies that guard.","time":{"start":1783486598508,"end":1783486599407},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0eaa1ef16bc3cf42016a4dd88683408191844418f00eeb0b7d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486599712,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_1uWL0uShnAHFQLrKU3oAPpLg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"cli-opencode"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"cli-opencode\">\n# Skill: cli-opencode\n\n<!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, deepseek, openai, minimax, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-m3, token-plan, xiaomi, xiaomi-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan-ams, xiaomi-api, xiaomi-direct, mimo, mimo-v2.5-pro, mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed, ultraspeed, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, glm-coding-plan -->\n\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\n\n> **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\n>\n> This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\n>\n> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n\nOrchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, OpenCode, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\n\n**Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n- **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n- **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n- **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n- **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n- Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n- Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n- Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n- Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n- Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Prerequisite Detection\n\n```bash\n# Verify OpenCode CLI is available\ncommand -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n\n# SELF-INVOCATION GUARD (ADR-001 layered detection)\n# Layer 1: env var lookup — any OPENCODE_* variable\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: OPENCODE_* env detected — already inside OpenCode.\"\n# Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\nps -o command= -p \"$PPID\" | grep -q opencode && echo \"ERROR: opencode parent process detected.\"\n# Layer 3: state lock-file probe\nls ~/.opencode/state/*/lock 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q lock && echo \"ERROR: live OpenCode session lock detected.\"\n```\n\n### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n\n```python\ndef detect_self_invocation():\n    \"\"\"Returns a non-None signal when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode.\"\"\"\n    # Layer 1: env var lookup — OpenCode sets OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR and OPENCODE_* vars\n    for key in os.environ:\n        if key == 'OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR' or key.startswith('OPENCODE_'):\n            return ('env', key)\n    # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n    try:\n        ancestry = subprocess.check_output(['ps', '-o', 'command=', '-p', str(os.getppid())]).decode()\n        if '/opencode' in ancestry or 'opencode ' in ancestry:\n            return ('ancestry', 'opencode')\n    except subprocess.SubprocessError:\n        pass\n    # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n    state_dir = os.path.expanduser('~/.opencode/state')\n    if os.path.isdir(state_dir):\n        for entry in os.listdir(state_dir):\n            if os.path.exists(os.path.join(state_dir, entry, 'lock')):\n                return ('lockfile', entry)\n    return None\n\nif detect_self_invocation():\n    # Single legitimate exception: explicit \"parallel detached\" keywords (use case 2)\n    # spawn a SEPARATE session id and state directory, not a self-dispatch.\n    if not has_parallel_session_keywords(prompt):\n        refuse(\n            \"Self-invocation refused: this agent is already running inside OpenCode. \"\n            \"Use a sibling cli-* skill or a fresh shell session in a different runtime to dispatch a different model. \"\n            \"For a parallel detached session, restate with explicit parallel-session keywords.\"\n        )\n```\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load            | Resources                      |\n| ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------ |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation  | `references/cli_reference.md`, `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Intent-mapped reference docs   |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request| Extended templates and patterns |\n\n### Smart Router\n\nIntent-specific dictionaries (used by the shared helper functions in [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md)):\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans existing `references/` and `assets/` folders with `base.exists()` safeguards.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, `inventory`, and `seen` so raw loads, missing files, duplicate loads, and path escapes are rejected.\n- Pattern 3: Not applicable here - `cli-opencode` has flat resource folders, not keyed `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subdirectories. Routing selects from `RESOURCE_MAP` by intent signal rather than by runtime resource key.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - low-confidence intent scores return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with a disambiguation checklist; missing intent resources still return always-load baseline docs plus a clear notice.\n\n```python\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate to opencode\", \"opencode run\", \"from claude code\", \"from opencode\", \"from copilot\", \"external runtime\", \"full plugin runtime\"]},\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", \"share url\", \"share-url\", \"detached session\"]},\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"spec kit\", \"spec-kit\", \"spec_kit\", \"code graph\", \"memory_search\", \"session_bootstrap\", \"skill advisor\", \"cross-ai handback\"]},\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ai-council\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\"]},\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"cross-repo\", \"different repo\", \"--dir\", \"another repository\", \"remote opencode\"]},\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"template\", \"prompt\", \"how to ask\", \"opencode prompt\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\", \"prompt framework\"]},\n    \"PATTERNS\":           {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"pattern\", \"workflow\", \"orchestrate\", \"session continue\", \"resume session\"]},\n    # WHY: DESIGN is an intent signal only. The durable sk-design loading contract lives in the\n    # always-fires Design Standards Loading rule and the dispatch manifest; RESOURCE_MAP stays\n    # limited to same-skill markdown paths.\n    \"DESIGN\":             {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"sk-design\", \"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"redesign the ui\", \"design foundations\", \"design tokens\", \"motion design\", \"micro-interactions\", \"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"references/integration_patterns.md\"],\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"references/opencode_tools.md\"],\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     [\"references/agent_delegation.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"references/opencode_tools.md\"],\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          [\"assets/prompt_templates.md\", \"references/cli_reference.md\"],\n    \"PATTERNS\":           [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"references/cli_reference.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"assets/prompt_quality_card.md\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/opencode_tools.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Is the user asking about OpenCode CLI specifically?\",\n    \"Does the task need the project's full plugin / skill / MCP runtime?\",\n    \"Is a parallel detached session what they want?\",\n    \"Is a non-Anthropic CLI handing back to OpenCode for a spec-kit workflow?\",\n]\n```\n\n**Call sequence** (using shared helpers from `shared_smart_router.md`):\n\n1. `discover_markdown_resources()` — recursively enumerate current `.md` files under existing `references/` and `assets/` folders at routing time.\n2. `_guard_in_skill()` + `load_if_available()` — sandbox paths to this skill, reject non-markdown loads, skip missing files, and suppress duplicates.\n3. `score_intents(task)` and `select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)` — preserve provider-specific weighted intent scoring and top-2 ambiguity handling.\n4. ALWAYS-load `LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]`, then return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` when max score is 0.\n5. CONDITIONAL-load existing `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` entries via `load_if_available()`, ON_DEMAND-load keyword matches, and return a notice when no intent-specific knowledge base is available beyond always-load resources.\n\nThe `route_opencode_resources(task)` function body lives in [`shared_smart_router.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md) — substitute `<PROVIDER>` = `opencode`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n```bash\n# Verify installation (cli-opencode v1.0.0 is pinned to opencode v1.3.17)\nopencode --version | grep -q '^1\\.' || echo \"Not installed or version drift. See references/cli_reference.md §9.\"\n\n# Self-invocation guard\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: Already inside OpenCode session\"\n\n# Authentication — providers configured via opencode providers (alias auth)\nopencode providers\n```\n\n**Authentication options**: `opencode providers login <provider>` (and `opencode auth login` for subscription plans) for OAuth and API key flows. Configured providers on a typical install: `deepseek` (api, DEFAULT), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan subscription — **DEFAULT MiniMax path**; `opencode auth login`; model `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API, pay-per-token — `opencode providers login minimax`; model `minimax/MiniMax-M3`), `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API, pay-per-token — `opencode providers login xiaomi`; models `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` and the low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe; `opencode auth login`; model `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), `openai` (api, premium alternative for `gpt-5.5`/`gpt-5.5-pro`/`gpt-5.5-fast`).\n\n### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (Smart Fallback)\n\n**MANDATORY before any first dispatch in a session.** The default provider may not be logged in on this machine — silently failing with `provider/model not found` or `401 Unauthorized` mid-dispatch wastes a round-trip. Run this check once per session, cache the result, and re-run it only if a dispatch fails with an auth error.\n\n```bash\n# One-shot pre-flight: list configured providers, capture for routing\nPROVIDERS=$(opencode providers list 2>&1)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"deepseek\"            && DEEPSEEK_OK=1       || DEEPSEEK_OK=0\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"minimax-coding-plan\" && MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1  || MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0   # MiniMax Token Plan (default MiniMax path)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"minimax([^-]|$)\"    && MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1 || MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0  # MiniMax Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the coding-plan provider\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\" && XIAOMI_OK=1       || XIAOMI_OK=0          # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"     && XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1 || XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0   # Xiaomi Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the token-plan-ams provider\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"openai\"              && OPENAI_OK=1         || OPENAI_OK=0\n```\n\n**Decision tree** (apply in order — first match wins):\n\n| State | DEEPSEEK_OK | OPENAI_OK | Action |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| Default available | 1 | * | Proceed with `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` |\n| Default missing, openai ready | 0 | 1 | **ASK user** before substituting to OpenAI — surface options A/B/C/D below; OpenAI is a paid premium fallback. |\n| All missing | 0 | 0 | **ASK user** to configure a provider — surface the login commands, do NOT dispatch. |\n\n**MiniMax routing** (default = Token Plan; Direct API is the pay-per-token alternative — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiniMax requested (default) | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` — **omit `--agent`** (rejected on opencode 1.15.13) |\n| Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login minimax` (needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — never substitute silently |\n\n**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (high reasoning is the standing default — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort) — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13); confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant requested (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive checks/smokes) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro serving tier, same COSTAR prompt contract as the standard model |\n| Direct API not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n\n**User prompt template — default missing, fallback configured:**\n\n```\nThe skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\nA configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n  A) Use `openai/gpt-5.5-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)\n  B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n  C) Use `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (Kimi For Coding plan, configured now — subscription)\n  D) Run `opencode providers login deepseek` first, then retry the original dispatch\n  E) Name a different model — paste the `--model <provider/model>` you want to use\n```\n\n**User prompt template — all providers missing:**\n\n```\nNo supported providers are configured on this machine. Run one:\n  - `opencode providers login deepseek`     (recommended — default for cli-opencode)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path; pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\" → provider minimax-coding-plan; model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode providers login minimax`      (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token; needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; model minimax/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n  - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Kimi For Coding plan — Kimi/Moonshot coding subscription; provider kimi-for-coding; model kimi-for-coding/k2p7)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n  - `opencode providers login openai`       (OpenAI premium alternative — paid)\nWhich would you like to set up? Confirm when login finishes; the skill will retry the original dispatch.\n```\n\n**Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (credential expired or rotated), invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n\n### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n\n**Default model + variant + format + dir**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>`. The repo root pin avoids CWD ambiguity. Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — it gives elevated reasoning at low cost for routine cli-opencode dispatches.\n\nUse `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\"`.\n\n> **The `--agent` flag (read this):** Do NOT pass `--agent` on a top-level `opencode run`. Current opencode treats named agents like `general` as **subagents** and rejects them at the top level, so `--agent general` fails the dispatch outright. When no `--agent` is given, the default agent runs — which is what you want for almost every dispatch. **To run as a specific agent profile, describe the role in the prompt body** (for example, open the prompt with \"Act as a code-review agent: …\"), not via `--agent`. Only pass `--agent <name>` if you have confirmed against `opencode run --help` on the installed version that it accepts that agent at the top level.\n\nHonor explicit user model, port, and handback phrasing verbatim; otherwise use the default invocation above.\n\n### Core Invocation Pattern\n\nCore flags: `--model`, `--agent`, `--variant`, `--format json`, `--dir`, continuation/session/fork flags, `--share` and `--port` for detached sessions, `--file`, `--thinking`, `--pure`, and log flags.\n\n> **Non-interactive invocation stdin**: always append `</dev/null` to any non-interactive `opencode run` invocation. Without it, opencode can inherit parent-terminal stdin and trigger the reactive-EOF exit path when that stream closes. See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6.\n\n> **Registered command dispatch (`--command`)**: slash-command text inside a `run` message is NOT expanded — `opencode run \"/memory:search query\"` delivers the slash text to the model as raw prose, and the command template (router contract, presentation assets, MUST-render envelopes) never enters the session. To execute a registered command non-interactively: `opencode run --command <family>/<name> [flags] \"<args>\"` — the message becomes `$ARGUMENTS`. Registry names are slash-namespaced: `memory/search` for `/memory:search` (a wrong `--command` name fails with the full registry list). Verified on opencode 1.17.4. Consequences: (a) any behavior/adherence probe of a slash command MUST use `--command`, and the raw-text form is only valid as a labeled negative control; (b) inside `` !`…` `` template injections `$ARGUMENTS` expands like `\"$@\"` — one word per argument — so renderer scripts must join argv themselves.\n\n### Model Selection\n\nRun `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45 transient dispatch failures (retry the cell). Empirical prompt framework: COSTAR (benchmark 008). **Vision (image input):** `glm-5.2` is natively multimodal (vision-to-code), but `opencode run --file <image>` does NOT deliver images to this provider — upstream #20802 for custom OpenAI-compatible providers (confirmed 2026-06-28: `--file` → `NO_IMAGE_RECEIVED`). For image input use the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 `image_url` at `https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions`) — a deviation from this skill's dispatch path justified only by the verified #20802 breakage; see `../sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md` §7. OpenAI chat models (`openai/gpt-5.5`, `openai/gpt-5.5-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`) are usable when explicitly requested — reasoning effort via `--variant` up to **`xhigh`** (e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.5 --variant xhigh`). **`openai/gpt-5.5-fast` is the low-latency Fast variant** (OpenAI `priority` service tier), same effort range — e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.5-fast --variant xhigh`. The model cache lists it as `gpt-5.5` + `experimental.modes:['fast']`; `opencode models openai` resolves the `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` slug directly. Confirm live slugs via `opencode models openai`.\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by a primary (`orchestrate`) using the Task tool. To exercise via the opencode CLI, route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>` from the CLI. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** for these agents (e.g. its registry-backed `/deep:review` Priority row) — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop (no iterating, no convergence checks, no continuity tracking); that remains the parent command's job.\n\nGeneric subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n\nSee [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n\n### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n\nOpenCode dispatch provides full project runtime loading, detached sessions, JSON event streams, agent routing, cross-repo/server dispatch, session continuation, and plugin-disable debugging.\n\n### Essential Commands\n\nUse the default invocation for external runtime handback, append `--share --port <N>` only for explicit detached sessions, select `--agent orchestrate` for generic subagent routing, and change `--dir` for cross-repo dispatch.\n\n### Error Handling\n\nInstall missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, and inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Verify OpenCode CLI is installed before first invocation; confirm version baseline against v1.3.17 (drift handling per `references/cli_reference.md` §9).\n2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n3. Pin model + variant + format + dir explicitly — **no `--agent`** (see the Default Invocation note: current opencode rejects a top-level `--agent general`; put any agent-profile request in the prompt body). Default: `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>`. Honor user overrides verbatim (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, `openai/gpt-5.5-pro`).\n4. Pass `--format json` unless the calling AI explicitly wants formatted output — JSON event stream is what external runtimes parse incrementally.\n5. **Append `</dev/null` to every non-interactive `opencode run` invocation** that redirects stdout and/or stderr to files OR runs inside `while read` loops. opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation; without explicit closed stdin, automation hangs forever at 0% CPU after the `+60s service=snapshot prune=7.days cleanup` log line. Position: AFTER the prompt positional argument, BEFORE the `> stdout 2> stderr` redirects. Foreground `| tail` happens to provide closed stdin (pipe stage upstream is empty) and accidentally bypasses the bug, but `> stdout.log 2> stderr.log` does not. The 9-character `</dev/null` redirect provides immediate EOF on stdin, unblocking the dispatch. **DO NOT auto-kill external operator-owned opencode sessions** when sweeping orphans between dispatches; exclude `opencode run` from pkill (per 2026-05-23 operator directive captured in memory `feedback_proactive_orphan_cleanup.md`). See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6 + memory `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md` + CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md §Fix 4.\n6. **Pass the spec folder to the dispatched session** in the prompt: if the calling AI has an active Gate-3 spec folder, include `Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)`. If none, ASK the user before delegating — the dispatched session cannot answer Gate 3 interactively in non-interactive `run` mode.\n7. **Prompt construction & model-craft (cli-* family precedence).** Compose every dispatch prompt via the 3-tier rule canonical in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md`:\n   1. **Fast path (default).** Build from the local `assets/prompt_quality_card.md`, which delegates the framework table + CLEAR check to the canonical card.\n   2. **Model override (mandatory for a profiled model).** If the target model has a profile at `../sk-prompt-models/references/models/<id>.md`, that profile OVERRIDES the cross-model default. The **sk-prompt-models** hub owns per-model prompt-craft (framework + scaffold + gotchas, mirroring `sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json` `recommended_frameworks`); consult it before composing for any small model.\n   3. **Deep path (escalation).** Dispatch `@prompt-improver` via the Task tool (never load full `sk-prompt` inline) when any canonical **Tier 3** trigger applies — the trigger list lives in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md` under \"Tier 3 — Deep path\"; do not re-enumerate it here.\n8. Validate dispatched session output: parse JSON events incrementally (tool calls, partial messages, final summary), run syntax checks if code generated, and cross-reference against project standards via `sk-code` surface detection plus its code-review mode when findings-first review is requested (see ALWAYS rule 12).\n9. Capture stderr (`2>&1`) to catch tool errors and warnings.\n10. Classify the use case (1 / 2 / 3) before dispatching — the smart router refuses dispatches that do not map to one of the three.\n11. **Run the Provider Auth Pre-Flight once per session** (see §3 Provider Auth Pre-Flight). Cache the configured-providers list. If the default `deepseek` is missing, ASK the user — never silently substitute the model. If a later dispatch returns an auth error, invalidate the cache and rerun the pre-flight before retrying.\n12. **Code Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for code review or code generation, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-code`; (2) let `sk-code` emit a surface tag matching the detected stack from markers and target files; (3) load the selected surface resources and run its verification commands; (4) load `sk-code`'s code-review mode only for formal findings-first review output. Fallback: if the surface cannot be determined confidently, ask for the runtime surface and verification command set. NEVER hardcode obsolete sibling code skills in dispatch prompts.\n13. **Design Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for design or UI work, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-design` (the hub); (2) let the hub resolve a `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json` (interface / foundations / motion / audit / md-generator / design-mcp-open-design); (3) load the selected mode packet, set the design register, and run that mode's design verification; (4) if the work feeds Open Design, carry the `design-mcp-open-design` pairing (a nested transport packet of the hub) — the transport never decides taste. Fallback: if the design mode cannot be determined confidently, ask for the surface and design intent. NEVER treat `mcp-figma` or `design-mcp-open-design` as the taste authority, or hardcode obsolete flat design skills in dispatch prompts.\n14. **Pass the design dispatch manifest to the dispatched session** — when dispatching design or UI work, inline a `DESIGN_DISPATCH_MANIFEST v1` block in the prompt (the child cannot resolve skill paths, so the manifest travels in the payload, not by reference): `skDesignLoaded` true, `register` resolved to `Brand` or `Product` (never `unknown`), registry-valid `workflowModes`, `dials`, `loadedFiles`, and `proofDemandBack`. If the manifest cannot be assembled — `sk-design` not loaded, register unresolved, or no registry-valid mode — ASK before launching the child rather than starting a silent design dispatch. The child returns the demanded proof; the parent reconciles it on the return path.\n15. **Destructive-scope-violation prevention (RM-8) for deep-loop dispatches** — If a permissions-matrix config is loaded (via `--permissions-matrix <path>` flag or recipe field), the structured gate applies and the four-layer prose mitigation is bypassed; see `references/permissions-matrix.md`. Without a loaded matrix, any non-interactive `opencode run` with `--dangerously-skip-permissions` against a populated worktree MUST apply the four-layer mitigation as a legacy fallback, deprecated-but-supported during transition: (L1) rendered prompt contains literal `BANNED OPERATIONS` and `ALLOWED WRITE PATHS`; (L2) `--dir` points at a fresh `git worktree`; (L3) main `git status` clean OR committed, recovery-baseline commit hash recorded; (L4) for multi-phase / phase-parent targets, prefer `cli-copilot` + `gpt-5.5 --reasoning-effort high` over `deepseek-v4-pro`. Background: on 2026-05-04 an `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` dispatch under `/deep:review:auto` deleted 44 files across two phase folders because the only safeguard was prose and `--dangerously-skip-permissions` granted unrestricted FS write. Full incident + root cause + checklist: `references/destructive_scope_violations.md`.\n16. **Single-dispatch discipline (operator-gated, session-scoped)** — Default: launch ONE cli-* dispatch at a time across the cli-* family (cli-opencode, cli-claude-code). Wait for the dispatched agent's work to return, verify outputs exist, then SIGKILL the dispatcher process + any orphan children (`pkill -9 -f \"opencode run\"` for this skill, plus `gtimeout` / `positional_scoring_fallback:app` cleanup). Only launch the next dispatch (this skill OR a sibling) after the prior one is dead and RSS has dropped. **Within a deep-flow session** (deep-review / deep-research): the operator authorizes the whole multi-iteration session at start — iterations chain back-to-back with kill-between as the safety mechanism, NOT a per-iteration operator confirmation prompt. **Exception (cross-skill parallel)**: when the operator explicitly authorizes N parallel dispatches, run N concurrently — but still SIGKILL each as its work returns.\n17. **Set `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1` in the dispatched session's env** when sessions may be launched through the per-session worktree wrapper (`.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh`). A dispatched `opencode run` is an orchestrated sub-session, not a new top-level session, so it must SHARE the parent's worktree rather than allocate its own. The wrapper checks `AI_SESSION_CHILD` (plus a `git --git-common-dir` structural backstop) and exec's in place when set. Pattern: `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`. Harmless when the wrapper is not in use. See `.opencode/bin/README.md` → \"Worktree session isolation\".\n\n### ❌ NEVER\n\n1. Invoke this skill from within OpenCode itself for a self-dispatch — refuse with the documented error message; use a sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords.\n2. Pass `--share` without operator confirmation (CHK-033) — share URL exposes session contents.\n3. Trust dispatched session output blindly for security-sensitive code, send sensitive data (API keys, passwords, credentials) in prompts, or hammer the API with rapid sequential calls.\n4. Use `--pure` outside of plugin debugging (disabling plugins removes the entire point of cli-opencode dispatch).\n5. Nest `opencode run` inside a dispatched session's tool calls — use OpenCode's native Task tool for sub-agent dispatch.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. OpenCode CLI is not installed and user has not acknowledged (provide `brew install opencode` or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`).\n2. Operator wants to publish a `--share` URL — get explicit confirmation per CHK-033.\n3. Binary version differs from the v1.3.17 baseline — run `opencode --version` and `opencode run --help`; surface drift and fall back or require approval.\n4. Smart router cannot map the prompt to one of the three use cases — surface the disambiguation checklist from UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n5. Self-invocation guard trips AND the prompt is ambiguous — surface the refusal with three remediation options (sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords).\n\n### Memory Handback Protocol\n\nWhen the calling AI needs to preserve session context from an OpenCode CLI delegation, run the canonical 7-step procedure (extract `MEMORY_HANDBACK` section → build structured JSON → scrub secrets → invoke `generate-context.js` via `--stdin`/`--json`/temp-file → `memory_index_scan`). Full procedure and caveats: [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md).\n\nFor read-only or hook-style recovery, use the daemon-backed CLI front doors instead of spawning OpenCode: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool>`, `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool>`, or `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool>`. Prompt-time paths must probe warm sockets or pass `--warm-only`; exit `75` is retryable daemon/IPC unavailability, not a model failure.\n\nOpenCode-specific Memory Epilogue template: see [assets/prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md) §14.\n\nExample invocation:\n```bash\nprintf '%s' \"$JSON_PAYLOAD\" | node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --stdin [spec-folder]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [cli_reference.md](./references/cli_reference.md) - Full subcommand and flag reference, models, version drift handling\n- [integration_patterns.md](./references/integration_patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard, silent stdin\n- [opencode_tools.md](./references/opencode_tools.md) - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n- [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) - Agent routing matrix, leaf-agent constraints\n- [destructive_scope_violations.md](./references/destructive_scope_violations.md) - RM-8 incident (2026-05-04, 44 files deleted), root cause analysis, four-layer prevention playbook\n\n### Templates and Assets\n\n- [prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md) - 13 numbered copy-paste templates per use case + agent + handback\n- [prompt_quality_card.md](./assets/prompt_quality_card.md) - Executor-specific model overrides (MiniMax, MiMo); delegates shared framework table and CLEAR check to canonical card\n\n### Shared (cli-* family)\n- [shared_smart_router.md](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md) - Helper-function bodies for the smart router.\n- [memory_handback.md](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md) - Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure.\n\n### External\n- [OpenCode GitHub](https://github.com/sst/opencode) - Official repository\n- [OpenCode Install](https://opencode.ai/install) - Standalone installer entry point\n- [OpenCode Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs) - Official docs\n\n### Reference Loading Notes\n\n- Load only references needed for current intent.\n- Smart Routing (Section 2) is the single routing authority.\n- `cli_reference.md` and `prompt_quality_card.md` are ALWAYS loaded as baseline.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Task Completion\n\n- OpenCode CLI invoked with the correct subcommand, flags, model, agent, variant, format, and dir.\n- Self-invocation guard checked before dispatch — refused when appropriate.\n- Use case (1 / 2 / 3) classified explicitly before invocation.\n- JSON event stream captured, parsed incrementally, validated, integrated.\n- No security vulnerabilities introduced from generated code.\n- `--share` URLs opt-in with operator confirmation per CHK-033.\n- Background dispatches in `while read` loops include `</dev/null` redirect.\n- Memory Handback extracted and saved through `generate-context.js` when applicable.\n\n### Skill Quality\n\n- All 8 sections present with proper anchor comments.\n- Smart routing covers all intent signals with UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n- Reference files provide deep-dive content without duplication.\n- Self-invocation guard pseudocode reproduced in Section 2 mirrors ADR-001.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via the Skill Advisor Hook (or `skill_advisor.py` fallback)\n- **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n- **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP (`generate-context.js`)\n- **Validation**: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh` for spec-folder workflows\n\n**Tool roles**: Bash dispatches the CLI; Read/Glob/Grep validate output and probe `~/.opencode/state/` for session locks.\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/cli_reference.md`, `references/integration_patterns.md`, `assets/prompt_quality_card.md`, `assets/prompt_templates.md`, `references/agent_delegation.md`, `references/opencode_tools.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\nRelated skills: `cli-claude-code` and `cli-opencode` for sibling cross-AI dispatch; `system-spec-kit` for handback; `sk-code` plus the selected overlay for generated code; `deep-loop-workflows` for loop execution (its `research` and `review` modes); and `mcp-code-mode` for MCP-backed tools.\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-packet-local.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_quality_card.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-readonly.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.schema.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-repo-wide.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/scripts/lib/dispatch-rule-checks.test.mjs</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/scripts/lib/dispatch-rule-checks.mjs</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/scripts/hooks/dispatch-preflight-lint.mjs</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/09--cross-repo-cross-server/cross-repo-dispatch.md</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"cli-opencode","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: cli-opencode","time":{"start":1783486599701,"end":1783486599710}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0eaa1ef16bc3cf42016a4dd8876a2c8191a7e91e5ce53e885d"}},"id":"prt_f4015d0f0001ILFGf8Cfo5wNvj","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4015af3f001iy1fq6t6qB2rdO"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783486600053,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f4015d3740015MOE4taOH87R0J","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"1aefe6e3f18684fce5e209858ae6abafa93ea75a","messageID":"msg_f4015af3f001iy1fq6t6qB2rdO","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":84497,"input":20609,"output":71,"reasoning":329,"cache":{"write":0,"read":63488}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783486601232,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f4015d80c001eq2rDKE2viEts6","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","snapshot":"1aefe6e3f18684fce5e209858ae6abafa93ea75a","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1783486620858,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"id":"prt_f40160cb2001c3DJieOufEltRe","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","type":"text","text":"The CLI contract allows this exact “parallel detached” case. I’m checking the fan-out runner prompt contract to match what this lineage is expected to do without widening writes outside the lineage directory.","time":{"start":1783486614706,"end":1783486620857},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0aae0e71b03b58cf016a4dd896b58c8191a26641e9dd95d580","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486620908,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kLj8exHAjEz6s88ADgtH9JAe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md","offset":1,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-research\n3: description: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: allow\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: allow\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\n17:   chrome_devtools: deny\n18:   task: deny\n19:   list: allow\n20:   patch: deny\n21:   external_directory: allow\n22: ---\n23: \n24: # The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\n25: \n26: Executes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\n27: \n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n29: \n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n31: \n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n33: \n34: **Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n35: \n36: > **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.\n37: \n38: **HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.\n39: - **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n40: - **State-first**: Read config, state JSONL, and strategy before selecting focus or executing research.\n41: - **Packet scope lock**: Write only within the resolved local-owner research packet and only to allowed iteration outputs.\n42: - **Evidence-bound output**: Never claim completion until the iteration file exists, the JSONL append is verified, and every finding has a cited source or inference marker.\n43: - **No speculative recovery**: Do not infer missing state, create replacement control files, or repair reducer-owned files from inside this agent.\n44: - **Read-budget freshness**: Reuse captured evidence and exact anchors before broad rereads. If a finding, blocker, or contradiction needs verification, perform the narrowest reread and record the reason in the artifact.\n45: - **Status honesty**: Do not convert partial success, unresolved contradiction, or stale evidence into completion language. State the exact remaining uncertainty and the next verification step.\n46: \n47: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n48: \n49: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n50: \n51: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n52: \n53: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n54: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n55: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n56: \n57: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND SCOPE LOCK (HARD BLOCK)\n62: \n63: This agent is LEAF-only.\n64: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n65: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n66: - Keep research actions self-contained in this single execution.\n67: - If delegation is needed, document it in findings and recommend it for a future iteration.\n68: \n69: Before any write, enforce the packet scope lock:\n70: - Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.\n71: - Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n72: - Reducer-owned files (`research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json`, `research/deep-research-dashboard.md`) are read-only for this agent.\n73: - If any intended write path escapes the resolved packet root, targets a reducer-owned file, or would overwrite an existing iteration file, STOP and return `Status: error` without writing outside the boundary.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n78: \n79: ### Single Iteration Protocol\n80: \n81: Every iteration follows this sequence:\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: 1. READ STATE ──────> Read config + JSONL + strategy.md\n85: 2. VERIFY BOUNDARY ─> Confirm packet root and allowed write targets\n86: 3. DETERMINE FOCUS ─> Pick focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n87: 4. CLASSIFY EDGES ──> Handle ambiguity, contradictions, missing deps, partial success\n88: 5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n89: 6. WRITE FINDINGS ──> Create research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n90: 7. APPEND STATE ────> Add exactly one iteration record to JSONL\n91: 8. UPDATE RESEARCH ─> Progressively update research/research.md when enabled\n92: 9. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──> Check files, append, citations, and scope before reporting\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Step 1: Read State\n96: \n97: Read the paths provided in dispatch context:\n98: - `research/deep-research-config.json` -- lifecycle mode, budgets, packet boundaries\n99: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` -- iteration history\n100: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md` -- focus, key questions, exhausted approaches\n101: - `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json` (if exists) -- open/resolved questions and key findings\n102: - `research/research-ideas.md` (if exists) -- deferred tangents\n103: \n104: Extract:\n105: - Current iteration number (count JSONL iteration records + 1)\n106: - Remaining key questions\n107: - Exhausted approaches (DO NOT retry these)\n108: - Recommended next focus\n109: - Lifecycle branch from `config.lineage.lineageMode` (`new`, `resume`, or `restart`; `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred -- see `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`)\n110: \n111: **HARD BLOCK -- Missing or unreadable state**:\n112: - If `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, or `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing, unreadable, or structurally corrupt, do not infer a focus and do not execute research actions.\n113: - Do not create replacement config, state, strategy, dashboard, or registry files.\n114: - Return an iteration completion report with `Status: error`, naming the missing or corrupt state file(s), and stop.\n115: \n116: ### Step 2: Verify Boundary\n117: \n118: Before selecting a focus or writing anything:\n119: 1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n120: 2. Precompute intended write paths for this run:\n121:    - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n122:    - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`\n123:    - `research/research.md` only if progressive synthesis is enabled\n124:    - `idea_observed` JSONL rows only if explicit idea capture is allowed\n125:    - `research/research-ideas.md` only if operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed\n126: 3. Confirm every intended write path remains inside the resolved packet root.\n127: 4. Confirm `iteration-NNN.md` does not already exist.\n128: 5. Confirm no reducer-owned file is scheduled for direct edit.\n129: \n130: If any check fails, STOP with `Status: error`. Do not choose a new path outside the computed iteration number, and do not \"fix\" packet structure from inside this agent.\n131: \n132: ### Step 3: Determine Focus\n133: \n134: Before choosing a focus, read strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\":\n135: - `BLOCKED` categories must not be retried or varied.\n136: - `PRODUCTIVE` categories should be preferred for related questions.\n137: - If the selected focus falls inside a BLOCKED category, choose another.\n138: \n139: Use strategy.md \"Next Focus\". If it is empty or vague, pick the first unchecked \"Key Questions (remaining)\" item; if none remain, investigate the lowest-coverage area.\n140: \n141: If multiple focus candidates are equally plausible:\n142: - Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n143: - If two candidates remain tied after that order, choose the narrower one that can be answered with available evidence in this iteration.\n144: - Record deferred focus candidates in the iteration file's `Ruled Out` or `Recommended Next Focus` section.\n145: \n146: For RECOVERY iterations, use a fundamentally different approach than prior iterations, widen or re-angle the search, and check `research/research-ideas.md` for viable escape paths.\n147: \n148: If useful tangents appear outside the current focus, append `idea_observed` JSONL events only when explicitly allowed and packet-local; otherwise record them in the iteration file's `Recommended Next Focus`. Never emit `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; the reducer owns promotion, ranking, and rejection filtering.\n149: \n150: ### Step 4: Classify Edge Cases\n151: \n152: Before research actions, classify any known edge condition and carry that classification into findings:\n153: \n154: | Condition | Trigger | Required Handling |\n155: |-----------|---------|-------------------|\n156: | Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n157: | Contradictory evidence | Two sources make incompatible claims about the same fact | Preserve both claims with citations, state which one is better supported if evidence allows, and avoid marking the question answered unless resolved |\n158: | Missing dependency | Optional file, tool, source, mirror report, or external URL needed for the ideal path is unavailable | Continue with an alternative in-scope source when possible; if the missing item is required state, report `error`; if evidence is partial, report `timeout` or `stuck` honestly |\n159: | Partial success | Some research actions succeed but others fail before the iteration completes | Write successful findings, document failed actions and recovery attempts, and set status based on the strongest truthful outcome |\n160: \n161: Status selection for edge cases:\n162: - Use `complete` when enough cited evidence answers at least one in-scope question despite minor missing sources.\n163: - Use `insight` when contradiction resolution or synthesis materially improves understanding with low new external evidence.\n164: - Use `timeout` when tool/source failures or budget limits prevent adequate coverage but some evidence was gathered.\n165: - Use `stuck` when ambiguity or missing evidence leaves no productive in-scope path after alternatives are tried.\n166: - Use `error` only for unrecoverable state corruption, missing required control files, or write failures that prevent valid artifacts.\n167: \n168: ### Step 5: Execute Research\n169: \n170: Perform 3-5 focused research actions.\n171: \n172: | Tool | When to Use | Example |\n173: |------|-------------|---------|\n174: | WebFetch | Official docs, API references, known URLs | Fetch MDN docs for an API |\n175: | Grep | Code patterns | Search for implementation examples |\n176: | Glob | File discovery | Find config files or tests |\n177: | Read | Specific file contents | Read implementation details |\n178: | memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n179: | Bash | Bounded data gathering | `wc -l`, `jq` for JSON parsing |\n180: \n181: **Budget**: Target 8-11 total tool calls, hard max 12. Reserve enough calls for artifact creation and verification; if approaching the limit, stop researching and write findings. Do not skip output verification to spend a final call on more research.\n182: \n183: **Citation rule**: Every finding must cite a source:\n184: - `[SOURCE: https://url]` for web sources\n185: - `[SOURCE: path/to/file:line]` for codebase sources\n186: - `[SOURCE: memory:spec-folder]` for memory hits\n187: - `[INFERENCE: based on X and Y]` for derived conclusions\n188: \n189: **Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n190: \n191: For source failures, apply Tier 1-2 recovery:\n192: - **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n193: - **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, recommend the focus for \"Exhausted Approaches\" in the iteration file; do not edit strategy directly.\n194: - **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, write the failure in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n195: \n196: ### Step 6: Write Findings\n197: \n198: Create `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`:\n199: \n200: ```markdown\n201: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n202: \n203: ## Focus\n204: [What this iteration investigated and why. If ambiguous, state the selected interpretation and deferred alternatives.]\n205: \n206: ## Findings\n207: 1. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n208: 2. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n209: 3. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n210: \n211: ## Ruled Out\n212: [Approaches tried this iteration that did not yield results, with why they failed.]\n213: \n214: ## Dead Ends\n215: [Paths definitively eliminated and candidates for reducer promotion to strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\".]\n216: \n217: ## Edge Cases\n218: - Ambiguous input: [none or selected interpretation + deferred alternatives]\n219: - Contradictory evidence: [none or source-backed conflict + resolution status]\n220: - Missing dependencies: [none or missing item + fallback used]\n221: - Partial success: [none or successful/failed actions + chosen status rationale]\n222: \n223: ## Sources Consulted\n224: - [URL or file:line reference]\n225: - [URL or file:line reference]\n226: \n227: ## Assessment\n228: - New information ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n229: - Questions addressed: [list]\n230: - Questions answered: [list]\n231: \n232: ## Reflection\n233: - What worked and why: [approach + causal explanation]\n234: - What did not work and why: [failure + root cause]\n235: - What I would do differently: [specific next adjustment]\n236: \n237: ## Recommended Next Focus\n238: [What to investigate next, based on gaps discovered]\n239: ```\n240: \n241: Do not write a placeholder iteration file. If findings are sparse because a tool failed, write the failure and recovery attempts with citations to tool outputs, consulted source paths, or prior packet evidence.\n242: \n243: ### Step 7: Respect Reducer-Owned State\n244: \n245: Do not use `research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json`, or `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` as primary write targets. Instead:\n246: 1. Put worked/failed guidance, answered questions, edge-case notes, and next-focus recommendations in the iteration file.\n247: 2. Append the structured JSONL record.\n248: 3. Let the workflow reducer refresh strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard.\n249: \n250: ### Step 8: Append State\n251: \n252: Append exactly ONE iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`:\n253: \n254: ```json\n255: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":N,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"[focus area]\",\"findingsCount\":N,\"newInfoRatio\":0.XX,\"noveltyJustification\":\"1-sentence explanation of newInfoRatio\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"q1\",\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q1\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"approach1\",\"approach2\"],\"focusTrack\":\"optional-track-label\",\"edgeCase\":\"none\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"WebFetch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"https://example.com/doc\",\"src/file.ts:42\"],\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"durationMs\":NNNNN}\n256: ```\n257: \n258: **Status values**: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n259: - `complete`: Normal evidence gathering with new findings\n260: - `timeout`: Time/tool budget exceeded before finishing\n261: - `error`: Unrecoverable iteration failure\n262: - `stuck`: No productive avenues remain for current focus\n263: - `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but meaningful synthesis or reframing\n264: - `thought`: Explicitly analytical iteration using prior packet evidence only\n265: \n266: Required fields:\n267: - `noveltyJustification`: one sentence explaining the ratio (for example, \"2 of 4 findings were new, 1 partially new\")\n268: - `ruledOut`: attempted but failed approaches, or `[]`\n269: - `toolsUsed`: tools actually used during the iteration\n270: - `sourcesQueried`: source URLs, file paths, memory references, or command outputs consulted\n271: \n272: Optional fields:\n273: - `focusTrack`: multi-track research label such as `architecture`, `performance`, or `security`\n274: - `edgeCase`: `none`, `ambiguous-input`, `contradictory-evidence`, `missing-dependency`, or `partial-success`\n275: \n276: **Append discipline**:\n277: - Append exactly one JSONL record for the iteration.\n278: - Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n279: - Never append `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; reducer and operator workflows own those events.\n280: - Never rewrite, truncate, sort, or reformat existing JSONL lines.\n281: - If append verification shows zero iteration records appended or more than one new iteration record, return `Status: error` and name the mismatch.\n282: \n283: **newInfoRatio calculation**:\n284: - Fully new findings count as 1.0.\n285: - Partially new findings count as 0.5.\n286: - `newInfoRatio = (fully_new + 0.5 * partially_new) / total_findings`.\n287: - If there are no findings, set 0.0.\n288: - Add a +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped at 1.0, when synthesis reduces open questions, resolves contradictions, or provides a cleaner model without new external evidence.\n289: \n290: ### Step 9: Update Research (Progressive)\n291: \n292: Read `research/deep-research-config.json` before touching `research/research.md`.\n293: - If `progressiveSynthesis == true`, add new findings to `research/research.md`; create it only if missing and only inside the resolved packet root.\n294: - If `progressiveSynthesis == false`, do not create or update `research/research.md`; synthesis owns it later.\n295: \n296: ### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n297: \n298: Before returning, verify:\n299: - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` exists at the computed packet-local path.\n300: - The iteration file contains Focus, Findings, Sources Consulted, Assessment, Reflection, and Recommended Next Focus sections.\n301: - Every non-empty Finding has a `[SOURCE: ...]` or `[INFERENCE: ...]` marker.\n302: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` has exactly one new iteration record for this iteration.\n303: - The JSONL line includes `type`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `findingsCount`, `newInfoRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `toolsUsed`, `sourcesQueried`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n304: - No reducer-owned file was edited directly.\n305: - No write escaped the resolved packet root.\n306: - No sub-agent was dispatched.\n307: \n308: If any item fails, fix the in-scope output if safe. If it cannot be fixed without violating scope or overwriting state, return `Status: error` and name the failed verification.\n309: \n310: ### Dashboard Awareness\n311: \n312: The orchestrator generates the dashboard and findings registry after each iteration. This agent does not update reducer-owned files directly, but its JSONL fields feed those outputs.\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n317: \n318: ### Tools\n319: \n320: | Tool | Purpose | Budget |\n321: |------|---------|--------|\n322: | Read | State files, source code | 2-3 calls |\n323: | Write | Iteration file, state append | 2-3 calls |\n324: | Edit | `research/research.md` update when progressiveSynthesis is true | 0-1 calls |\n325: | WebFetch | External documentation | 1-2 calls |\n326: | Grep | Code pattern search | 1-2 calls |\n327: | Glob | File discovery | 0-1 calls |\n328: | Bash | Bounded data gathering (`jq`, `wc`, file checks) | 0-1 calls |\n329: \n330: ### MCP Tools\n331: \n332: | Tool | Purpose |\n333: |------|---------|\n334: | `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n335: | `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n336: \n337: **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources), or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n338: \n339: ## 3. ITERATION PROTOCOL\n340: \n341: ### Focus Selection\n342: \n343: ```text\n344: Strategy \"Next Focus\" available?\n345:   Yes --> Use it after exhausted-approach and scope checks\n346:   No --> Pick first unchecked \"Key Question\"\n347:     No questions? --> Investigate lowest-coverage area\n348:       Multiple equal options? --> Choose narrowest evidence-backed option and document ambiguity\n349:         No coverage data? --> Report stuck (newInfoRatio = 0.0)\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ### Recovery Mode\n353: \n354: If dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY MODE\":\n355: 1. Read \"Exhausted Approaches\" in strategy.md.\n356: 2. Choose a DIFFERENT approach:\n357:    - Prior WebFetch --> try codebase search.\n358:    - Prior broad search --> narrow to a specific aspect.\n359:    - Prior domain-specific pass --> try cross-domain analysis.\n360: 3. Document the recovery attempt in findings.\n361: \n362: ### Error-Aware Execution\n363: \n364: Apply Tier 1-2 error handling:\n365: - **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n366: - **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, add the focus to the iteration file's Dead Ends or Recommended Next Focus section for reducer promotion to \"Exhausted Approaches\"; do not edit strategy directly.\n367: - **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, report the error in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n368: \n369: ### Tool Call Budget\n370: \n371: | Iteration Phase | Target Calls | Max Calls |\n372: |-----------------|--------------|-----------|\n373: | Read state | 2 | 3 |\n374: | Boundary and focus checks | 1 | 2 |\n375: | Research actions | 3-5 | 6 |\n376: | Write outputs | 2-3 | 3 |\n377: | Verify outputs | 1 | 1 |\n378: | **Total** | **8-11** | **12** |\n379: \n380: If approaching 12 tool calls, stop research and write/verify the findings already gathered.\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT\n385: \n386: ### File Paths\n387: \n388: All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `research/`; child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that target's `research/` folder.\n389: \n390: | File | Path | Operation |\n391: |------|------|-----------|\n392: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | Read only |\n393: | State log | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Read + append exactly one line |\n394: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Read only for focus selection |\n395: | Findings registry | `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n396: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Read only if needed |\n397: | Iteration findings | `research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file only |\n398: | Research output | `research/research.md` | Read + edit only when `progressiveSynthesis` is true |\n399: | Idea observations | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Append `idea_observed` events only when explicit idea capture is allowed |\n400: | Ideas file | `research/research-ideas.md` | Append only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed |\n401: \n402: ### Iteration Number Derivation\n403: \n404: ```text\n405: Count lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\n406: Current iteration = count + 1\n407: Pad to 3 digits for filename: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n408: Verify iteration-NNN.md does not already exist before writing\n409: ```\n410: \n411: ### Write Safety\n412: \n413: - JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; optional idea capture may add `idea_observed` events, but never `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`.\n414: - Strategy, registry, dashboard: reducer-owned; do not edit directly.\n415: - Iteration file: create new; if the computed file exists, stop with status `error`.\n416: - Research.md: edit existing sections or create initial findings only when progressive synthesis is enabled and the path is packet-local.\n417: - Idea observations: append `idea_observed` only when dispatch explicitly allows it; otherwise record ideas in the iteration file.\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n\n(Showing lines 1-420 of 584. Use offset=421 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  code_graph_status: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - mk_code_index\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n\n**Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Allowed Tools\n\n| Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n| `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n| `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n| `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n| `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | Structure | Semantic and exact discovery | Find implementation concepts, then verify with exact matches and reads |\n| `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n| `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n| `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n| `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n| `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n| `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n| `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n| `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources). Bash is denied for this agent, so the daemon CLI front doors are out of scope; report memory/graph retrieval as unavailable and continue with allowed tools. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Denied Capability Guard\n\nThe frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n\n- Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n- Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n- Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n\n### Query Routing Matrix\n\n| Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n| Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n| Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n| File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n| Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n| Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n| Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n| Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n\n### Tool Selection Flow\n\n```text\nWhat evidence is needed?\n    |\n    +-- Current packet continuity?\n    |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n    |\n    +-- Known exact path?\n    |     -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n    |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n    |     -> Grep -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n    |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n    |\n    +-- Structural relationship?\n    |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n          -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n\nThis agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n| **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n| **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n| **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n| **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n| **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n| **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n\n**Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n**Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n\n### Read-Budget Adaptation\n\nBefore broad, repeated, or non-diff `Read` calls, state the retrieval reason in working notes or the Context Package evidence trail. Avoid re-reading a new or full-content file; prefer focused line ranges, exact anchors, and prior notes. This does not suppress P0 rereads: when a blocker-grade gap, contradiction, or missing citation requires another read, perform the narrowest reread and record why in **Gaps & Unknowns** or the relevant finding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n\n### The 3-Layer Approach\n\nEvery exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n\n### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n\n**Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n**Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n\n**Process**:\n- Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n- Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n- Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n- Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n- Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n**Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n\n**Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n- **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n- **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n- **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n- **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n- **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n\n**Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n\n### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n\n**Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n- Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n- Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n- Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n\n**Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n\n### Hard Rule\n\nNested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n\n### Enforcement\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n- NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n- If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n- If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n\n### Escalation Contract\n\nWhen blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n\n- Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n- State unresolved gaps clearly.\n- State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n- Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### The Context Package\n\nEvery exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n\n```markdown\n## Context Package: [Topic]\n\n### Memory Context\n[Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n\n### Codebase Findings\n[File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n- `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n- `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n- Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n\n### Pattern Analysis\n[Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n- Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n- Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n- Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n\n### Nested Dispatch Status\n[Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n- Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n- Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n- Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n\n### Gaps & Unknowns\n[What could not be found, verified, or accessed]\n- Gap: [What was looked for but not found]\n- Unknown: [What could not be determined from available context]\n- Risk: [Potential issue flagged during exploration]\n\n### Recommendation\n[proceed | research-deeper | ask-user]\n- **Verdict**: [proceed / research-deeper / ask-user]\n- **Rationale**: [Why this recommendation follows from cited evidence]\n- **Suggested next**: [Specific orchestrator action; no @context write path or sub-agent dispatch]\n```\n\n### Output Rules\n\nAn optional `AGENT_IO_DISPATCH v1` header may provide `task_definition`, `context_snapshot`, and `read_directives`. Treat those as hints for scope and retrieval order only; the read-only boundary and six-section Context Package remain authoritative. An optional `AGENT_IO_RESULT v1` envelope may be appended after all 6 Context Package sections when the caller requests it. Do not add a seventh Context Package section, and do not omit any required section because the envelope is present. Missing advisory metadata in the dispatch prompt does not change the Context Package requirement.\n\n| Rule | Description | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Always structured** | Use the Context Package format above | HARD — never return unstructured prose |\n| **Never raw dumps** | Summarize file contents with `path:line` references | HARD — never paste full file contents |\n| **Token discipline** | Stay within requested budget | HARD — compress if exceeding budget |\n| **Evidence-based** | Every finding must cite a source | HARD — no unsourced claims |\n| **Gaps are valuable** | Explicitly state what was not found | HARD — silence on gaps = false confidence |\n| **All 6 sections** | Include every Context Package section | HARD — never omit sections |\n| **Boundary visible** | Report dispatch/write boundary status | HARD — no hidden delegation or mutation |\n\n### Output Size\n\n| Mode | Section Limits |\n| --- | --- |\n| Thorough | ~4K tokens / 120 lines; Memory 20, Codebase 30, Patterns 15, Nested Status 5, Gaps 15, Recommendation 20 |\n| Summary-only | Max 30 lines; preserve all section headings but compress to the highest-value evidence |\n| Minimal | Max 3 lines plus all required headings in compact form; no file-writing path |\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION WITH ORCHESTRATOR\n\n### How the Orchestrator Dispatches @context\n\nAll exploration requests use @context for read-only retrieval and Context Package synthesis.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Trigger | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Rule 1: Exploration-First | \"Build X\" without existing plan | Gather evidence before implementation |\n| Rule 2: Spec Folder | New or active spec folder needs grounding | Discover related patterns and packet state |\n| Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n| Review/Debug Prep | Need evidence before specialist action | Collect file, memory, and graph context without changing files |\n\n### Example Dispatch Prompt\n\n```text\nExplore everything related to the authentication system: codebase patterns,\nmemory context from prior work, spec folder status, and architecture decisions.\nFocus: both. Stay read-only and return a Context Package.\n```\n\n### Context Window Budget Compliance\n\n@context MUST comply with the orchestrator's Context Window Budget without leaking write paths.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Expected Return Size | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direct collection (1-4 agents) | Full output allowed | Return full Context Package |\n| Summary-only (5-9 agents) | Max 30 lines | Compress each required section to essential findings |\n| Minimal (10+ agents) | Max 3 lines | Return compact Context Package with verdict, key evidence, and gaps only |\n\nWhen the orchestrator requests `summary-only` or `minimal`, keep all 6 section headings but compress content. Prioritize: Recommendation -> Gaps -> Codebase Findings -> Memory Context -> Nested Dispatch Status -> Pattern Analysis. Do not suggest writing a separate artifact from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 8. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- Context Package includes all 6 required sections.\n- Every major finding includes evidence (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- Gaps and unknowns are explicitly stated.\n- Output remains within the requested budget.\n- Recommendation is actionable and scoped to the request.\n- Nested Dispatch Status says no sub-agents were dispatched.\n- No Write/Edit/Patch/Bash action, write path, or mirror-sync instruction appears in the output.\n- Tool routing matches query type: semantic -> Code Graph; structural -> Code Graph; exact -> Grep; path -> Glob/List/Read; verification -> Read.\n\n### Anti-Hallucination Rules\n\n| Rule | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- |\n| NEVER claim patterns/findings without a cited source | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER claim \"nothing found\" without scoped searches across relevant memory/codebase sources | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER omit critical risks/unknowns to make output look complete | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER cite unverified Code Graph or graph hits as facts without Read/Grep confirmation | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER imply a denied tool was used | HARD BLOCK |\n\n---\n\n## 9. RULES & CONSTRAINTS\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- Cite sources for every finding (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- State what was not found or could not be verified.\n- Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n- Use the correct retrieval route for the evidence need.\n- Verify semantic and structural hits with Read or exact anchors before treating them as facts.\n- Include all 6 Context Package sections in output.\n- Respect the 10-20 tool call budget in thorough mode.\n- Keep @context read-only and LEAF-only.\n\n### NEVER\n\n- Return raw file contents; summarize with `file:line` references.\n- Exceed the requested output size.\n- Search beyond the requested scope.\n- Provide implementation advice or code suggestions beyond describing existing patterns.\n- Dispatch any sub-agents; nested dispatch is illegal.\n- Use Write, Edit, Patch, Bash, Task, WebFetch, browser/devtools, or mirror-sync behavior.\n- Recommend a path for @context to write later.\n- Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n- Treat memory search as newer truth than active packet docs.\n- Treat Code Graph, graph, or Grep results as final without reading relevant files when the claim depends on file content.\n- Claim \"nothing found\" without actually searching the scoped sources.\n- Omit sections from the Context Package.\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- Memory system is unavailable; report the issue and continue with codebase-only retrieval.\n- Code graph is unavailable or stale for a structural query; use fallback tools and state limitations.\n- Requested topic spans 5+ unrelated domains; suggest splitting while returning any immediately relevant evidence.\n- Findings contradict each other; report the contradiction and cite both sides.\n- The caller requests mutation, promotion, mirror sync, or nested delegation; refuse that portion and continue read-only retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Correct Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Raw Dump** | Summarize with `file:line` references; never return full file contents |\n| **Scope Creep** | Report only what was requested; note critical tangential findings in Gaps |\n| **Over-Reading** | Respect the tool call budget and narrow searches by scope |\n| **Implementation Advice** | Report existing patterns rather than prescribing new code |\n| **Verbose Returns** | Stay within the requested output budget |\n| **False Confidence** | Include Gaps & Unknowns for what was not found or verified |\n| **Kitchen Sink** | Filter by relevance and cite only findings that answer the query |\n| **Illegal Nesting** | Never delegate from @context; perform direct retrieval and report gaps |\n| **Missing Sections** | Include all 6 Context Package sections in every output |\n| **Delegation Request Drift** | Ignore nested-delegation requests and keep retrieval local |\n| **Write Path Leakage** | Do not include @context write paths, artifact paths, or persistence instructions |\n| **Capability Drift** | Do not recommend Bash/install/fix commands from a bash-denied agent |\n| **Semantic Overreach** | Use Code Graph for discovery, not as uncited proof |\n\n---\n\n\nUse Code Graph when the query is semantic and exact tokens are unknown. Use exact tools when the query gives exact evidence handles.\n\n1. **Semantic discovery** (\"find code that...\", \"how is X implemented\", \"similar pattern\", \"where is the logic for...\") -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` first.\n2. **Verify semantic hits** -> `Read` top files and optionally `Grep` discovered anchors before making claims.\n3. **Structural questions** (\"what calls...\", \"what imports...\", \"impact of...\", \"dependency path\") -> `code_graph_status` then `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context` when healthy.\n4. **Exact text/symbol/literal** -> `Grep` first, then `Read`.\n5. **Known file path** -> `Read` directly.\n6. **File name or directory shape** -> `Glob` or `List`, then `Read`.\n7. **Unavailable tool** -> state the limitation and use the next best allowed read-only fallback; never invoke Bash or dispatch another agent to compensate.\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            THE CONTEXT AGENT: READ-ONLY RETRIEVAL SPECIALIST            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n│  ├─► Evidence-based retrieval across memory, graph, and codebase layers │\n│  ├─► Structured Context Package synthesis with explicit gaps            │\n│  └─► Tool routing by query type and verification need                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  RETRIEVAL LAYERS                                                       │\n│  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n│  ├─► Layer 2: Code Graph, Glob, Grep, List, Read             │\n│  └─► Layer 3: deep memory search and spec cross-reference               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Receive request and lock scope                                  │\n│  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n│  ├─► 3. Route search through the correct read-only tools                │\n│  ├─► 4. Verify findings with cited evidence                              │\n│  └─► 5. Return Context Package with gaps and recommendation             │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► Read-only: never write, edit, patch, bash, sync, or persist files   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal                    │\n│  └─► Structured output only, with explicit evidence and unknowns        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny","truncated":true,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md","text":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\n---\n\n# The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\n\nExecutes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n**Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n\n**Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n\n> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.\n\n**HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.\n- **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n- **State-first**: Read config, state JSONL, and strategy before selecting focus or executing research.\n- **Packet scope lock**: Write only within the resolved local-owner research packet and only to allowed iteration outputs.\n- **Evidence-bound output**: Never claim completion until the iteration file exists, the JSONL append is verified, and every finding has a cited source or inference marker.\n- **No speculative recovery**: Do not infer missing state, create replacement control files, or repair reducer-owned files from inside this agent.\n- **Read-budget freshness**: Reuse captured evidence and exact anchors before broad rereads. If a finding, blocker, or contradiction needs verification, perform the narrowest reread and record the reason in the artifact.\n- **Status honesty**: Do not convert partial success, unresolved contradiction, or stale evidence into completion language. State the exact remaining uncertainty and the next verification step.\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND SCOPE LOCK (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n- NEVER use the Task tool.\n- Keep research actions self-contained in this single execution.\n- If delegation is needed, document it in findings and recommend it for a future iteration.\n\nBefore any write, enforce the packet scope lock:\n- Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.\n- Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n- Reducer-owned files (`research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json`, `research/deep-research-dashboard.md`) are read-only for this agent.\n- If any intended write path escapes the resolved packet root, targets a reducer-owned file, or would overwrite an existing iteration file, STOP and return `Status: error` without writing outside the boundary.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n### Single Iteration Protocol\n\nEvery iteration follows this sequence:\n\n```text\n1. READ STATE ──────> Read config + JSONL + strategy.md\n2. VERIFY BOUNDARY ─> Confirm packet root and allowed write targets\n3. DETERMINE FOCUS ─> Pick focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n4. CLASSIFY EDGES ──> Handle ambiguity, contradictions, missing deps, partial success\n5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n6. WRITE FINDINGS ──> Create research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n7. APPEND STATE ────> Add exactly one iteration record to JSONL\n8. UPDATE RESEARCH ─> Progressively update research/research.md when enabled\n9. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──> Check files, append, citations, and scope before reporting\n```\n\n### Step 1: Read State\n\nRead the paths provided in dispatch context:\n- `research/deep-research-config.json` -- lifecycle mode, budgets, packet boundaries\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` -- iteration history\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md` -- focus, key questions, exhausted approaches\n- `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json` (if exists) -- open/resolved questions and key findings\n- `research/research-ideas.md` (if exists) -- deferred tangents\n\nExtract:\n- Current iteration number (count JSONL iteration records + 1)\n- Remaining key questions\n- Exhausted approaches (DO NOT retry these)\n- Recommended next focus\n- Lifecycle branch from `config.lineage.lineageMode` (`new`, `resume`, or `restart`; `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred -- see `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`)\n\n**HARD BLOCK -- Missing or unreadable state**:\n- If `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, or `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing, unreadable, or structurally corrupt, do not infer a focus and do not execute research actions.\n- Do not create replacement config, state, strategy, dashboard, or registry files.\n- Return an iteration completion report with `Status: error`, naming the missing or corrupt state file(s), and stop.\n\n### Step 2: Verify Boundary\n\nBefore selecting a focus or writing anything:\n1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n2. Precompute intended write paths for this run:\n   - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`\n   - `research/research.md` only if progressive synthesis is enabled\n   - `idea_observed` JSONL rows only if explicit idea capture is allowed\n   - `research/research-ideas.md` only if operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed\n3. Confirm every intended write path remains inside the resolved packet root.\n4. Confirm `iteration-NNN.md` does not already exist.\n5. Confirm no reducer-owned file is scheduled for direct edit.\n\nIf any check fails, STOP with `Status: error`. Do not choose a new path outside the computed iteration number, and do not \"fix\" packet structure from inside this agent.\n\n### Step 3: Determine Focus\n\nBefore choosing a focus, read strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\":\n- `BLOCKED` categories must not be retried or varied.\n- `PRODUCTIVE` categories should be preferred for related questions.\n- If the selected focus falls inside a BLOCKED category, choose another.\n\nUse strategy.md \"Next Focus\". If it is empty or vague, pick the first unchecked \"Key Questions (remaining)\" item; if none remain, investigate the lowest-coverage area.\n\nIf multiple focus candidates are equally plausible:\n- Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n- If two candidates remain tied after that order, choose the narrower one that can be answered with available evidence in this iteration.\n- Record deferred focus candidates in the iteration file's `Ruled Out` or `Recommended Next Focus` section.\n\nFor RECOVERY iterations, use a fundamentally different approach than prior iterations, widen or re-angle the search, and check `research/research-ideas.md` for viable escape paths.\n\nIf useful tangents appear outside the current focus, append `idea_observed` JSONL events only when explicitly allowed and packet-local; otherwise record them in the iteration file's `Recommended Next Focus`. Never emit `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; the reducer owns promotion, ranking, and rejection filtering.\n\n### Step 4: Classify Edge Cases\n\nBefore research actions, classify any known edge condition and carry that classification into findings:\n\n| Condition | Trigger | Required Handling |\n|-----------|---------|-------------------|\n| Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n| Contradictory evidence | Two sources make incompatible claims about the same fact | Preserve both claims with citations, state which one is better supported if evidence allows, and avoid marking the question answered unless resolved |\n| Missing dependency | Optional file, tool, source, mirror report, or external URL needed for the ideal path is unavailable | Continue with an alternative in-scope source when possible; if the missing item is required state, report `error`; if evidence is partial, report `timeout` or `stuck` honestly |\n| Partial success | Some research actions succeed but others fail before the iteration completes | Write successful findings, document failed actions and recovery attempts, and set status based on the strongest truthful outcome |\n\nStatus selection for edge cases:\n- Use `complete` when enough cited evidence answers at least one in-scope question despite minor missing sources.\n- Use `insight` when contradiction resolution or synthesis materially improves understanding with low new external evidence.\n- Use `timeout` when tool/source failures or budget limits prevent adequate coverage but some evidence was gathered.\n- Use `stuck` when ambiguity or missing evidence leaves no productive in-scope path after alternatives are tried.\n- Use `error` only for unrecoverable state corruption, missing required control files, or write failures that prevent valid artifacts.\n\n### Step 5: Execute Research\n\nPerform 3-5 focused research actions.\n\n| Tool | When to Use | Example |\n|------|-------------|---------|\n| WebFetch | Official docs, API references, known URLs | Fetch MDN docs for an API |\n| Grep | Code patterns | Search for implementation examples |\n| Glob | File discovery | Find config files or tests |\n| Read | Specific file contents | Read implementation details |\n| memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n| Bash | Bounded data gathering | `wc -l`, `jq` for JSON parsing |\n\n**Budget**: Target 8-11 total tool calls, hard max 12. Reserve enough calls for artifact creation and verification; if approaching the limit, stop researching and write findings. Do not skip output verification to spend a final call on more research.\n\n**Citation rule**: Every finding must cite a source:\n- `[SOURCE: https://url]` for web sources\n- `[SOURCE: path/to/file:line]` for codebase sources\n- `[SOURCE: memory:spec-folder]` for memory hits\n- `[INFERENCE: based on X and Y]` for derived conclusions\n\n**Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n\nFor source failures, apply Tier 1-2 recovery:\n- **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n- **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, recommend the focus for \"Exhausted Approaches\" in the iteration file; do not edit strategy directly.\n- **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, write the failure in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n\n### Step 6: Write Findings\n\nCreate `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[What this iteration investigated and why. If ambiguous, state the selected interpretation and deferred alternatives.]\n\n## Findings\n1. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n2. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n3. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n\n## Ruled Out\n[Approaches tried this iteration that did not yield results, with why they failed.]\n\n## Dead Ends\n[Paths definitively eliminated and candidates for reducer promotion to strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\".]\n\n## Edge Cases\n- Ambiguous input: [none or selected interpretation + deferred alternatives]\n- Contradictory evidence: [none or source-backed conflict + resolution status]\n- Missing dependencies: [none or missing item + fallback used]\n- Partial success: [none or successful/failed actions + chosen status rationale]\n\n## Sources Consulted\n- [URL or file:line reference]\n- [URL or file:line reference]\n\n## Assessment\n- New information ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Questions addressed: [list]\n- Questions answered: [list]\n\n## Reflection\n- What worked and why: [approach + causal explanation]\n- What did not work and why: [failure + root cause]\n- What I would do differently: [specific next adjustment]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next, based on gaps discovered]\n```\n\nDo not write a placeholder iteration file. If findings are sparse because a tool failed, write the failure and recovery attempts with citations to tool outputs, consulted source paths, or prior packet evidence.\n\n### Step 7: Respect Reducer-Owned State\n\nDo not use `research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json`, or `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` as primary write targets. Instead:\n1. Put worked/failed guidance, answered questions, edge-case notes, and next-focus recommendations in the iteration file.\n2. Append the structured JSONL record.\n3. Let the workflow reducer refresh strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard.\n\n### Step 8: Append State\n\nAppend exactly ONE iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":N,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"[focus area]\",\"findingsCount\":N,\"newInfoRatio\":0.XX,\"noveltyJustification\":\"1-sentence explanation of newInfoRatio\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"q1\",\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q1\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"approach1\",\"approach2\"],\"focusTrack\":\"optional-track-label\",\"edgeCase\":\"none\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"WebFetch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"https://example.com/doc\",\"src/file.ts:42\"],\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"durationMs\":NNNNN}\n```\n\n**Status values**: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n- `complete`: Normal evidence gathering with new findings\n- `timeout`: Time/tool budget exceeded before finishing\n- `error`: Unrecoverable iteration failure\n- `stuck`: No productive avenues remain for current focus\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but meaningful synthesis or reframing\n- `thought`: Explicitly analytical iteration using prior packet evidence only\n\nRequired fields:\n- `noveltyJustification`: one sentence explaining the ratio (for example, \"2 of 4 findings were new, 1 partially new\")\n- `ruledOut`: attempted but failed approaches, or `[]`\n- `toolsUsed`: tools actually used during the iteration\n- `sourcesQueried`: source URLs, file paths, memory references, or command outputs consulted\n\nOptional fields:\n- `focusTrack`: multi-track research label such as `architecture`, `performance`, or `security`\n- `edgeCase`: `none`, `ambiguous-input`, `contradictory-evidence`, `missing-dependency`, or `partial-success`\n\n**Append discipline**:\n- Append exactly one JSONL record for the iteration.\n- Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n- Never append `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; reducer and operator workflows own those events.\n- Never rewrite, truncate, sort, or reformat existing JSONL lines.\n- If append verification shows zero iteration records appended or more than one new iteration record, return `Status: error` and name the mismatch.\n\n**newInfoRatio calculation**:\n- Fully new findings count as 1.0.\n- Partially new findings count as 0.5.\n- `newInfoRatio = (fully_new + 0.5 * partially_new) / total_findings`.\n- If there are no findings, set 0.0.\n- Add a +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped at 1.0, when synthesis reduces open questions, resolves contradictions, or provides a cleaner model without new external evidence.\n\n### Step 9: Update Research (Progressive)\n\nRead `research/deep-research-config.json` before touching `research/research.md`.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis == true`, add new findings to `research/research.md`; create it only if missing and only inside the resolved packet root.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis == false`, do not create or update `research/research.md`; synthesis owns it later.\n\n### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n\nBefore returning, verify:\n- `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` exists at the computed packet-local path.\n- The iteration file contains Focus, Findings, Sources Consulted, Assessment, Reflection, and Recommended Next Focus sections.\n- Every non-empty Finding has a `[SOURCE: ...]` or `[INFERENCE: ...]` marker.\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` has exactly one new iteration record for this iteration.\n- The JSONL line includes `type`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `findingsCount`, `newInfoRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `toolsUsed`, `sourcesQueried`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n- No reducer-owned file was edited directly.\n- No write escaped the resolved packet root.\n- No sub-agent was dispatched.\n\nIf any item fails, fix the in-scope output if safe. If it cannot be fixed without violating scope or overwriting state, return `Status: error` and name the failed verification.\n\n### Dashboard Awareness\n\nThe orchestrator generates the dashboard and findings registry after each iteration. This agent does not update reducer-owned files directly, but its JSONL fields feed those outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose | Budget |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| Read | State files, source code | 2-3 calls |\n| Write | Iteration file, state append | 2-3 calls |\n| Edit | `research/research.md` update when progressiveSynthesis is true | 0-1 calls |\n| WebFetch | External documentation | 1-2 calls |\n| Grep | Code pattern search | 1-2 calls |\n| Glob | File discovery | 0-1 calls |\n| Bash | Bounded data gathering (`jq`, `wc`, file checks) | 0-1 calls |\n\n### MCP Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n| `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources), or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n## 3. ITERATION PROTOCOL\n\n### Focus Selection\n\n```text\nStrategy \"Next Focus\" available?\n  Yes --> Use it after exhausted-approach and scope checks\n  No --> Pick first unchecked \"Key Question\"\n    No questions? --> Investigate lowest-coverage area\n      Multiple equal options? --> Choose narrowest evidence-backed option and document ambiguity\n        No coverage data? --> Report stuck (newInfoRatio = 0.0)\n```\n\n### Recovery Mode\n\nIf dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY MODE\":\n1. Read \"Exhausted Approaches\" in strategy.md.\n2. Choose a DIFFERENT approach:\n   - Prior WebFetch --> try codebase search.\n   - Prior broad search --> narrow to a specific aspect.\n   - Prior domain-specific pass --> try cross-domain analysis.\n3. Document the recovery attempt in findings.\n\n### Error-Aware Execution\n\nApply Tier 1-2 error handling:\n- **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n- **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, add the focus to the iteration file's Dead Ends or Recommended Next Focus section for reducer promotion to \"Exhausted Approaches\"; do not edit strategy directly.\n- **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, report the error in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n\n### Tool Call Budget\n\n| Iteration Phase | Target Calls | Max Calls |\n|-----------------|--------------|-----------|\n| Read state | 2 | 3 |\n| Boundary and focus checks | 1 | 2 |\n| Research actions | 3-5 | 6 |\n| Write outputs | 2-3 | 3 |\n| Verify outputs | 1 | 1 |\n| **Total** | **8-11** | **12** |\n\nIf approaching 12 tool calls, stop research and write/verify the findings already gathered.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `research/`; child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that target's `research/` folder.\n\n| File | Path | Operation |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | Read only |\n| State log | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Read + append exactly one line |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Read only for focus selection |\n| Findings registry | `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Read only if needed |\n| Iteration findings | `research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file only |\n| Research output | `research/research.md` | Read + edit only when `progressiveSynthesis` is true |\n| Idea observations | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Append `idea_observed` events only when explicit idea capture is allowed |\n| Ideas file | `research/research-ideas.md` | Append only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed |\n\n### Iteration Number Derivation\n\n```text\nCount lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\nCurrent iteration = count + 1\nPad to 3 digits for filename: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\nVerify iteration-NNN.md does not already exist before writing\n```\n\n### Write Safety\n\n- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; optional idea capture may add `idea_observed` events, but never `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`.\n- Strategy, registry, dashboard: reducer-owned; do not edit directly.\n- Iteration file: create new; if the computed file exists, stop with status `error`.\n- Research.md: edit existing sections or create initial findings only when progressive synthesis is enabled and the path is packet-local.\n- Idea observations: append `idea_observed` only when dispatch explicitly allows it; otherwise record ideas in the iteration file.\n\n---\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":420,"totalLines":584,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/agents/deep-research.md","time":{"start":1783486620899,"end":1783486620906}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aae0e71b03b58cf016a4dd89cd48c81918c9f2be4ef0ce141"}},"id":"prt_f401624df001qilErDugiuaWOA","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486620913,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_u6sUbaLm7xRodj4ZV7c9gCUR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: \n3: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n4: // ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n5: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n6: // ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n7: // ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n8: // ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n9: // ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n10: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n11: \n12: 'use strict';\n13: \n14: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n15: // 1. IMPORTS\n16: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n17: \n18: const fs = require('node:fs');\n19: const os = require('node:os');\n20: const path = require('node:path');\n21: const { spawn } = require('node:child_process');\n22: \n23: const {\n24:   classifyExitCode,\n25:   maybeThrowTestFault,\n26:   validateNamespaceValue,\n27: } = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n28: \n29: const {\n30:   runCappedPool,\n31:   appendStatusLedger,\n32:   markOrphanedLineages,\n33:   readRetryCountsFromLedger,\n34:   createWavePlannerInterface,\n35:   writeOrchestrationSummary,\n36: } = require('./fanout-pool.cjs');\n37: \n38: const {\n39:   runSalvageSweep,\n40:   extractTextFromOpencodeJson,\n41: } = require('./fanout-salvage.cjs');\n42: \n43: const {\n44:   appendObservabilityEvent,\n45: } = require('../lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs');\n46: \n47: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n48: // 2. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n49: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n50: \n51: const TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\n52: const isTsxLoaded = process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED === '1';\n53: \n54: function runTsxBootstrap() {\n55:   const child = spawn(\n56:     process.execPath,\n57:     ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n58:     {\n59:       cwd: process.cwd(),\n60:       env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n61:       stdio: [process.stdin.isTTY ? 'ignore' : 'pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n62:     },\n63:   );\n64: \n65:   if (!process.stdin.isTTY && child.stdin) {\n66:     child.stdin.on('error', () => {});\n67:     process.stdin.pipe(child.stdin);\n68:   }\n69: \n70:   child.stdout?.pipe(process.stdout);\n71:   child.stderr?.pipe(process.stderr);\n72: \n73:   for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n74:     process.once(signal, () => {\n75:       child.kill(signal);\n76:     });\n77:   }\n78: \n79:   child.on('close', (status, signal) => {\n80:     if (status !== null) {\n81:       process.exit(status);\n82:     }\n83:     process.exit(signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : signal === 'SIGTERM' ? 143 : 1);\n84:   });\n85: }\n86: \n87: if (require.main === module && !isTsxLoaded) {\n88:   runTsxBootstrap();\n89: }\n90: \n91: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: // 3. HELPERS\n93: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: \n95: function parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n96:   const args = {};\n97:   for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n98:     const token = argv[i];\n99:     if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n100:       throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n101:     }\n102:     const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n103:     const next = argv[i + 1];\n104:     if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n105:       args[key] = true;\n106:     } else {\n107:       args[key] = next;\n108:       i += 1;\n109:     }\n110:   }\n111:   return args;\n112: }\n113: \n114: function inputError(message) {\n115:   const err = new Error(message);\n116:   err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n117:   return err;\n118: }\n119: \n120: function ensureString(args, key) {\n121:   if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n122:     throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n123:   }\n124:   return args[key];\n125: }\n126: \n127: function parseOptionalNumber(args, key) {\n128:   const raw = args[key];\n129:   if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n130:     return null;\n131:   }\n132:   if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n133:     throw inputError(`${key} must be a number`);\n134:   }\n135:   const value = Number(raw);\n136:   if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n137:     throw inputError(`${key} must be a non-negative number`);\n138:   }\n139:   return value;\n140: }\n141: \n142: function readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName) {\n143:   if (!isRecord(rawConfig)) return null;\n144:   for (const name of names) {\n145:     if (!Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(rawConfig, name)) continue;\n146:     const raw = rawConfig[name];\n147:     if (raw === undefined || raw === null || raw === '') return null;\n148:     if (raw === true || raw === false) {\n149:       throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n150:     }\n151:     const value = Number(raw);\n152:     if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n153:       throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n154:     }\n155:     return Math.floor(value);\n156:   }\n157:   return null;\n158: }\n159: \n160: function readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName, fallback) {\n161:   const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName);\n162:   if (value === null) return fallback;\n163:   if (value <= 0) {\n164:     throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be greater than 0`);\n165:   }\n166:   return value;\n167: }\n168: \n169: function rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args) {\n170:   const merged = { ...(isRecord(rawConfig) ? rawConfig : {}) };\n171:   const mappings = [\n172:     ['stallWatchdogMs', 'stallWatchdogMs'],\n173:     ['maxCostUnitsPerLineage', 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage'],\n174:     ['maxTokensPerLineage', 'maxTokensPerLineage'],\n175:     ['maxTokenBudget', 'maxTokenBudget'],\n176:     ['maxTokenBudgetPerLineage', 'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage'],\n177:     ['costUnitsPerIteration', 'costUnitsPerIteration'],\n178:     ['estimatedTokensPerIteration', 'estimatedTokensPerIteration'],\n179:   ];\n180:   for (const [targetKey, argKey] of mappings) {\n181:     if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(args, argKey)) {\n182:       merged[targetKey] = args[argKey];\n183:     }\n184:   }\n185:   return merged;\n186: }\n187: \n188: function normalizeStopPolicy(raw) {\n189:   if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n190:     return 'convergence';\n191:   }\n192:   if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n193:     throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n194:   }\n195:   if (raw !== 'convergence' && raw !== 'max-iterations') {\n196:     throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n197:   }\n198:   return raw;\n199: }\n200: \n201: function jsonOut(payload) {\n202:   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n203: }\n204: \n205: function signalExitCode(signal) {\n206:   return signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : 143;\n207: }\n208: \n209: let fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = false;\n210: \n211: function installFanoutSignalHandlers(onStop) {\n212:   if (fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled) return;\n213:   fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = true;\n214: \n215:   for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n216:     process.once(signal, () => {\n217:       try {\n218:         onStop(signal);\n219:       } finally {\n220:         process.exit(signalExitCode(signal));\n221:       }\n222:     });\n223:   }\n224: }\n225: \n226: function updateLineageSnapshot(snapshots, event) {\n227:   if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return;\n228:   const existing = snapshots.get(event.label) || { label: event.label };\n229: \n230:   if (event.event === 'started') {\n231:     snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'running', started_at_iso: event.at });\n232:     return;\n233:   }\n234:   if (event.event === 'completed') {\n235:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n236:       ...existing,\n237:       status: 'fulfilled',\n238:       completed_at_iso: event.at,\n239:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n240:     });\n241:     return;\n242:   }\n243:   if (event.event === 'failed') {\n244:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n245:       ...existing,\n246:       status: event.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'rejected',\n247:       completed_at_iso: event.at,\n248:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n249:       error: event.error,\n250:     });\n251:     return;\n252:   }\n253:   if (event.event === 'retry_scheduled' || event.event === 'orphan_requeued') {\n254:     snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'requeued', updated_at_iso: event.at });\n255:     return;\n256:   }\n257:   if (event.event === 'progress') {\n258:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n259:       ...existing,\n260:       status: 'running',\n261:       updated_at_iso: event.at,\n262:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n263:     });\n264:   }\n265: }\n266: \n267: function buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n268:   return lineages.map((lineage) => snapshots.get(lineage.label) || { label: lineage.label, status: 'pending' });\n269: }\n270: \n271: function summarizeSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n272:   const results = buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots);\n273:   const succeeded = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'fulfilled').length;\n274:   const failed = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'rejected').length;\n275:   return {\n276:     results,\n277:     summary: {\n278:       total: lineages.length,\n279:       succeeded,\n280:       failed,\n281:       all_failed: lineages.length > 0 && failed === lineages.length,\n282:     },\n283:   };\n284: }\n285: \n286: function observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath) {\n287:   return path.join(path.dirname(ledgerPath), OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME);\n288: }\n289: \n290: function statusForLedgerEvent(entry) {\n291:   if (entry && typeof entry.status === 'string' && entry.status.trim() !== '') {\n292:     return entry.status;\n293:   }\n294:   if (!entry || typeof entry.event !== 'string') return 'unknown';\n295:   if (entry.event === 'started' || entry.event === 'progress' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting') return 'running';\n296:   if (entry.event === 'completed' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting_complete') return 'completed';\n297:   if (entry.event === 'failed') return entry.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'failed';\n298:   if (entry.event === 'stopped') return 'stopped';\n299:   if (entry.event === 'retry_scheduled' || entry.event === 'orphan_requeued') return 'retrying';\n300:   // Lag-ceiling signals from the pool: a stall warning while work remains pending, or a\n301:   // forced abort of the stalled attempt. Map both to typed statuses instead of 'unknown'.\n302:   if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_exceeded') return entry.action === 'abort' ? 'failed' : 'warning';\n303:   if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_abort') return 'failed';\n304:   if (entry.event === 'stall_detected') return 'warning';\n305:   if (entry.event === 'budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n306:   return 'unknown';\n307: }\n308: \n309: function appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry) {\n310:   appendStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry);\n311:   try {\n312:     appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath), entry, {\n313:       producer: 'fanout-run',\n314:       stream: 'orchestration-status',\n315:       subject: {\n316:         run_id: entry.run_id ?? null,\n317:         label: entry.label ?? null,\n318:         loop_type: entry.loop_type ?? null,\n319:         spec_folder: entry.spec_folder ?? null,\n320:       },\n321:       event: entry.event,\n322:       status: statusForLedgerEvent(entry),\n323:     });\n324:   } catch {\n325:     // Observability must not make the primary orchestration ledger fail.\n326:   }\n327: }\n328: \n329: const FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'flat_pool';\n330: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'wave';\n331: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment_model requires conflict-safety substrate';\n332: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment metadata requires conflict-safety substrate';\n333: const STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE = {\n334:   research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n335:   review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n336: };\n337: const ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES = new Set(['research', 'review']);\n338: const DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE = 'loopType must be \"research\" or \"review\"; context fan-out is deprecated. Use @context for one-shot retrieval, /deep:research or /deep:review bounded snapshots for iterative work, or /speckit:plan for implementation planning.';\n339: \n340: function assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType) {\n341:   if (!ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES.has(loopType)) {\n342:     throw inputError(DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE);\n343:   }\n344: }\n345: \n346: function hasNonEmptyArrayField(value) {\n347:   return Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0;\n348: }\n349: \n350: function collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig) {\n351:   const rejections = [];\n352:   if (fanoutConfig.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n353:     rejections.push({\n354:       scope: 'fanout',\n355:       label: null,\n356:       field: 'assignment_model',\n357:       message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n358:     });\n359:   }\n360: \n361:   for (const lineage of fanoutConfig.executors) {\n362:     if (lineage.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n363:       rejections.push({\n364:         scope: 'lineage',\n365:         label: lineage.label,\n366:         field: 'assignment_model',\n367:         message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n368:       });\n369:     }\n370: \n371:     const reservedFields = [];\n372:     if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.depends_on)) {\n373:       reservedFields.push('depends_on');\n374:     }\n375:     if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.touches)) {\n376:       reservedFields.push('touches');\n377:     }\n378:     if (reservedFields.length > 0) {\n379:       rejections.push({\n380:         scope: 'lineage',\n381:         label: lineage.label,\n382:         field: reservedFields.join(','),\n383:         message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION,\n384:       });\n385:     }\n386:   }\n387: \n388:   return rejections;\n389: }\n390: \n391: /**\n392:  * Force fan-out execution onto the existing flat pool while wave planning is gated.\n393:  *\n394:  * @param {Object} fanoutConfig - Parsed fan-out config.\n395:  * @returns {{ config: Object, rejections: Array<Object> }} Guarded config and rejection records.\n396:  */\n397: function applyFlatPoolAssignmentGuard(fanoutConfig) {\n398:   const rejections = collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig);\n399:   return {\n400:     config: {\n401:       ...fanoutConfig,\n402:       assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n403:       executors: fanoutConfig.executors.map((lineage) => ({\n404:         ...lineage,\n405:         assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n406:       })),\n407:     },\n408:     rejections,\n409:   };\n410: }\n411: \n412: function logFlatPoolGuardRejections({ rejections, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder }) {\n413:   if (rejections.length === 0) {\n414:     return;\n415:   }\n416:   const wavePlanner = createWavePlannerInterface();\n417:   for (const rejection of rejections) {\n418:     const labelSuffix = rejection.label ? ` lineage=${rejection.label}` : '';\n419:     process.stderr.write(`[fanout-run] ${rejection.message}${labelSuffix}\\n`);\n420:     appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n\n(Showing lines 1-420 of 1871. Use offset=421 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n// ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst os = require('node:os');\nconst path = require('node:path');","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n// ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst os = require('node:os');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { spawn } = require('node:child_process');\n\nconst {\n  classifyExitCode,\n  maybeThrowTestFault,\n  validateNamespaceValue,\n} = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  runCappedPool,\n  appendStatusLedger,\n  markOrphanedLineages,\n  readRetryCountsFromLedger,\n  createWavePlannerInterface,\n  writeOrchestrationSummary,\n} = require('./fanout-pool.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  runSalvageSweep,\n  extractTextFromOpencodeJson,\n} = require('./fanout-salvage.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  appendObservabilityEvent,\n} = require('../lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\nconst isTsxLoaded = process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED === '1';\n\nfunction runTsxBootstrap() {\n  const child = spawn(\n    process.execPath,\n    ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n    {\n      cwd: process.cwd(),\n      env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n      stdio: [process.stdin.isTTY ? 'ignore' : 'pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n    },\n  );\n\n  if (!process.stdin.isTTY && child.stdin) {\n    child.stdin.on('error', () => {});\n    process.stdin.pipe(child.stdin);\n  }\n\n  child.stdout?.pipe(process.stdout);\n  child.stderr?.pipe(process.stderr);\n\n  for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n    process.once(signal, () => {\n      child.kill(signal);\n    });\n  }\n\n  child.on('close', (status, signal) => {\n    if (status !== null) {\n      process.exit(status);\n    }\n    process.exit(signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : signal === 'SIGTERM' ? 143 : 1);\n  });\n}\n\nif (require.main === module && !isTsxLoaded) {\n  runTsxBootstrap();\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n  const args = {};\n  for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n    const token = argv[i];\n    if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n      throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n    }\n    const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n    const next = argv[i + 1];\n    if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n      args[key] = true;\n    } else {\n      args[key] = next;\n      i += 1;\n    }\n  }\n  return args;\n}\n\nfunction inputError(message) {\n  const err = new Error(message);\n  err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n  return err;\n}\n\nfunction ensureString(args, key) {\n  if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n  }\n  return args[key];\n}\n\nfunction parseOptionalNumber(args, key) {\n  const raw = args[key];\n  if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n    return null;\n  }\n  if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} must be a number`);\n  }\n  const value = Number(raw);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n    throw inputError(`${key} must be a non-negative number`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName) {\n  if (!isRecord(rawConfig)) return null;\n  for (const name of names) {\n    if (!Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(rawConfig, name)) continue;\n    const raw = rawConfig[name];\n    if (raw === undefined || raw === null || raw === '') return null;\n    if (raw === true || raw === false) {\n      throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n    }\n    const value = Number(raw);\n    if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n      throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n    }\n    return Math.floor(value);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName, fallback) {\n  const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName);\n  if (value === null) return fallback;\n  if (value <= 0) {\n    throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be greater than 0`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args) {\n  const merged = { ...(isRecord(rawConfig) ? rawConfig : {}) };\n  const mappings = [\n    ['stallWatchdogMs', 'stallWatchdogMs'],\n    ['maxCostUnitsPerLineage', 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage'],\n    ['maxTokensPerLineage', 'maxTokensPerLineage'],\n    ['maxTokenBudget', 'maxTokenBudget'],\n    ['maxTokenBudgetPerLineage', 'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage'],\n    ['costUnitsPerIteration', 'costUnitsPerIteration'],\n    ['estimatedTokensPerIteration', 'estimatedTokensPerIteration'],\n  ];\n  for (const [targetKey, argKey] of mappings) {\n    if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(args, argKey)) {\n      merged[targetKey] = args[argKey];\n    }\n  }\n  return merged;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeStopPolicy(raw) {\n  if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n    return 'convergence';\n  }\n  if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n  }\n  if (raw !== 'convergence' && raw !== 'max-iterations') {\n    throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n  }\n  return raw;\n}\n\nfunction jsonOut(payload) {\n  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n}\n\nfunction signalExitCode(signal) {\n  return signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : 143;\n}\n\nlet fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = false;\n\nfunction installFanoutSignalHandlers(onStop) {\n  if (fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled) return;\n  fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = true;\n\n  for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n    process.once(signal, () => {\n      try {\n        onStop(signal);\n      } finally {\n        process.exit(signalExitCode(signal));\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction updateLineageSnapshot(snapshots, event) {\n  if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return;\n  const existing = snapshots.get(event.label) || { label: event.label };\n\n  if (event.event === 'started') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'running', started_at_iso: event.at });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'completed') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: 'fulfilled',\n      completed_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'failed') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: event.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'rejected',\n      completed_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n      error: event.error,\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'retry_scheduled' || event.event === 'orphan_requeued') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'requeued', updated_at_iso: event.at });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'progress') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: 'running',\n      updated_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n  return lineages.map((lineage) => snapshots.get(lineage.label) || { label: lineage.label, status: 'pending' });\n}\n\nfunction summarizeSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n  const results = buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots);\n  const succeeded = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'fulfilled').length;\n  const failed = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'rejected').length;\n  return {\n    results,\n    summary: {\n      total: lineages.length,\n      succeeded,\n      failed,\n      all_failed: lineages.length > 0 && failed === lineages.length,\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath) {\n  return path.join(path.dirname(ledgerPath), OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME);\n}\n\nfunction statusForLedgerEvent(entry) {\n  if (entry && typeof entry.status === 'string' && entry.status.trim() !== '') {\n    return entry.status;\n  }\n  if (!entry || typeof entry.event !== 'string') return 'unknown';\n  if (entry.event === 'started' || entry.event === 'progress' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting') return 'running';\n  if (entry.event === 'completed' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting_complete') return 'completed';\n  if (entry.event === 'failed') return entry.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'stopped') return 'stopped';\n  if (entry.event === 'retry_scheduled' || entry.event === 'orphan_requeued') return 'retrying';\n  // Lag-ceiling signals from the pool: a stall warning while work remains pending, or a\n  // forced abort of the stalled attempt. Map both to typed statuses instead of 'unknown'.\n  if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_exceeded') return entry.action === 'abort' ? 'failed' : 'warning';\n  if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_abort') return 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'stall_detected') return 'warning';\n  if (entry.event === 'budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n  return 'unknown';\n}\n\nfunction appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry) {\n  appendStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry);\n  try {\n    appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath), entry, {\n      producer: 'fanout-run',\n      stream: 'orchestration-status',\n      subject: {\n        run_id: entry.run_id ?? null,\n        label: entry.label ?? null,\n        loop_type: entry.loop_type ?? null,\n        spec_folder: entry.spec_folder ?? null,\n      },\n      event: entry.event,\n      status: statusForLedgerEvent(entry),\n    });\n  } catch {\n    // Observability must not make the primary orchestration ledger fail.\n  }\n}\n\nconst FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'flat_pool';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'wave';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment_model requires conflict-safety substrate';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment metadata requires conflict-safety substrate';\nconst STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE = {\n  research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n  review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n};\nconst ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES = new Set(['research', 'review']);\nconst DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE = 'loopType must be \"research\" or \"review\"; context fan-out is deprecated. Use @context for one-shot retrieval, /deep:research or /deep:review bounded snapshots for iterative work, or /speckit:plan for implementation planning.';\n\nfunction assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType) {\n  if (!ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES.has(loopType)) {\n    throw inputError(DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction hasNonEmptyArrayField(value) {\n  return Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0;\n}\n\nfunction collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig) {\n  const rejections = [];\n  if (fanoutConfig.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n    rejections.push({\n      scope: 'fanout',\n      label: null,\n      field: 'assignment_model',\n      message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n    });\n  }\n\n  for (const lineage of fanoutConfig.executors) {\n    if (lineage.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n      rejections.push({\n        scope: 'lineage',\n        label: lineage.label,\n        field: 'assignment_model',\n        message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n      });\n    }\n\n    const reservedFields = [];\n    if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.depends_on)) {\n      reservedFields.push('depends_on');\n    }\n    if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.touches)) {\n      reservedFields.push('touches');\n    }\n    if (reservedFields.length > 0) {\n      rejections.push({\n        scope: 'lineage',\n        label: lineage.label,\n        field: reservedFields.join(','),\n        message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION,\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  return rejections;\n}\n\n/**\n * Force fan-out execution onto the existing flat pool while wave planning is gated.\n *\n * @param {Object} fanoutConfig - Parsed fan-out config.\n * @returns {{ config: Object, rejections: Array<Object> }} Guarded config and rejection records.\n */\nfunction applyFlatPoolAssignmentGuard(fanoutConfig) {\n  const rejections = collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig);\n  return {\n    config: {\n      ...fanoutConfig,\n      assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n      executors: fanoutConfig.executors.map((lineage) => ({\n        ...lineage,\n        assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n      })),\n    },\n    rejections,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction logFlatPoolGuardRejections({ rejections, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder }) {\n  if (rejections.length === 0) {\n    return;\n  }\n  const wavePlanner = createWavePlannerInterface();\n  for (const rejection of rejections) {\n    const labelSuffix = rejection.label ? ` lineage=${rejection.label}` : '';\n    process.stderr.write(`[fanout-run] ${rejection.message}${labelSuffix}\\n`);\n    appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":420,"totalLines":1871,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1783486620894,"end":1783486620910}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aae0e71b03b58cf016a4dd89cd47c8191b4743c1d977fae7a"}},"id":"prt_f401624bf001Ak2CeTFkgYVvtl","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486620913,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MLIzFpE5OV2XaHIlGfqw0A7H","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"antiConvergence\": {\n6:     \"minIterations\": 3,\n7:     \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n8:     \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n9:   },\n10:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n11:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n12:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n13:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n14:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n15:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n16:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n17:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n18:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n19:   \"executor\": {\n20:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n21:     \"model\": null,\n22:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n23:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n24:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n25:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n26:   },\n27:   \"lineage\": {\n28:     \"sessionId\": \"\",\n29:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n30:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n31:     \"allowedModes\": [\n32:       \"new\",\n33:       \"resume\",\n34:       \"restart\"\n35:     ],\n36:     \"deferredModes\": [\n37:       \"fork\",\n38:       \"completed-continue\"\n39:     ],\n40:     \"generation\": 1,\n41:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n42:   },\n43:   \"reducer\": {\n44:     \"enabled\": true,\n45:     \"version\": \"1.0\",\n46:     \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n47:     \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n48:     \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n49:     \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n50:       \"key-questions\",\n51:       \"answered-questions\",\n52:       \"what-worked\",\n53:       \"what-failed\",\n54:       \"exhausted-approaches\",\n55:       \"ruled-out-directions\",\n56:       \"next-focus\"\n57:     ]\n58:   },\n59:   \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n60:   \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n61:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n62:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n63:   \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n64:   \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n65:   \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n66:   \"fileProtection\": {\n67:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n68:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n69:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n70:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n71:     \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n72:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n73:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n74:   },\n75:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n76:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n77:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n78:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n79:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n80:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n81:   }\n82: }\n\n(End of file - total 82 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"allowedModes\": [\n      \"new\",\n      \"resume\",\n      \"restart\"\n    ],\n    \"deferredModes\": [\n      \"fork\",\n      \"completed-continue\"\n    ],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n    \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n    \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n      \"key-questions\",\n      \"answered-questions\",\n      \"what-worked\",\n      \"what-failed\",\n      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n      \"next-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":82,"totalLines":82,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","time":{"start":1783486620901,"end":1783486620912}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aae0e71b03b58cf016a4dd89cd4948191b24e151a4e15e768"}},"id":"prt_f401624e4001E846OhFBtsRNqK","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486620925,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_REq6EQx7ZXmGGynyOpjQXtOr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ### Question Injection Surface\n34: \n35: Use `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n36: \n37: - `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n38: - `text`: question text to promote\n39: - `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n40: - `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n41: - `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n42: - `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n43: \n44: The reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n45: \n46: Question ownership is explicit:\n47: \n48: - Inbox rows are immutable input.\n49: - The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n50: - Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n51: \n52: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. TOPIC\n57: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n62: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n63: Generated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n64: \n65: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n66: - [ ] [Question 2]\n67: - [ ] [Question 3]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n73: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n78: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n83: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n84: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n90: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n91: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n92: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n93: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n99: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n100: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n101: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n107: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n108: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n109: \n110: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n111: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n112: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n113: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n114: \n115: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n116: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n117: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n124: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n125: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n126: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n131: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n132: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n133: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n138: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n139: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n140: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n145: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n146: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n147: \n148: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n149: \n150: Populate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n151: \n152: - Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n153: - Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n154: - Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n155: - Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n156: \n157: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n162: - Max iterations: [from config]\n163: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n164: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n165: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n166: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n167: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n168: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n169: - Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n170: - Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n171: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n172: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n173: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n174: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n175: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n176: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n### Question Injection Surface\n\nUse `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n\n- `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n- `text`: question text to promote\n- `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n- `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n- `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n- `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n\nThe reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n\nQuestion ownership is explicit:\n\n- Inbox rows are immutable input.\n- The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n- Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\nGenerated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n\n- Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n- Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n- Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n- Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n- Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n- Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":176,"totalLines":176,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1783486620921,"end":1783486620924}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aae0e71b03b58cf016a4dd89cd498819192da83f478832121"}},"id":"prt_f401624e6001MSmgE4OZu8rL9W","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486620960,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UlRXSZXr92agWeJyyZn72ICV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: DEEP-RESEARCH\n2: Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n3: \n4: # Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n5: \n6: This prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n7: \n8: ## STATE\n9: \n10: {state_summary}\n11: \n12: Research Topic: {research_topic}\n13: Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n14: Focus Area: {next_focus}\n15: Remaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\n16: Carried-Forward Open Questions:\n17: {carried_forward_open_questions}\n18: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n19: \n20: ## STATE FILES\n21: \n22: All paths are relative to the repo root.\n23: \n24: - Config: {state_paths_config}\n25: - State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n26: - Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n27: - Registry: {state_paths_registry}\n28: - Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n29: - Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n30: \n31: ## CONSTRAINTS\n32: \n33: - You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n34: - Target 3-5 research actions. Max 12 tool calls total.\n35: - Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n36: - The workflow reducer owns strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard synchronization.\n37: - Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n38: - When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced. Each event MUST use one of these two EXACT shapes. The reducer discriminates node vs edge by `type`, then validates each node's `kind` against the node vocabulary and each edge's `relation` against the relation vocabulary — any event outside these vocabularies is silently dropped, and if every event is dropped the convergence graph stays empty (nodeCount 0, empty signals):\n39:   - Node: `{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"kind\":\"<QUESTION|FINDING|CLAIM|SOURCE>\",\"label\":\"<short human name>\"}` — the semantic kind goes in the dedicated `kind` field (uppercase, one of the four listed); `label` is a free-text display name ONLY, never the kind.\n40:   - Edge: `{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"source\":\"<nodeId>\",\"target\":\"<nodeId>\",\"relation\":\"<ANSWERS|SUPPORTS|CONTRADICTS|SUPERSEDES|DERIVED_FROM|COVERS|CITES>\"}` — use `source`/`target`/`relation` (NOT `from`/`to`/`label`); `source` and `target` must reference node `id`s.\n41: \n42: ## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n43: \n44: You MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n45: \n46: 1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path is pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Next Focus.\n47: \n48: 2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY — NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored (the iteration will look incomplete and the reducer may re-run it). Required schema:\n49: \n50: ```json\n51: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":<0..1>,\"status\":\"<string>\",\"focus\":\"<string>\",\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */],\"executor\":{/* workflow-owned for non-native runs */}}\n52: ```\n53: \n54: Append via single-line JSON with newline terminator — for example: `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print the JSON to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n55: \n56: For non-native CLI executors, the workflow owns executor provenance. It writes a pre-dispatch sentinel, then patches the first canonical `\"type\":\"iteration\"` record with the `executor` block before `post_dispatch_validate` runs. Do NOT append your own `dispatch_failure` event or a partial fallback record when the executor itself crashes or times out; the workflow emits the typed failure event on that path.\n57: \n58: 3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration — e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same content as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, invariant, observation, edge, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line. The reducer reads the combined state log + delta files to rebuild dashboards and registries after interruption or partial runs.\n59: \n60: Example delta file contents (one iteration):\n61: ```json\n62: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"...\"}\n63: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter003-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n64: {\"type\":\"invariant\",\"id\":\"inv-iter003-001\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n65: {\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter003-001\",\"packet\":\"007\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":3}\n66: {\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-iter003-001\",\"relation\":\"VIOLATES\",\"source\":\"obs-001\",\"target\":\"inv-001\",\"iteration\":3}\n67: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n68: ```\n69: \n70: All three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).\n\n(End of file - total 70 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP-RESEARCH\nResolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n\n# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nResearch Topic: {research_topic}\nIteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nFocus Area: {next_focus}\nRemaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\nCarried-Forward Open Questions:\n{carried_forward_open_questions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n\n## STATE FILES","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","text":"DEEP-RESEARCH\nResolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n\n# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nResearch Topic: {research_topic}\nIteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nFocus Area: {next_focus}\nRemaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\nCarried-Forward Open Questions:\n{carried_forward_open_questions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n\n- Config: {state_paths_config}\n- State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n- Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n- Registry: {state_paths_registry}\n- Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n- Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n- Target 3-5 research actions. Max 12 tool calls total.\n- Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n- The workflow reducer owns strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard synchronization.\n- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n- When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced. Each event MUST use one of these two EXACT shapes. The reducer discriminates node vs edge by `type`, then validates each node's `kind` against the node vocabulary and each edge's `relation` against the relation vocabulary — any event outside these vocabularies is silently dropped, and if every event is dropped the convergence graph stays empty (nodeCount 0, empty signals):\n  - Node: `{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"kind\":\"<QUESTION|FINDING|CLAIM|SOURCE>\",\"label\":\"<short human name>\"}` — the semantic kind goes in the dedicated `kind` field (uppercase, one of the four listed); `label` is a free-text display name ONLY, never the kind.\n  - Edge: `{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"source\":\"<nodeId>\",\"target\":\"<nodeId>\",\"relation\":\"<ANSWERS|SUPPORTS|CONTRADICTS|SUPERSEDES|DERIVED_FROM|COVERS|CITES>\"}` — use `source`/`target`/`relation` (NOT `from`/`to`/`label`); `source` and `target` must reference node `id`s.\n\n## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n\nYou MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n\n1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path is pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Next Focus.\n\n2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY — NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored (the iteration will look incomplete and the reducer may re-run it). Required schema:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":<0..1>,\"status\":\"<string>\",\"focus\":\"<string>\",\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */],\"executor\":{/* workflow-owned for non-native runs */}}\n```\n\nAppend via single-line JSON with newline terminator — for example: `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print the JSON to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n\nFor non-native CLI executors, the workflow owns executor provenance. It writes a pre-dispatch sentinel, then patches the first canonical `\"type\":\"iteration\"` record with the `executor` block before `post_dispatch_validate` runs. Do NOT append your own `dispatch_failure` event or a partial fallback record when the executor itself crashes or times out; the workflow emits the typed failure event on that path.\n\n3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration — e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same content as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, invariant, observation, edge, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line. The reducer reads the combined state log + delta files to rebuild dashboards and registries after interruption or partial runs.\n\nExample delta file contents (one iteration):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"...\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter003-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"invariant\",\"id\":\"inv-iter003-001\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter003-001\",\"packet\":\"007\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-iter003-001\",\"relation\":\"VIOLATES\",\"source\":\"obs-001\",\"target\":\"inv-001\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n```\n\nAll three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":70,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","time":{"start":1783486620956,"end":1783486620959}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0aae0e71b03b58cf016a4dd89cd4a08191ab376d4f87224faf"}},"id":"prt_f4016250f0016g86n2VR4ZXgNZ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4015d4ae001YJhShN2tXALza3"}}
