 Line 56:        e.g. registry[\"research\"].packet → deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n\n  Line 57:        (the 4 improvement modes all share the deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/ packet)\n\n  Line 74: deep-loop-workflows/\n\n  Line 85: All modes consume `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free): executor config, prompt-pack, validation, atomic state, coverage-graph, Bayesian scoring, fan-out, the council primitives, and the promoted plumbing (capability resolver, artifact-root, loop-lock CLI, lifecycle taxonomy). The runtime never gains an `improvement` loopType — improvement stays host-driven.\n\n  Line 95: - **ALWAYS** keep exactly one `graph-metadata.json` (this hub's) so the advisor sees one skill identity, whether a mode is reached via `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)`, a `/deep:*` command, or an agent.\n\n  Line 96: - **ALWAYS** keep `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` hub routing, the `/deep:*` commands, and the agent types as complementary surfaces over the same packets — never let one surface fork per-mode logic out of its packet.\n\n  Line 99: - **NEVER** add an `improvement` `loopType` to `deep-loop-runtime/convergence.cjs` (improvement is host-driven; `runtimeLoopType` stays `null`).\n\n  Line 112: - Backend: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` (frozen, consumed by every mode).\n\n  Line 123: - `Skill(deep-loop-workflows[, hint])` reaches a mode, and the `/deep:*` commands and agent types still reach the same packets.\n\n  Line 137: - `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` is the invokable hub; active `/deep:*` commands and the agent types (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `ai-council`, `deep-improvement`) are complementary surfaces over the same packets.\n\n  Line 138: - `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend every mode consumes.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:\n  Line 3:   \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n\n  Line 114:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 6 samples/cell, throttled serial real kimi-for-coding/k2p7 dispatches. (The 4th fixture hard-roman-to-int was excluded - its run stalled under orchestration churn; the 3-fixture result is conclusive.) Unlike the saturated run 006, correctness SEPARATED here. Per-framework correctness (n=18): tidd-ec 1.0 = race 1.0 = costar 1.0 (perfect tier) > cidi 0.996 > rcaf 0.992. Trust verdict: TIE on correctness (the 3 perfect frameworks cannot be statistically separated, top-pair margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The actionable signal: rcaf (the former convention default) is objectively the WEAKEST - it produced strict-validator code that missed adversarial cases - so it is retired/avoided for this model. Among the perfect tier, costar is primary for cross-evidence robustness (also MiMo's empirical winner, benchmark 004; favored by run 006's judge); tidd-ec is the most token-efficient (25 vs costar 70 median words) and is the fallback. This objectively refutes run 006's subjective gpt-5.5 judge, which had wrongly ranked rcaf/race highest.\",\n\n  Line 190:       \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 200:           \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verify the full live list with 'opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams'. Omit --agent (warns + falls back on 1.15.13). Manual direct-provider reroute uses xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined. Context window 1,000,000 tokens (released 2026-04-22). OpenAI-compatible endpoint https://token-plan-ams.xiaomimimo.com/v1; opencode cost shows 0/0 (Token-Plan subscription). --variant maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings — always dispatch with --variant high (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13). Best prompt framework (benchmark 004, 10/10 real runs): COSTAR or RACE + lean pre-planning — frame for format/brevity, not guardrails; TIDD-EC/dense ranked last; avoid CIDI (intermittent tool-only file-writes).\"\n\n  Line 207:         \"model_slug\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 214:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13 (2026-06-01). default_variant high: `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) and `--variant high` is confirmed accepted — always dispatch with it. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` warns and falls back on 1.15.13. format_mode json: OpenAI-compatible endpoint; dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized envelope. Manual direct-provider reroutes use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined.\",\n\n  Line 225:         \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n\n  Line 231:         \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n\n  Line 247:           \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n\n  Line 250:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n\n  Line 255:       \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 265:           \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n\n  Line 272:         \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 283:         \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n\n  Line 284:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n\n  Line 287:         \"dedicated Z.AI GLM Coding Plan subscription pool (`zai-coding-plan`), independent of kimi / minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n\n  Line 288:         \"flagship long-horizon coding model (Z.AI docs: Terminal-Bench 2.1 81.0, SWE-bench Pro 62.1 — both above GLM-5.1)\",\n\n  Line 296:         \"--variant ↔ reasoning_effort mapping unverified (GLM has native high/max; opencode forwarding not confirmed)\",\n\n  Line 311:           \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n\n  Line 314:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n\n  Line 317:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md:\n  Line 3: description: Per-model prompt-craft hub for small-model dispatch (DeepSeek-v4-pro + Kimi-k2.7-code + MiniMax-M3 + MiMo-V2.5-Pro + GLM-5.2 via cli-opencode). OWNS the per-model prompt-craft profiles in references/models/ (framework + scaffold + gotchas, mirroring model_profiles.json); executor MECHANICS (binary flags, invocation wrappers) stay in cli-opencode. Advisor co-surfaces it with that executor.\n\n  Line 8: <!-- Keywords: small-model, deepseek-v4-pro, kimi-k2.7-code, kimi-for-coding, minimax-m3, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-token-plan, minimax-api, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, haiku, opencode-go, deepseek-api, context-budget, output-verification, model-profiles, structured-permissions, quota-fallback -->\n\n  Line 23: - MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via `cli-opencode`)\n\n  Line 24: - GLM-5.2 (via `cli-opencode`)\n\n  Line 32: - Model names: `kimi-k2.7-code`, `deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-m3`, `mimo-v2.5-pro`, `glm-5.2`, `haiku`\n\n  Line 33: - Provider names: `opencode-go`, `deepseek-api`, `kimi-for-coding` (Kimi For Coding plan), `minimax-coding-plan` (Token Plan) / `minimax` (Direct API), `minimax-token-plan` / `minimax-api`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe) / `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API), `zai-coding-plan` (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan)\n\n  Line 69:     \"mimo\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"mimo-v2.5-pro\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"mimo pro\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 70:     \"glm\": \"glm-5.2\", \"glm-5.2\": \"glm-5.2\", \"glm5.2\": \"glm-5.2\", \"zai\": \"glm-5.2\", \"zai-coding-plan\": \"glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 101: - `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` (runtime helpers)\n\n  Line 208: | MiMo-V2.5-Pro | `cli-opencode` → xiaomi-token-plan-ams (xiaomi-token-plan) · `cli-opencode` → xiaomi (xiaomi-direct-api) | active — Token Plan (default) + Direct API (pay-per-token) |\n\n  Line 209: | GLM-5.2 | `cli-opencode` → zai-coding-plan (zai-coding-plan) | active (single path; Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) |\n\n  Line 232: 5. **Honor the in-scope model set** — DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro, GLM-5.2 active; Haiku optional. Frontier models (Opus, Sonnet, gpt-5.5) are explicitly out of scope.\n\n  Line 266: - [`cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md`](../cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md) — Executor prompt-pack templates (MiniMax, MiMo scaffolds in mechanics form)\n\n  Line 281:     +-- cli-opencode                ← owns MECHANICS: DeepSeek/Kimi/MiniMax/MiMo flags + permissions\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/quota_fallback.md:\n  Line 60: > The user's actual model rotation is small-only: DeepSeek-v4-pro (deepseek-api pool), Kimi-k2.7-code (kimi-for-coding pool), MiniMax-M3 (minimax-token-plan primary pool, minimax-api secondary executor pool), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (xiaomi-token-plan pool), with optional future Claude Haiku. There are no frontier models (Opus / Sonnet / gpt-5.5) in scope to escalate to. The original Phase D plan assumed a small-to-frontier escalation chain; that assumption is gone. Naive \"pick another model\" routing on hard-fail would just pick a same-pool sibling, accomplishing nothing while spending more quota.\n\n  Line 76: | `xiaomi-token-plan` | `mimo-v2.5-pro` | none | Xiaomi Token Plan Europe. |\n\n  Line 148: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts\n\n  Line 259: 9. Run `fallback-router` unit tests.\n\n  Line 304: npx vitest run tests/deep-loop/fallback-router.vitest.ts\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/pattern_index.md:\n  Line 49: | Bayesian tool scoring (Laplace-smoothed per-call scoring) | `system-spec-kit` + `sk-prompt-models` | [`../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/bayesian-scorer.ts`](../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/bayesian-scorer.ts) + [`./output_verification.md`](./output_verification.md) § Tool scoring state file format | shipped |\n\n  Line 50: | Fallback router (TS helper applied via recipe field) | `system-spec-kit` | [`../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`](../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts) | shipped |\n\n  Line 53: | Permissions gate runtime (pre-tool-call enforcer) | `system-spec-kit` | [`../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/permissions-gate.ts`](../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/permissions-gate.ts) | shipped |\n\n  Line 56: | MiMo-V2.5-Pro prompt-framework guidance (empirical winner: **COSTAR + lean**; RACE fallback — frame for format/brevity, NOT guardrails; TIDD-EC ranked last) | `sk-prompt-models` | [`./models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md`](./models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md) | shipped (benchmark 004) |\n\n  Line 64: | `cli-opencode` | DeepSeek-v4-pro via DeepSeek API direct + DeepSeek via opencode-go pool + Kimi-k2.7-code via the Kimi For Coding plan + MiniMax-M3 via the Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan`) and Direct API (`minimax`, pay-per-token) + MiMo-V2.5-Pro via the Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams`) and Xiaomi Direct API (`xiaomi`) + GLM-5.2 via the Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (`zai-coding-plan`) | Permissions matrix, budget propagation mirror. Prompt-CRAFT (framework selection, pre-planning density, per-model guidance) now lives in the hub profiles at `sk-prompt-models/references/models/`; cli-opencode owns only invocation MECHANICS (binary flags, provider id, quota pool). |\n\n  Line 67: | `system-spec-kit` | Runtime helpers (TypeScript) | bayesian-scorer.ts, fallback-router.ts, permissions-gate.ts |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/_index.md:\n  Line 27: | `mimo-v2.5-pro` | [`mimo-v2.5-pro.md`](./mimo-v2.5-pro.md) | COSTAR; RACE fallback (avoid TIDD-EC, CIDI) | lean | empirical (benchmark 004, confidence high) |\n\n  Line 30: | `glm-5.2` | [`glm-5.2.md`](./glm-5.2.md) | COSTAR; TIDD-EC fallback (avoid RCAF) | lean | empirical (benchmark 008; perfect tier tied, rcaf weakest) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md:\n  Line 2: title: GLM-5.2 Prompt-Craft Profile\n\n  Line 3: model_id: \"glm-5.2\"\n\n  Line 4: description: How to prompt GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan, slug zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2) via cli-opencode — COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008 — best-of-tied perfect tier; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF) with lean pre-planning over the 1M window, file-anchored context scaffold, Z.AI Coding Plan dispatch gotchas, and native vision-to-code image input (§7).\n\n  Line 6:   - \"glm-5.2 prompt framework\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"glm-5.2 dispatch scaffold\"\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"deep-loop-runtime|deep-loop-workflows|system-deep-loop|fallback-router|mimo|glm-5\\.2|glm52|MiMo|GLM","time":{"start":1783486719666,"end":1783486719681}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00b8938aba7e0f4d016a4dd8ff82c0819190360682e2ab7542"}},"id":"prt_f4017a654001jl9kE0IAMoRMww","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f40177d06001Bo0FwBZzcHRgoj"}}
