ch backend actually runs the mode: runtime-loop-type (deep-loop-runtime convergence), improvement-host (deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode), or external-adapter (loop owned by external packaging).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. 'lexical' = weighted-regex scoring in skill_advisor.py AND present in both projection maps. 'alias-fold' = TS DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL only (alias projection, not lexically scored). 'metadata' = resolved by skill membership; no advisor map entry. 'command-bridge' = routed by its /deep:* command, not an advisor map entry.\",\n    \"legacyAdvisorId\": \"The legacy deep-* skill id the projection maps key on (present for lexical + alias-fold modes only).\",\n    \"advisorDefaultMode\": \"Marks the default mode a multi-mode legacy id folds to (deep-improvement -> agent-improvement). Never inferred from array order.\",\n    \"legacyAliases\": \"The TypeScript scorer alias set (aliases.ts SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS[legacyAdvisorId]) the merged-identity layer keys on; the drift-guard asserts these match it order-insensitive. The Python deep-router uses its own alias set + regex patterns by design (same keys, different values), so the guard only cross-checks that each legacyAdvisorId key also exists in the Python SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. Most packets use folder == packetSkillName == deep-<mode> (e.g. deep-ai-council). Exception: the four improvement lanes (agent/skill/model/ai-system-improvement) multiplex onto one shared packet 'deep-improvement', so several workflowModes map to that single folder/packetSkillName. The legacy public key 'ai-council' is preserved only on the command/agent surfaces, not on the packet folder/name.\",\n    \"driftGuard\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"runtime-loop\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the runtime-loop backend: modes with backendKind 'runtime-loop-type' converge over deep-loop-runtime, keyed by runtimeLoopType (research|review|council). runtimeLoopType is explicit null for improvement-host and external-adapter modes and is never inferred from workflowMode.\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"skill\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n  \"version\": \"1.1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the three-tier discriminator (workflowMode/runtimeLoopType/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection. The advisor keeps its hardcoded projection maps (Python DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY, TypeScript DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL) in sync with this registry via a CI drift-guard test (maps == registry projection); the advisor does NOT read this file at runtime, which avoids cross-skill import coupling on the advisor hot path.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public command/advisor/mode key. Stable identity used in commands, advisor aliases, and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"runtimeLoopType\": \"The graph-backed convergence loop key consumed by deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs. Validated against exactly research|review|council. Explicit null for improvement-host and external-adapter modes; NEVER inferred from workflowMode.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend actually runs the mode: runtime-loop-type (deep-loop-runtime convergence), improvement-host (deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode), or external-adapter (loop owned by external packaging).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. 'lexical' = weighted-regex scoring in skill_advisor.py AND present in both projection maps. 'alias-fold' = TS DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL only (alias projection, not lexically scored). 'metadata' = resolved by skill membership; no advisor map entry. 'command-bridge' = routed by its /deep:* command, not an advisor map entry.\",\n    \"legacyAdvisorId\": \"The legacy deep-* skill id the projection maps key on (present for lexical + alias-fold modes only).\",\n    \"advisorDefaultMode\": \"Marks the default mode a multi-mode legacy id folds to (deep-improvement -> agent-improvement). Never inferred from array order.\",\n    \"legacyAliases\": \"The TypeScript scorer alias set (aliases.ts SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS[legacyAdvisorId]) the merged-identity layer keys on; the drift-guard asserts these match it order-insensitive. The Python deep-router uses its own alias set + regex patterns by design (same keys, different values), so the guard only cross-checks that each legacyAdvisorId key also exists in the Python SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. Most packets use folder == packetSkillName == deep-<mode> (e.g. deep-ai-council). Exception: the four improvement lanes (agent/skill/model/ai-system-improvement) multiplex onto one shared packet 'deep-improvement', so several workflowModes map to that single folder/packetSkillName. The legacy public key 'ai-council' is preserved only on the command/agent surfaces, not on the packet folder/name.\",\n    \"driftGuard\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"runtime-loop\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the runtime-loop backend: modes with backendKind 'runtime-loop-type' converge over deep-loop-runtime, keyed by runtimeLoopType (research|review|council). runtimeLoopType is explicit null for improvement-host and external-adapter modes and is never inferred from workflowMode.\",\n      \"runtimeLoopTypes\": [\"research\", \"review\", \"council\"]\n    },\n    \"advisor-projection\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares that the advisor keeps hardcoded projection maps (Python DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY, TypeScript DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL) in sync with this registry's advisorRouting projection. The advisor does not read this file at runtime; a CI drift-guard asserts maps == registry projection.\",\n      \"driftGuard\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"deprecatedModes\": [],\n  \"modes\": [\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"research\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": \"research\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"runtime-loop-type\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\", \"WebFetch\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-research\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:research\",\n      \"agent\": \"deep-research\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"research/\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"deep-research\", \"research loop\", \"iterative investigation workflow\", \"research convergence detection\", \"autoresearch\", \"iterative-research\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"lexical\",\n        \"legacyAdvisorId\": \"deep-research\",\n        \"legacyAliases\": [\"command-spec-kit-deep-research\", \"/deep:start-research-loop\", \"spec_kit:deep-research\", \"deep-research\", \"sk-deep-research\"],\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-research\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"review\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": \"review\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"runtime-loop-type\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-review\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:review\",\n      \"agent\": \"deep-review\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"review/\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"deep-review\", \"review loop\", \"iterative review loop\", \"severity weighted findings\", \"convergence review\", \"release-readiness\", \"deep-review wave\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"lexical\",\n        \"legacyAdvisorId\": \"deep-review\",\n        \"legacyAliases\": [\"command-spec-kit-deep-review\", \"/deep:start-review-loop\", \"spec_kit:deep-review\", \"deep-review\", \"sk-deep-review\"],\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-review\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"ai-council\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": \"council\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"runtime-loop-type\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-ai-council\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:ai-council\",\n      \"agent\": \"ai-council\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"ai-council/\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"deep-ai-council\", \"ai council deliberation\", \"multi-seat planning council\", \"council convergence\", \"planning council\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"lexical\",\n        \"legacyAdvisorId\": \"deep-ai-council\",\n        \"legacyAliases\": [\"@deep-ai-council\", \"deep-ai-council\", \"deep ai council\", \"ai council\", \"planning council\", \"council deliberation\", \"multi-ai-council\"],\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-ai-council\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"agent-improvement\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": null,\n      \"backendKind\": \"improvement-host\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"loopHostMode\": \"agent-improvement\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:agent-improvement\",\n      \"agent\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"improvement/\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"improve agent\", \"evaluate agent\", \"agent scoring\", \"score agent candidate\", \"promote or rollback agent change\", \"agent-improvement\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"alias-fold\",\n        \"legacyAdvisorId\": \"deep-improvement\",\n        \"advisorDefaultMode\": true,\n        \"legacyAliases\": [\"command-spec-kit-deep-agent-improvement\", \"/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop\", \"deep-agent-improvement\", \"sk-deep-agent-improvement\"],\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-improvement\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"model-benchmark\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": null,\n      \"backendKind\": \"improvement-host\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"loopHostMode\": \"model-benchmark\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:model-benchmark\",\n      \"agent\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"improvement/\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"model benchmark\", \"benchmark a model\", \"prompt framework benchmark\", \"benchmark-harness\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"command-bridge\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-improvement\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"skill-benchmark\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": null,\n      \"backendKind\": \"improvement-host\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"loopHostMode\": \"skill-benchmark\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:skill-benchmark\",\n      \"agent\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"improvement/\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"skill benchmark\", \"benchmark a skill\", \"skill routing benchmark\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"command-bridge\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-improvement\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"ai-system-improvement\",\n      \"runtimeLoopType\": null,\n      \"backendKind\": \"external-adapter\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\", \"Grep\", \"Glob\", \"Task\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"loopHostMode\": \"non-dev-ai-system-refine\",\n      \"command\": \"/deep:ai-system-improvement\",\n      \"agent\": \"deep-improvement\",\n      \"artifactRoot\": \"improvement/\",\n      \"externalLoopOwner\": \"external packaging (e.g. Barter Copywriter) owns the Python loop, gates, scoring, and kill-switches\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"non-dev ai system\", \"non-dev-ai-system\", \"package ai system benchmark\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"command-bridge\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"deep-improvement\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":199,"totalLines":199,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json","time":{"start":1783486731311,"end":1783486731332}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cb781f35fd74d7f016a4dd909cf3c8191b2324842fe849816"}},"id":"prt_f4017d42c0013SLWlqyfIVW1vd","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4017a9e4001pEEavI0qn5pDNp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486731336,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JL4OQAlyTbL6EkAOsTlp31iQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-loop-runtime\n3: version: 1.5.0.1\n4: description: \"Shared deep-loop runtime: executor + prompt-pack + validation + atomic state + coverage-graph + Bayesian scoring + fallback routing.\"\n5: allowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Glob, Grep]\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Deep Loop Runtime\n9: \n10: Shared runtime infrastructure for the active deep-review, deep-research, and deep-ai-council workflows, plus host-driven deep-improvement support. Legacy context parsers remain only for historical artifacts. The FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation moved the shared runtime libraries, coverage-graph ownership, script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests into this peer skill.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n15: \n16: This skill is consumed by the deep-review and deep-research workflow YAML and script paths, the deep-ai-council council modules, and shared deep-improvement primitives. It is not invoked directly as a user-facing workflow.\n17: \n18: Use it when a deep-loop workflow needs shared runtime support for:\n19: \n20: - executor configuration and audit metadata\n21: - prompt-pack rendering\n22: - post-dispatch validation\n23: - atomic state files and JSONL repair\n24: - loop locking and permissions gates\n25: - Bayesian scoring and fallback routing\n26: - coverage-graph schema, query, and signal interpretation\n27: \n28: ### Activation Triggers\n29: \n30: This skill is activated when:\n31: \n32: - A deep-review or deep-research workflow YAML invokes `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<name>.cjs`\n33: - A test file imports `from '.../deep-loop-runtime/lib/...'`\n34: - An operator queries / mutates the coverage graph via the runtime scripts\n35: - A workflow needs Bayesian convergence scoring or fallback executor routing\n36: \n37: ### When NOT to Use\n38: \n39: Do not invoke this skill when:\n40: \n41: - A user requests an interactive command (use `/deep:review` or `/deep:research` instead — those orchestrate this runtime)\n42: - A package outside deep-review / deep-research needs deep-loop semantics (out of supported scope; open a packet to extend ownership)\n43: - An MCP tool surface is needed (this skill explicitly has none — the isolation ADR removed the deep-loop MCP tools)\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n48: \n49: This skill has no direct LLM-facing keyword triggers — it is invoked by workflow YAMLs (via `bash:` script calls) and by test imports. It is a simple intent-to-runtime-domain router, not a keyed `references/<key>/` / `assets/<key>/` resource router: `references/` is a flat contract set and this skill has no `assets/` directory.\n50: \n51: ### Primary Detection Signal\n52: \n53: ```bash\n54: request_text=\"$(printf '%s' \"$USER_REQUEST\" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')\"\n55: case \"$request_text\" in\n56:   *\"deep-loop runtime\"*|*\"deep-loop-runtime\"*|*\"executor config\"*|*\"prompt pack\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n57:   *\"coverage graph\"*|*\"deep_loop_graph\"*|*\"bayesian scorer\"*|*\"loop lock\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n58:   *\"fallback router\"*|*\"post-dispatch validate\"*|*\"jsonl repair\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n59:   *) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=0 ;;\n60: esac\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Phase Detection\n64: \n65: ```text\n66: TASK CONTEXT\n67:     |\n68:     +- STEP 0: Detect runtime-call intent vs. consumer-orchestration intent\n69:     +- STEP 1: If consumer (workflow YAML), invoke the relevant scripts/*.cjs\n70:     +- STEP 2: If contributor (modifying lib code), load matching lib/ subtree\n71:     +- STEP 3: If test author, load tests/ + lib/ pair\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Resource Domains\n75: \n76: ```text\n77: lib/deep-loop/*.ts            # 10 runtime modules (executor, prompt-pack, validation, state, scoring, routing)\n78: lib/coverage-graph/*.ts       # 3 schema + query + signals modules\n79: scripts/*.cjs                 # 4 entry points (convergence, upsert, query, status)\n80: database/*.sqlite              # runtime-owned SQLite (deep-loop-graph.sqlite + council-graph.sqlite)\n81: tests/{unit,integration,lifecycle}/  # 21+ vitest files split by responsibility\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ### Resource Loading Levels\n85: \n86: | Tier | When loaded | Purpose |\n87: |------|-------------|---------|\n88: | ALWAYS | SKILL.md frontmatter | description, allowed-tools, version |\n89: | CONDITIONAL | When a runtime call dispatches | `lib/` modules required by the called function |\n90: | ON_DEMAND | When a test fails or a contributor extends | `tests/` + matching `lib/` sub-tree |\n91: \n92: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n93: \n94: ```python\n95: from pathlib import Path\n96: \n97: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n98: RESOURCE_BASES = (\n99:     SKILL_ROOT / \"lib\",\n100:     SKILL_ROOT / \"scripts\",\n101:     SKILL_ROOT / \"tests\",\n102:     SKILL_ROOT / \"references\",\n103: )\n104: ROUTABLE_SUFFIXES = {\".md\", \".ts\", \".cjs\"}\n105: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n106:     \"Confirm whether the request targets a runtime library, coverage graph, script entry point, or consumer workflow\",\n107:     \"Name the concrete module, script, test, or failing command\",\n108:     \"Confirm whether deep-review, deep-research, deep-ai-council, or deep-improvement is the consuming workflow\",\n109:     \"Confirm the verification command set before completion\",\n110: ]\n111: \n112: def discover_runtime_resources() -> set[str]:\n113:     resources = []\n114:     for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n115:         if base.exists():\n116:             resources.extend(\n117:                 path for path in base.rglob(\"*\")\n118:                 if path.is_file() and path.suffix.lower() in ROUTABLE_SUFFIXES\n119:             )\n120:     return {path.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for path in resources}\n121: \n122: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n123:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n124:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n125:     if resolved.suffix.lower() not in ROUTABLE_SUFFIXES:\n126:         raise ValueError(f\"Only runtime skill resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n127:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n128: \n129: def load_if_available(relative_path: str, inventory: set[str], loaded: list[str], seen: set[str]) -> None:\n130:     guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n131:     if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n132:         load(guarded)\n133:         loaded.append(guarded)\n134:         seen.add(guarded)\n135: \n136: def route(task):\n137:     inventory = discover_runtime_resources()\n138:     loaded, seen = [], set()\n139: \n140:     if mentions_specific_lib(task):\n141:         name = normalize_lib_name(task)  # e.g. bayesian-scorer, prompt-pack\n142:         load_if_available(f\"lib/deep-loop/{name}.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n143:         load_if_available(f\"tests/unit/{name}.vitest.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n144:     elif mentions_coverage_graph(task):\n145:         for path in sorted(p for p in inventory if p.startswith(\"lib/coverage-graph/\")):\n146:             load_if_available(path, inventory, loaded, seen)\n147:         for path in sorted(p for p in inventory if p.startswith(\"tests/integration/review-depth-\")):\n148:             load_if_available(path, inventory, loaded, seen)\n149:     elif mentions_script(task):\n150:         script = normalize_script_name(task)  # e.g. convergence, status, query, upsert\n151:         load_if_available(f\"scripts/{script}.cjs\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n152:         load_if_available(f\"tests/integration/{script}-script.vitest.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n153:         load_if_available(\"lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n154:     else:\n155:         load_if_available(\"references/integration_points.md\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n156:         return {\n157:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n158:             \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n159:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n160:             \"defer_to\": \"consumer skill: deep-review, deep-research, deep-ai-council, or deep-improvement\",\n161:             \"resources\": loaded,\n162:         }\n163: \n164:     if not loaded:\n165:         load_if_available(\"references/integration_points.md\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n166:         return {\n167:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n168:             \"notice\": \"Matched a runtime domain but no current resource path was available\",\n169:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n170:             \"resources\": loaded,\n171:         }\n172: \n173:     return {\"load_level\": \"CONDITIONAL\", \"resources\": loaded}\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ---\n177: \n178: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n179: \n180: ### Runtime Architecture\n181: \n182: The runtime exposes deep-loop primitives to consumer workflows through two paths: **direct `.cjs` script invocation** (replacing the removed `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools) and **TypeScript library imports** (from workflow scripts and tests).\n183: \n184: ```text\n185: [deep-review/deep-research workflow YAML]\n186:             │\n187:             ├─ bash: node .../scripts/<name>.cjs   (coverage-graph mutations)\n188:             │       └─→ lib/coverage-graph/*.ts → database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite\n189:             │\n190:             └─ ts-import: lib/deep-loop/<lib>.ts   (runtime primitives)\n191:                     └─→ atomic-state, prompt-pack, post-dispatch-validate, etc.\n192: ```\n193: \n194: ### Library Structure\n195: \n196: **`lib/deep-loop/` (19 modules):**\n197: - `executor-config.ts` — schema + parsing for per-iteration executor settings\n198: - `executor-audit.ts` — appends `executor` block to iteration JSONL (provenance)\n199: - `prompt-pack.ts` — renders the iteration prompt template\n200: - `post-dispatch-validate.ts` — validates iteration outputs (markdown + JSONL + delta)\n201: - `atomic-state.ts` — atomic state-log writes\n202: - `jsonl-repair.ts` — recovers corrupt JSONL state lines\n203: - `loop-lock.ts` — single-writer locking\n204: - `permissions-gate.ts` — permission scope checks\n205: - `bayesian-scorer.ts` — convergence scoring\n206: - `fallback-router.ts` — executor fallback decision matrix\n207: - `artifact-root.cjs` — resolves the canonical review/research artifact root\n208: - `continuity-thread.cjs` — continuity-thread linkage across runs\n209: - `evidence-contract.ts` — evidence/citation contract validation\n210: - `lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` — lifecycle-mode taxonomy (new/resume/restart)\n211: - `lineage-timestamp-window.ts` — lineage timestamp-window checks\n212: - `observability-events.cjs` — observability event emission\n213: - `receipt-crypto.ts` — engine-held HMAC receipt crypto primitives\n214: - `runtime-capabilities.cjs` — runtime capability resolver\n215: - `sleep.ts` — async sleep helper\n216: \n217: **`lib/coverage-graph/` (3 modules):**\n218: - `coverage-graph-db.ts` — SQLite schema + node-kind allow-list + connection lifecycle\n219: - `coverage-graph-query.ts` — query builders\n220: - `coverage-graph-signals.ts` — convergence signal extraction\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 380. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-loop-runtime\nversion: 1.5.0.1\ndescription: \"Shared deep-loop runtime: executor + prompt-pack + validation + atomic state + coverage-graph + Bayesian scoring + fallback routing.\"\nallowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Glob, Grep]\n---\n\n# Deep Loop Runtime\n\nShared runtime infrastructure for the active deep-review, deep-research, and deep-ai-council workflows, plus host-driven deep-improvement support. Legacy context parsers remain only for historical artifacts. The FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation moved the shared runtime libraries, coverage-graph ownership, script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests into this peer skill.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\nThis skill is consumed by the deep-review and deep-research workflow YAML and script paths, the deep-ai-council council modules, and shared deep-improvement primitives. It is not invoked directly as a user-facing workflow.\n\nUse it when a deep-loop workflow needs shared runtime support for:\n\n- executor configuration and audit metadata","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: deep-loop-runtime\nversion: 1.5.0.1\ndescription: \"Shared deep-loop runtime: executor + prompt-pack + validation + atomic state + coverage-graph + Bayesian scoring + fallback routing.\"\nallowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Glob, Grep]\n---\n\n# Deep Loop Runtime\n\nShared runtime infrastructure for the active deep-review, deep-research, and deep-ai-council workflows, plus host-driven deep-improvement support. Legacy context parsers remain only for historical artifacts. The FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation moved the shared runtime libraries, coverage-graph ownership, script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests into this peer skill.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\nThis skill is consumed by the deep-review and deep-research workflow YAML and script paths, the deep-ai-council council modules, and shared deep-improvement primitives. It is not invoked directly as a user-facing workflow.\n\nUse it when a deep-loop workflow needs shared runtime support for:\n\n- executor configuration and audit metadata\n- prompt-pack rendering\n- post-dispatch validation\n- atomic state files and JSONL repair\n- loop locking and permissions gates\n- Bayesian scoring and fallback routing\n- coverage-graph schema, query, and signal interpretation\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\nThis skill is activated when:\n\n- A deep-review or deep-research workflow YAML invokes `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<name>.cjs`\n- A test file imports `from '.../deep-loop-runtime/lib/...'`\n- An operator queries / mutates the coverage graph via the runtime scripts\n- A workflow needs Bayesian convergence scoring or fallback executor routing\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\nDo not invoke this skill when:\n\n- A user requests an interactive command (use `/deep:review` or `/deep:research` instead — those orchestrate this runtime)\n- A package outside deep-review / deep-research needs deep-loop semantics (out of supported scope; open a packet to extend ownership)\n- An MCP tool surface is needed (this skill explicitly has none — the isolation ADR removed the deep-loop MCP tools)\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\nThis skill has no direct LLM-facing keyword triggers — it is invoked by workflow YAMLs (via `bash:` script calls) and by test imports. It is a simple intent-to-runtime-domain router, not a keyed `references/<key>/` / `assets/<key>/` resource router: `references/` is a flat contract set and this skill has no `assets/` directory.\n\n### Primary Detection Signal\n\n```bash\nrequest_text=\"$(printf '%s' \"$USER_REQUEST\" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')\"\ncase \"$request_text\" in\n  *\"deep-loop runtime\"*|*\"deep-loop-runtime\"*|*\"executor config\"*|*\"prompt pack\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n  *\"coverage graph\"*|*\"deep_loop_graph\"*|*\"bayesian scorer\"*|*\"loop lock\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n  *\"fallback router\"*|*\"post-dispatch validate\"*|*\"jsonl repair\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n  *) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=0 ;;\nesac\n```\n\n### Phase Detection\n\n```text\nTASK CONTEXT\n    |\n    +- STEP 0: Detect runtime-call intent vs. consumer-orchestration intent\n    +- STEP 1: If consumer (workflow YAML), invoke the relevant scripts/*.cjs\n    +- STEP 2: If contributor (modifying lib code), load matching lib/ subtree\n    +- STEP 3: If test author, load tests/ + lib/ pair\n```\n\n### Resource Domains\n\n```text\nlib/deep-loop/*.ts            # 10 runtime modules (executor, prompt-pack, validation, state, scoring, routing)\nlib/coverage-graph/*.ts       # 3 schema + query + signals modules\nscripts/*.cjs                 # 4 entry points (convergence, upsert, query, status)\ndatabase/*.sqlite              # runtime-owned SQLite (deep-loop-graph.sqlite + council-graph.sqlite)\ntests/{unit,integration,lifecycle}/  # 21+ vitest files split by responsibility\n```\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Tier | When loaded | Purpose |\n|------|-------------|---------|\n| ALWAYS | SKILL.md frontmatter | description, allowed-tools, version |\n| CONDITIONAL | When a runtime call dispatches | `lib/` modules required by the called function |\n| ON_DEMAND | When a test fails or a contributor extends | `tests/` + matching `lib/` sub-tree |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (\n    SKILL_ROOT / \"lib\",\n    SKILL_ROOT / \"scripts\",\n    SKILL_ROOT / \"tests\",\n    SKILL_ROOT / \"references\",\n)\nROUTABLE_SUFFIXES = {\".md\", \".ts\", \".cjs\"}\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm whether the request targets a runtime library, coverage graph, script entry point, or consumer workflow\",\n    \"Name the concrete module, script, test, or failing command\",\n    \"Confirm whether deep-review, deep-research, deep-ai-council, or deep-improvement is the consuming workflow\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before completion\",\n]\n\ndef discover_runtime_resources() -> set[str]:\n    resources = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            resources.extend(\n                path for path in base.rglob(\"*\")\n                if path.is_file() and path.suffix.lower() in ROUTABLE_SUFFIXES\n            )\n    return {path.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for path in resources}\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() not in ROUTABLE_SUFFIXES:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only runtime skill resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef load_if_available(relative_path: str, inventory: set[str], loaded: list[str], seen: set[str]) -> None:\n    guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n    if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n        load(guarded)\n        loaded.append(guarded)\n        seen.add(guarded)\n\ndef route(task):\n    inventory = discover_runtime_resources()\n    loaded, seen = [], set()\n\n    if mentions_specific_lib(task):\n        name = normalize_lib_name(task)  # e.g. bayesian-scorer, prompt-pack\n        load_if_available(f\"lib/deep-loop/{name}.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n        load_if_available(f\"tests/unit/{name}.vitest.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n    elif mentions_coverage_graph(task):\n        for path in sorted(p for p in inventory if p.startswith(\"lib/coverage-graph/\")):\n            load_if_available(path, inventory, loaded, seen)\n        for path in sorted(p for p in inventory if p.startswith(\"tests/integration/review-depth-\")):\n            load_if_available(path, inventory, loaded, seen)\n    elif mentions_script(task):\n        script = normalize_script_name(task)  # e.g. convergence, status, query, upsert\n        load_if_available(f\"scripts/{script}.cjs\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n        load_if_available(f\"tests/integration/{script}-script.vitest.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n        load_if_available(\"lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n    else:\n        load_if_available(\"references/integration_points.md\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n        return {\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"defer_to\": \"consumer skill: deep-review, deep-research, deep-ai-council, or deep-improvement\",\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    if not loaded:\n        load_if_available(\"references/integration_points.md\", inventory, loaded, seen)\n        return {\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"notice\": \"Matched a runtime domain but no current resource path was available\",\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    return {\"load_level\": \"CONDITIONAL\", \"resources\": loaded}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Runtime Architecture\n\nThe runtime exposes deep-loop primitives to consumer workflows through two paths: **direct `.cjs` script invocation** (replacing the removed `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools) and **TypeScript library imports** (from workflow scripts and tests).\n\n```text\n[deep-review/deep-research workflow YAML]\n            │\n            ├─ bash: node .../scripts/<name>.cjs   (coverage-graph mutations)\n            │       └─→ lib/coverage-graph/*.ts → database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite\n            │\n            └─ ts-import: lib/deep-loop/<lib>.ts   (runtime primitives)\n                    └─→ atomic-state, prompt-pack, post-dispatch-validate, etc.\n```\n\n### Library Structure\n\n**`lib/deep-loop/` (19 modules):**\n- `executor-config.ts` — schema + parsing for per-iteration executor settings\n- `executor-audit.ts` — appends `executor` block to iteration JSONL (provenance)\n- `prompt-pack.ts` — renders the iteration prompt template\n- `post-dispatch-validate.ts` — validates iteration outputs (markdown + JSONL + delta)\n- `atomic-state.ts` — atomic state-log writes\n- `jsonl-repair.ts` — recovers corrupt JSONL state lines\n- `loop-lock.ts` — single-writer locking\n- `permissions-gate.ts` — permission scope checks\n- `bayesian-scorer.ts` — convergence scoring\n- `fallback-router.ts` — executor fallback decision matrix\n- `artifact-root.cjs` — resolves the canonical review/research artifact root\n- `continuity-thread.cjs` — continuity-thread linkage across runs\n- `evidence-contract.ts` — evidence/citation contract validation\n- `lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` — lifecycle-mode taxonomy (new/resume/restart)\n- `lineage-timestamp-window.ts` — lineage timestamp-window checks\n- `observability-events.cjs` — observability event emission\n- `receipt-crypto.ts` — engine-held HMAC receipt crypto primitives\n- `runtime-capabilities.cjs` — runtime capability resolver\n- `sleep.ts` — async sleep helper\n\n**`lib/coverage-graph/` (3 modules):**\n- `coverage-graph-db.ts` — SQLite schema + node-kind allow-list + connection lifecycle\n- `coverage-graph-query.ts` — query builders\n- `coverage-graph-signals.ts` — convergence signal extraction","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":380,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1783486731314,"end":1783486731334}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cb781f35fd74d7f016a4dd909cf448191bc89303ef7a83136"}},"id":"prt_f4017d430001Tsd7lROo9uKLcR","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4017a9e4001pEEavI0qn5pDNp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486731345,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cTJDGSclhZOiWZzhZBYOmdqO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/quota_fallback.md","offset":130,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/quota_fallback.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n130: \n131: if (failed.fallback_target === null) {\n132:   return failFast(`${failed.primary_quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured`);\n133: }\n134: \n135: const target = registry.models.find((model) => model.id === failed.fallback_target);\n136: if (!target) return failFast(\"configured fallback is not in the registry\");\n137: \n138: if (target.primary_quota_pool === failed.primary_quota_pool) {\n139:   return failFast(\"same-pool fallback rejected\");\n140: }\n141: \n142: return fallback(target.id);\n143: ```\n144: \n145: The production helper is:\n146: \n147: ```text\n148: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts\n149: ```\n150: \n151: That helper consumes a normalized projection where `quota_pool` is derived from\n152: the registry's `primary_quota_pool`.\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Worked Examples\n157: \n158: ### DeepSeek-v4-pro Default\n159: \n160: Registry:\n161: \n162: ```json\n163: {\n164:   \"id\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n165:   \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n166:   \"fallback_target\": null\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: Result:\n171: \n172: ```json\n173: {\n174:   \"action\": \"fail-fast\",\n175:   \"reason\": \"deepseek-api pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for deepseek-v4-pro\"\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: This prevents an unapproved retry through another provider path.\n180: \n181: ### Same-Pool Fallback Rejected (hypothetical)\n182: \n183: If `deepseek-v4-pro` were configured to fall back to a second model that also lived on the `deepseek-api` pool:\n184: \n185: ```json\n186: {\n187:   \"id\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n188:   \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n189:   \"fallback_target\": \"some-deepseek-api-model\"\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: Target (same pool):\n194: \n195: ```json\n196: {\n197:   \"id\": \"some-deepseek-api-model\",\n198:   \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\"\n199: }\n200: ```\n201: \n202: Result:\n203: \n204: ```json\n205: {\n206:   \"action\": \"fail-fast\",\n207:   \"reason\": \"deepseek-api pool exhausted, fallback target some-deepseek-api-model shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected\"\n208: }\n209: ```\n210: \n211: Same-pool siblings are rejected. The pool is the boundary, not the model's context window.\n212: \n213: ### Haiku To DeepSeek-v4-pro\n214: \n215: Registry change:\n216: \n217: ```json\n218: {\n219:   \"id\": \"haiku\",\n220:   \"primary_quota_pool\": \"anthropic\",\n221:   \"fallback_target\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\"\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: Target:\n226: \n227: ```json\n228: {\n229:   \"id\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n230:   \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\"\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: Result:\n235: \n236: ```json\n237: {\n238:   \"action\": \"fallback\",\n239:   \"target\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\"\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: This is a separate-pool fallback.\n244: \n245: It is only relevant after the optional Haiku stub becomes active.\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Adoption Checklist For Haiku\n250: \n251: 1. Confirm Haiku is actually in the user's dispatch rotation.\n252: 2. Confirm the exact executor and model id.\n253: 3. Populate the `haiku` stub in `sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n254: 4. Set `context_length` from current official/runtime information.\n255: 5. Set `avg_iter_wall_clock_min` from a measured iteration.\n256: 6. Change `status` from `optional-unverified` to `active`.\n257: 7. Set source model `fallback_target` fields only where fallback is desired.\n258: 8. Run `jq empty` on the registry.\n259: 9. Run `fallback-router` unit tests.\n260: 10. Re-index the advisor.\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Error Message Templates\n265: \n266: ### No Target Configured\n267: \n268: ```text\n269: {quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for {model_id}\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### Same-Pool Target Rejected\n273: \n274: ```text\n275: {quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target {target_id} shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Unknown Source\n279: \n\n(Showing lines 130-279 of 329. Use offset=280 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nif (failed.fallback_target === null) {\n  return failFast(`${failed.primary_quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured`);\n}\n\nconst target = registry.models.find((model) => model.id === failed.fallback_target);\nif (!target) return failFast(\"configured fallback is not in the registry\");\n\nif (target.primary_quota_pool === failed.primary_quota_pool) {\n  return failFast(\"same-pool fallback rejected\");\n}\n\nreturn fallback(target.id);\n```\n\nThe production helper is:\n\n```text\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts\n```","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/quota_fallback.md","text":"\nif (failed.fallback_target === null) {\n  return failFast(`${failed.primary_quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured`);\n}\n\nconst target = registry.models.find((model) => model.id === failed.fallback_target);\nif (!target) return failFast(\"configured fallback is not in the registry\");\n\nif (target.primary_quota_pool === failed.primary_quota_pool) {\n  return failFast(\"same-pool fallback rejected\");\n}\n\nreturn fallback(target.id);\n```\n\nThe production helper is:\n\n```text\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts\n```\n\nThat helper consumes a normalized projection where `quota_pool` is derived from\nthe registry's `primary_quota_pool`.\n\n---\n\n## Worked Examples\n\n### DeepSeek-v4-pro Default\n\nRegistry:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n  \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n  \"fallback_target\": null\n}\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"fail-fast\",\n  \"reason\": \"deepseek-api pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for deepseek-v4-pro\"\n}\n```\n\nThis prevents an unapproved retry through another provider path.\n\n### Same-Pool Fallback Rejected (hypothetical)\n\nIf `deepseek-v4-pro` were configured to fall back to a second model that also lived on the `deepseek-api` pool:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n  \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n  \"fallback_target\": \"some-deepseek-api-model\"\n}\n```\n\nTarget (same pool):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"some-deepseek-api-model\",\n  \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\"\n}\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"fail-fast\",\n  \"reason\": \"deepseek-api pool exhausted, fallback target some-deepseek-api-model shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected\"\n}\n```\n\nSame-pool siblings are rejected. The pool is the boundary, not the model's context window.\n\n### Haiku To DeepSeek-v4-pro\n\nRegistry change:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"haiku\",\n  \"primary_quota_pool\": \"anthropic\",\n  \"fallback_target\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\"\n}\n```\n\nTarget:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n  \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\"\n}\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"fallback\",\n  \"target\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\"\n}\n```\n\nThis is a separate-pool fallback.\n\nIt is only relevant after the optional Haiku stub becomes active.\n\n---\n\n## Adoption Checklist For Haiku\n\n1. Confirm Haiku is actually in the user's dispatch rotation.\n2. Confirm the exact executor and model id.\n3. Populate the `haiku` stub in `sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n4. Set `context_length` from current official/runtime information.\n5. Set `avg_iter_wall_clock_min` from a measured iteration.\n6. Change `status` from `optional-unverified` to `active`.\n7. Set source model `fallback_target` fields only where fallback is desired.\n8. Run `jq empty` on the registry.\n9. Run `fallback-router` unit tests.\n10. Re-index the advisor.\n\n---\n\n## Error Message Templates\n\n### No Target Configured\n\n```text\n{quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for {model_id}\n```\n\n### Same-Pool Target Rejected\n\n```text\n{quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target {target_id} shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected\n```\n\n### Unknown Source\n","lineStart":130,"lineEnd":279,"totalLines":329,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/quota_fallback.md","time":{"start":1783486731329,"end":1783486731344}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cb781f35fd74d7f016a4dd909cf4c8191b5b12c0388543174"}},"id":"prt_f4017d43f001JELEWAog0PsQ0v","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4017a9e4001pEEavI0qn5pDNp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486731349,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_l3NnVvEtpPMNGpUu3eZalwbF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Deep-Loop Fallback Router\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: \n5: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: // 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n7: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8: \n9: export type FallbackAction = 'fallback' | 'fail-fast';\n10: \n11: /** Executor result category used by typed fallback route selection. */\n12: export type FallbackRouteOutcome = 'success' | 'failure';\n13: \n14: /** Failure classes that can select a targeted fallback route. */\n15: export type FallbackFailureKind =\n16:   | 'timeout'\n17:   | 'auth-failure'\n18:   | 'quota-exceeded'\n19:   | 'executor-error'\n20:   | (string & {});\n21: \n22: /** Per-failure target map for typed fallback routes. */\n23: export interface FallbackFailureTargets {\n24:   readonly default?: string;\n25:   readonly [failureKind: string]: string | undefined;\n26: }\n27: \n28: /** Fallback decision returned to dispatch callers. */\n29: export type FallbackRoute = {\n30:   readonly action: FallbackAction;\n31:   readonly target?: string;\n32:   readonly reason: string;\n33:   readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n34:   readonly routeGroupId?: string;\n35:   readonly hopIndex?: number;\n36: };\n37: \n38: /** Runtime context attached to a routed fallback decision. */\n39: export interface FallbackRouteContext {\n40:   readonly outcome?: FallbackRouteOutcome;\n41:   readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n42:   readonly routeGroupId?: string;\n43:   readonly hopIndex?: number;\n44: }\n45: \n46: /** Model routing profile used by fallback graph resolution. */\n47: export type ModelProfile = {\n48:   readonly id: string;\n49:   readonly quota_pool: string;\n50:   readonly fallback_target: string | null;\n51:   readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n52:   readonly onSuccessTarget?: string | null;\n53:   readonly onFailureTarget?: string | FallbackFailureTargets | null;\n54:   readonly routeScope?: string;\n55: };\n56: \n57: /** Registry of model profiles available to the fallback router. */\n58: export type ModelRegistry = {\n59:   readonly models: readonly ModelProfile[];\n60: };\n61: \n62: /** Configuration for validating fallback graph edges before dispatch. */\n63: export interface FallbackGraphValidationOptions {\n64:   readonly maxHops?: number;\n65: }\n66: \n67: /** Validated router that binds a registry after graph preflight. */\n68: export interface FallbackRouter {\n69:   resolve(\n70:     failedModelId: string,\n71:     approvedModelIds?: readonly string[],\n72:     context?: FallbackRouteContext,\n73:   ): FallbackRoute;\n74: }\n75: \n76: type TargetKind = 'legacy' | 'success' | 'failure';\n77: \n78: interface TargetSelection {\n79:   readonly target: string | null;\n80:   readonly kind: TargetKind;\n81:   readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n82: }\n83: \n84: interface FallbackEdge {\n85:   readonly source: ModelProfile;\n86:   readonly targetId: string;\n87:   readonly kind: TargetKind;\n88:   readonly failureKind?: string;\n89: }\n90: \n91: const DEFAULT_MAX_HOPS = 1;\n92: \n93: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: // 2. HELPERS\n95: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n96: \n97: function findModel(registry: ModelRegistry, modelId: string): ModelProfile | undefined {\n98:   return registry.models.find((model) => model.id === modelId);\n99: }\n100: \n101: function isFailureTargets(\n102:   value: string | FallbackFailureTargets | null | undefined,\n103: ): value is FallbackFailureTargets {\n104:   return typeof value === 'object' && value !== null;\n105: }\n106: \n107: function selectFailureTarget(\n108:   failedModel: ModelProfile,\n109:   failureKind: FallbackFailureKind | undefined,\n110: ): TargetSelection {\n111:   const configuredTarget = failedModel.onFailureTarget;\n112:   const effectiveFailureKind = failureKind ?? failedModel.failureKind;\n113: \n114:   if (typeof configuredTarget === 'string') {\n115:     return { target: configuredTarget, kind: 'failure', failureKind: effectiveFailureKind };\n116:   }\n117: \n118:   if (isFailureTargets(configuredTarget)) {\n119:     const mappedTarget =\n120:       effectiveFailureKind === undefined\n121:         ? configuredTarget.default ?? null\n122:         : configuredTarget[effectiveFailureKind] ?? configuredTarget.default ?? null;\n123: \n124:     return {\n125:       target: mappedTarget,\n126:       kind: 'failure',\n127:       failureKind: effectiveFailureKind,\n128:     };\n129:   }\n130: \n131:   return {\n132:     target: failedModel.fallback_target,\n133:     kind: 'legacy',\n134:     failureKind: effectiveFailureKind,\n135:   };\n136: }\n137: \n138: function selectTarget(failedModel: ModelProfile, context: FallbackRouteContext | undefined): TargetSelection {\n139:   if (context?.outcome === 'success' && failedModel.onSuccessTarget !== undefined) {\n140:     return {\n141:       target: failedModel.onSuccessTarget,\n142:       kind: 'success',\n143:       failureKind: context.failureKind ?? failedModel.failureKind,\n144:     };\n145:   }\n146: \n147:   return selectFailureTarget(failedModel, context?.failureKind);\n148: }\n149: \n150: function createTrace(\n151:   failedModelId: string,\n152:   context: FallbackRouteContext | undefined,\n153: ): Pick<FallbackRoute, 'routeGroupId' | 'hopIndex'> | undefined {\n154:   if (context === undefined) return undefined;\n155: \n156:   return {\n157:     routeGroupId: context.routeGroupId ?? `${failedModelId}:${context.failureKind ?? context.outcome ?? 'fallback'}`,\n158:     hopIndex: context.hopIndex ?? 0,\n159:   };\n160: }\n161: \n162: function withRouteMetadata(\n163:   route: FallbackRoute,\n164:   trace: Pick<FallbackRoute, 'routeGroupId' | 'hopIndex'> | undefined,\n165:   failureKind: FallbackFailureKind | undefined,\n166: ): FallbackRoute {\n167:   if (trace === undefined && failureKind === undefined) return route;\n168: \n169:   return {\n170:     ...route,\n171:     ...(failureKind === undefined ? {} : { failureKind }),\n172:     ...trace,\n173:   };\n174: }\n175: \n176: function describeTargetKind(selection: TargetSelection): string {\n177:   if (selection.kind === 'success') return 'success target';\n178:   if (selection.kind === 'failure') return 'failure target';\n179:   return 'fallback';\n180: }\n181: \n182: function collectTargets(profile: ModelProfile): readonly FallbackEdge[] {\n183:   const edges: FallbackEdge[] = [];\n184: \n185:   if (profile.fallback_target !== null) {\n186:     edges.push({ source: profile, targetId: profile.fallback_target, kind: 'legacy' });\n187:   }\n188: \n189:   if (profile.onSuccessTarget !== undefined && profile.onSuccessTarget !== null) {\n190:     edges.push({ source: profile, targetId: profile.onSuccessTarget, kind: 'success' });\n191:   }\n192: \n193:   if (typeof profile.onFailureTarget === 'string') {\n194:     edges.push({\n195:       source: profile,\n196:       targetId: profile.onFailureTarget,\n197:       kind: 'failure',\n198:       failureKind: profile.failureKind,\n199:     });\n200:   } else if (isFailureTargets(profile.onFailureTarget)) {\n201:     for (const [failureKind, targetId] of Object.entries(profile.onFailureTarget)) {\n202:       if (targetId !== undefined) {\n203:         edges.push({ source: profile, targetId, kind: 'failure', failureKind });\n204:       }\n205:     }\n206:   }\n207: \n208:   return edges;\n209: }\n210: \n211: function buildEdges(registry: ModelRegistry): readonly FallbackEdge[] {\n212:   return registry.models.flatMap((profile) => collectTargets(profile));\n213: }\n214: \n215: function assertKnownTargets(registry: ModelRegistry, edges: readonly FallbackEdge[]): void {\n216:   for (const edge of edges) {\n217:     if (findModel(registry, edge.targetId) === undefined) {\n218:       throw new Error(`fallback graph references missing ${edge.kind} target ${edge.targetId} from ${edge.source.id}`);\n219:     }\n220:   }\n221: }\n222: \n223: function assertScopesDoNotWiden(registry: ModelRegistry, edges: readonly FallbackEdge[]): void {\n224:   for (const edge of edges) {\n225:     const target = findModel(registry, edge.targetId);\n226:     if (target === undefined) continue;\n227: \n228:     const hasScopedEdge = edge.source.routeScope !== undefined || target.routeScope !== undefined;\n229:     if (hasScopedEdge && edge.source.routeScope !== target.routeScope) {\n230:       throw new Error(`fallback graph cross-scope route rejected from ${edge.source.id} to ${target.id}`);\n231:     }\n232:   }\n233: }\n234: \n235: function assertNoCycles(edges: readonly FallbackEdge[]): void {\n236:   const adjacency = new Map<string, readonly string[]>();\n237:   for (const edge of edges) {\n238:     adjacency.set(edge.source.id, [...(adjacency.get(edge.source.id) ?? []), edge.targetId]);\n239:   }\n240: \n241:   const visiting = new Set<string>();\n242:   const visited = new Set<string>();\n243: \n244:   function visit(modelId: string, path: readonly string[]): void {\n245:     if (visiting.has(modelId)) {\n246:       throw new Error(`fallback graph cycle detected: ${[...path, modelId].join(' -> ')}`);\n247:     }\n248: \n249:     if (visited.has(modelId)) return;\n250: \n251:     visiting.add(modelId);\n252:     for (const targetId of adjacency.get(modelId) ?? []) {\n253:       visit(targetId, [...path, modelId]);\n254:     }\n255:     visiting.delete(modelId);\n256:     visited.add(modelId);\n257:   }\n258: \n259:   for (const sourceId of adjacency.keys()) {\n260:     visit(sourceId, []);\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 431. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Deep-Loop Fallback Router\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport type FallbackAction = 'fallback' | 'fail-fast';\n\n/** Executor result category used by typed fallback route selection. */\nexport type FallbackRouteOutcome = 'success' | 'failure';\n\n/** Failure classes that can select a targeted fallback route. */\nexport type FallbackFailureKind =\n  | 'timeout'\n  | 'auth-failure'\n  | 'quota-exceeded'\n  | 'executor-error'\n  | (string & {});","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Deep-Loop Fallback Router\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport type FallbackAction = 'fallback' | 'fail-fast';\n\n/** Executor result category used by typed fallback route selection. */\nexport type FallbackRouteOutcome = 'success' | 'failure';\n\n/** Failure classes that can select a targeted fallback route. */\nexport type FallbackFailureKind =\n  | 'timeout'\n  | 'auth-failure'\n  | 'quota-exceeded'\n  | 'executor-error'\n  | (string & {});\n\n/** Per-failure target map for typed fallback routes. */\nexport interface FallbackFailureTargets {\n  readonly default?: string;\n  readonly [failureKind: string]: string | undefined;\n}\n\n/** Fallback decision returned to dispatch callers. */\nexport type FallbackRoute = {\n  readonly action: FallbackAction;\n  readonly target?: string;\n  readonly reason: string;\n  readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n  readonly routeGroupId?: string;\n  readonly hopIndex?: number;\n};\n\n/** Runtime context attached to a routed fallback decision. */\nexport interface FallbackRouteContext {\n  readonly outcome?: FallbackRouteOutcome;\n  readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n  readonly routeGroupId?: string;\n  readonly hopIndex?: number;\n}\n\n/** Model routing profile used by fallback graph resolution. */\nexport type ModelProfile = {\n  readonly id: string;\n  readonly quota_pool: string;\n  readonly fallback_target: string | null;\n  readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n  readonly onSuccessTarget?: string | null;\n  readonly onFailureTarget?: string | FallbackFailureTargets | null;\n  readonly routeScope?: string;\n};\n\n/** Registry of model profiles available to the fallback router. */\nexport type ModelRegistry = {\n  readonly models: readonly ModelProfile[];\n};\n\n/** Configuration for validating fallback graph edges before dispatch. */\nexport interface FallbackGraphValidationOptions {\n  readonly maxHops?: number;\n}\n\n/** Validated router that binds a registry after graph preflight. */\nexport interface FallbackRouter {\n  resolve(\n    failedModelId: string,\n    approvedModelIds?: readonly string[],\n    context?: FallbackRouteContext,\n  ): FallbackRoute;\n}\n\ntype TargetKind = 'legacy' | 'success' | 'failure';\n\ninterface TargetSelection {\n  readonly target: string | null;\n  readonly kind: TargetKind;\n  readonly failureKind?: FallbackFailureKind;\n}\n\ninterface FallbackEdge {\n  readonly source: ModelProfile;\n  readonly targetId: string;\n  readonly kind: TargetKind;\n  readonly failureKind?: string;\n}\n\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_HOPS = 1;\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. HELPERS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction findModel(registry: ModelRegistry, modelId: string): ModelProfile | undefined {\n  return registry.models.find((model) => model.id === modelId);\n}\n\nfunction isFailureTargets(\n  value: string | FallbackFailureTargets | null | undefined,\n): value is FallbackFailureTargets {\n  return typeof value === 'object' && value !== null;\n}\n\nfunction selectFailureTarget(\n  failedModel: ModelProfile,\n  failureKind: FallbackFailureKind | undefined,\n): TargetSelection {\n  const configuredTarget = failedModel.onFailureTarget;\n  const effectiveFailureKind = failureKind ?? failedModel.failureKind;\n\n  if (typeof configuredTarget === 'string') {\n    return { target: configuredTarget, kind: 'failure', failureKind: effectiveFailureKind };\n  }\n\n  if (isFailureTargets(configuredTarget)) {\n    const mappedTarget =\n      effectiveFailureKind === undefined\n        ? configuredTarget.default ?? null\n        : configuredTarget[effectiveFailureKind] ?? configuredTarget.default ?? null;\n\n    return {\n      target: mappedTarget,\n      kind: 'failure',\n      failureKind: effectiveFailureKind,\n    };\n  }\n\n  return {\n    target: failedModel.fallback_target,\n    kind: 'legacy',\n    failureKind: effectiveFailureKind,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction selectTarget(failedModel: ModelProfile, context: FallbackRouteContext | undefined): TargetSelection {\n  if (context?.outcome === 'success' && failedModel.onSuccessTarget !== undefined) {\n    return {\n      target: failedModel.onSuccessTarget,\n      kind: 'success',\n      failureKind: context.failureKind ?? failedModel.failureKind,\n    };\n  }\n\n  return selectFailureTarget(failedModel, context?.failureKind);\n}\n\nfunction createTrace(\n  failedModelId: string,\n  context: FallbackRouteContext | undefined,\n): Pick<FallbackRoute, 'routeGroupId' | 'hopIndex'> | undefined {\n  if (context === undefined) return undefined;\n\n  return {\n    routeGroupId: context.routeGroupId ?? `${failedModelId}:${context.failureKind ?? context.outcome ?? 'fallback'}`,\n    hopIndex: context.hopIndex ?? 0,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction withRouteMetadata(\n  route: FallbackRoute,\n  trace: Pick<FallbackRoute, 'routeGroupId' | 'hopIndex'> | undefined,\n  failureKind: FallbackFailureKind | undefined,\n): FallbackRoute {\n  if (trace === undefined && failureKind === undefined) return route;\n\n  return {\n    ...route,\n    ...(failureKind === undefined ? {} : { failureKind }),\n    ...trace,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction describeTargetKind(selection: TargetSelection): string {\n  if (selection.kind === 'success') return 'success target';\n  if (selection.kind === 'failure') return 'failure target';\n  return 'fallback';\n}\n\nfunction collectTargets(profile: ModelProfile): readonly FallbackEdge[] {\n  const edges: FallbackEdge[] = [];\n\n  if (profile.fallback_target !== null) {\n    edges.push({ source: profile, targetId: profile.fallback_target, kind: 'legacy' });\n  }\n\n  if (profile.onSuccessTarget !== undefined && profile.onSuccessTarget !== null) {\n    edges.push({ source: profile, targetId: profile.onSuccessTarget, kind: 'success' });\n  }\n\n  if (typeof profile.onFailureTarget === 'string') {\n    edges.push({\n      source: profile,\n      targetId: profile.onFailureTarget,\n      kind: 'failure',\n      failureKind: profile.failureKind,\n    });\n  } else if (isFailureTargets(profile.onFailureTarget)) {\n    for (const [failureKind, targetId] of Object.entries(profile.onFailureTarget)) {\n      if (targetId !== undefined) {\n        edges.push({ source: profile, targetId, kind: 'failure', failureKind });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return edges;\n}\n\nfunction buildEdges(registry: ModelRegistry): readonly FallbackEdge[] {\n  return registry.models.flatMap((profile) => collectTargets(profile));\n}\n\nfunction assertKnownTargets(registry: ModelRegistry, edges: readonly FallbackEdge[]): void {\n  for (const edge of edges) {\n    if (findModel(registry, edge.targetId) === undefined) {\n      throw new Error(`fallback graph references missing ${edge.kind} target ${edge.targetId} from ${edge.source.id}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfunction assertScopesDoNotWiden(registry: ModelRegistry, edges: readonly FallbackEdge[]): void {\n  for (const edge of edges) {\n    const target = findModel(registry, edge.targetId);\n    if (target === undefined) continue;\n\n    const hasScopedEdge = edge.source.routeScope !== undefined || target.routeScope !== undefined;\n    if (hasScopedEdge && edge.source.routeScope !== target.routeScope) {\n      throw new Error(`fallback graph cross-scope route rejected from ${edge.source.id} to ${target.id}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfunction assertNoCycles(edges: readonly FallbackEdge[]): void {\n  const adjacency = new Map<string, readonly string[]>();\n  for (const edge of edges) {\n    adjacency.set(edge.source.id, [...(adjacency.get(edge.source.id) ?? []), edge.targetId]);\n  }\n\n  const visiting = new Set<string>();\n  const visited = new Set<string>();\n\n  function visit(modelId: string, path: readonly string[]): void {\n    if (visiting.has(modelId)) {\n      throw new Error(`fallback graph cycle detected: ${[...path, modelId].join(' -> ')}`);\n    }\n\n    if (visited.has(modelId)) return;\n\n    visiting.add(modelId);\n    for (const targetId of adjacency.get(modelId) ?? []) {\n      visit(targetId, [...path, modelId]);\n    }\n    visiting.delete(modelId);\n    visited.add(modelId);\n  }\n\n  for (const sourceId of adjacency.keys()) {\n    visit(sourceId, []);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":431,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts","time":{"start":1783486731326,"end":1783486731347}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cb781f35fd74d7f016a4dd909cf4881919ab2375309c6fc2d"}},"id":"prt_f4017d436001VE7j43xP490Gno","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffeH0lBIVcE9YycJ4","messageID":"msg_f4017a9e4001pEEavI0qn5pDNp"}}
