p-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural move and bidirectional path-coupling stress test\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.68,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Second pass added concrete risk decomposition for forward coupling, reverse coupling, system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, and metadata consolidation.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Does the structural merge plan cover both path-coupling directions?\",\"What validation must run before child 002 can claim done?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Does the structural merge plan cover both path-coupling directions?\",\"What validation must run before child 002 can claim done?\"],\"findingDetails\":[{\"id\":\"G55F5-F005\",\"title\":\"Forward runtime-to-workflows coupling is explicitly mapped and mostly preserves hop count while deleting the old segment\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:68\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:72\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:75\"]},{\"id\":\"G55F5-F006\",\"title\":\"Reverse workflows-to-runtime coupling needs a different hop-count rule and is not safe as a blanket string rewrite\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:78\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:82\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:88\"]},{\"id\":\"G55F5-F007\",\"title\":\"The system-spec-kit tooling-borrow path repair is load-bearing and correctly kept in child 002 rather than deferred\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-l