":true,\"resolved_route\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring, GLM-to-MiMo risk, and stop decision\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.18,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Fourth pass mainly confirmed previous risks and added the concrete fallback-router gap; all key questions now have source-backed answers.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is automatic GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback already wired?\",\"Should fallback wiring block the structural merge?\",\"Has the research reached legal convergence?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is automatic GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback already wired?\",\"Should fallback wiring block the structural merge?\",\"Has the research reached legal convergence?\"],\"findingDetails\":[{\"id\":\"G55F5-F014\",\"title\":\"The fallback router module is implemented and validates missing targets, cycles, scopes, hop count, approval, and same-pool rejection\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:320\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:400\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411\"]},{\"id\":\"G55F5-F015\",\"title\":\"Fanout retry exhaustion currently settles failure instead of resolving a fallback target\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:653\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:43\"]},{\"id\":\"G55F5-F016\",\"title\":\"The live model registry has both GLM and MiMo active in separate pools, but both fallback_target fields are null\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:203\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:268\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]},{\"id\":\"G55F5-F017\",\"title\":\"Fallback wiring is correctly tracked as optional and should not block child 002 or 003 unless the operator changes scope\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:51\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:85\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:124\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Treat GLM-to-MiMo fallback as already active during fan-out\",\"reason\":\"The registry has null fallback targets and fanout-pool settles retry-exhausted failures without calling resolveFallback.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269; .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"},{\"approach\":\"Block the structural rename on fallback wiring\",\"reason\":\"The fallback plan is explicitly optional and awaits an operator scope decision; structural and reference migration plans already account for current retry-and-salvage behavior.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:51\"}],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"question\",\"id\":\"q-fallback\",\"label\":\"Is GLM-to-MiMo fallback wired today?\"},{\"type\":\"question\",\"id\":\"q-stop\",\"label\":\"Can this lineage stop?\"},{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"G55F5-F015\",\"label\":\"Fanout retry exhaustion does not resolve fallback\"},{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"G55F5-F017\",\"label\":\"Fallback wiring remains optional\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"from\":\"G55F5-F015\",\"to\":\"q-fallback\",\"relation\":\"ANSWERS\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"from\":\"G55F5-F017\",\"to\":\"q-stop\",\"relation\":\"SUPPORTS\"}],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.4267,\"madScore\":0.71,\"entropyCoverage\":1,\"compositeStop\":0.77},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:40Z\",\"durationMs\":30000}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"legal_stop_evaluated\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":4,\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":\"pass\",\"coverageGate\":\"pass\",\"qualityGate\":\"pass\",\"graphGate\":\"pass\"},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:45Z\"}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"phase_synthesis\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-5-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"totalIterations\":4,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:50Z\",\"status\":\"complete\"}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,52 @@\n+# Deep Research Strategy: gpt55-fast-5\n+\n+## Research Topic\n+\n+Validate the planned merge of `deep-loop-workflows` and `deep-loop-runtime` into `system-deep-loop`, with emphasis on structural layout, bidirectional path repair, system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, external reference migration, and GLM-to-MiMo fallback assumptions.\n+\n+## Known Context\n+\n+- The reference phase is read-only investigation; it may create research artifacts but must not execute the merge. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68]\n+- Child 002 owns the irreversible move and runtime nesting after this research phase. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:14]\n+- Child 003 owns dependency-ordered external reference migration after child 002 lands. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:150]\n+- Child 004 tracks fallback-router wiring as optional and blocked on operator scope decision. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:51]\n+- `resource-map.md` was not present at init; this lineage emits its own coverage map after synthesis.\n+\n+## Key Questions\n+\n+- Does the structural merge plan cover both path-coupling directions and the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow?\n+- Is the external reference migration plan broad enough for generated routing projections, tests, command contracts, agents, docs, and examples?\n+- Is GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro automatic fallback already live, and should it block the merge?\n+- What validation gates should be treated as non-negotiable before child 002/003 completion claims?\n+\n+## Answered Questions\n+\n+- The structural plan covers Class A forward coupling, Class B reverse coupling, tooling-borrow, graph-metadata consolidation, and live validation gates.\n+- The reference migration plan correctly treats advisor projections, command contracts, generated outputs, ledgers, system-spec-kit consumers, and sk-doc examples as migration-critical.\n+- Automatic GLM-to-MiMo fallback is not live: the fallback router exists, fanout-pool does not call it on retry exhaustion, and the model registry has null fallback targets for both models.\n+- The fallback wiring phase should remain optional unless the operator explicitly changes scope.\n+\n+## What Worked\n+\n+- Dependency-ordered reading of phase specs before code/data hotspots avoided a false assumption that command YAML was the whole migration surface.\n+- Direct `verify-iteration.cjs --artifact-dir` validation is compatible with the lineage-only write boundary.\n+- Grep-scoped evidence across advisor, command, system-spec-kit, sk-doc, workflow, and runtime folders exposed the broad reference blast radius.\n+\n+## What Failed\n+\n+- `reduce-state.cjs` was not used because it resolves canonical research roots rather than the requested detached lineage root.\n+- No live fallback dispatch was exercised; the relevant finding is static evidence only.\n+\n+## Exhausted Approaches\n+\n+- Using canonical reducers for this detached lineage: rejected because the user constrained writes to `artifact_dir` and asked not to run `resolveArtifactRoot`.\n+- Treating stale `deep-loop-workflows` and `deep-loop-runtime` references under specs as migration targets: rejected because child 003 marks `.opencode/specs/**` historical and untouched.\n+\n+## Ruled-Out Directions\n+\n+- Treat GLM-to-MiMo fallback as already active during fan-out. Evidence shows null registry fallback targets and no `resolveFallback` call in `fanout-pool.cjs`.\n+- Block the structural rename on fallback wiring. The fallback phase is optional and blocked on an operator scope decision.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Stop. All key questions have source-backed answers and the fourth iteration passed the convergence, coverage, quality, and graph gates.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,43 @@\n+# Deep Research Dashboard: gpt55-fast-5\n+\n+## Iteration Table\n+\n+| Iteration | Focus | Findings | newInfoRatio | Stop Score | Status |\n+|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---|\n+| 001 | Baseline topology, scope, and current contracts | 4 | 1.00 | 0.12 | complete |\n+| 002 | Structural move and bidirectional path-coupling stress test | 4 | 0.68 | 0.31 | complete |\n+| 003 | External reference migration and advisor/routing blast radius | 5 | 0.42 | 0.55 | complete |\n+| 004 | Fallback-router wiring, GLM-to-MiMo risk, and stop decision | 4 | 0.18 | 0.77 | complete |\n+\n+## Question Status\n+\n+| Question | Status | Evidence |\n+|---|---|---|\n+| Structural path-coupling coverage | answered | G55F5-F005, G55F5-F006, G55F5-F007, G55F5-F008 |\n+| External reference migration completeness | answered | G55F5-F009, G55F5-F010, G55F5-F011, G55F5-F012, G55F5-F013 |\n+| GLM-to-MiMo fallback status | answered | G55F5-F014, G55F5-F015, G55F5-F016, G55F5-F017 |\n+| Merge-blocking decisions | answered | Fallback wiring remains optional unless operator expands scope |\n+\n+## Convergence Trend\n+\n+- Novelty dropped from 1.00 to 0.18 across four iterations.\n+- Composite stop score reached 0.77 in iteration 004.\n+- Legal-stop gates passed: convergence, coverage, quality, graph.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Canonical reducer path for this detached lineage: not used because it would resolve outside the allowed artifact directory.\n+- Automatic GLM-to-MiMo fallback assumption: ruled out by registry and pool evidence.\n+\n+## Blocked Stops\n+\n+- None. No STOP candidate was blocked.\n+\n+## Graph Convergence\n+\n+- Key question nodes `q-scope`, `q-topology`, `q-structural`, `q-references`, `q-fallback`, and `q-stop` each have answering findings.\n+- No graph-aware stop blocker remains.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Stop and feed findings into cross-lineage fan-out merge.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-5/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,170 @@\n+{\n+  \"schemaVersion\": \"deep-research-findings-registry.v1\",\n+  \"lineage\": \"gpt55-fast-5\",\n+  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55-fast-5-1783486518892-2qss01\",\n+  \"updatedAt\": \"2026-07-08T05:01:50Z\",\n+  \"metrics\": {\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 4,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.77,\n+    \"newInfoRatios\": [1, 0.68, 0.42, 0.18],\n+    \"stopReason\": \"converged\"\n+  },\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"G55F5-F001\",\n+      \"iteration\": 1,\n+      \"title\": \"Reference phase is read-only and artifact-scoped\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The phase explicitly creates research outputs and lineage packets while excluding merge execution or runtime/workflow modifications.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68\",\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec